72 /// isFunctionOrMethod - Return true if the given decl has function
73 /// type (function or function-typed variable) or an Objective-C
74 /// method.
75 static bool isFunctionOrMethod(const Decl *D) {
76  return (D->getFunctionType() != nullptr) || isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
77 }
78 
79 /// Return true if the given decl has function type (function or
80 /// function-typed variable) or an Objective-C method or a block.
81 static bool isFunctionOrMethodOrBlock(const Decl *D) {
82  return isFunctionOrMethod(D) || isa<BlockDecl>(D);
83 }
84 
85 /// Return true if the given decl has a declarator that should have
86 /// been processed by Sema::GetTypeForDeclarator.
87 static bool hasDeclarator(const Decl *D) {
88  // In some sense, TypedefDecl really *ought* to be a DeclaratorDecl.
89  return isa<DeclaratorDecl>(D) || isa<BlockDecl>(D) || isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D) ||
90  isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D);
91 }
92 
93 /// hasFunctionProto - Return true if the given decl has a argument
94 /// information. This decl should have already passed
95 /// isFunctionOrMethod or isFunctionOrMethodOrBlock.
96 static bool hasFunctionProto(const Decl *D) {
97  if (const FunctionType *FnTy = D->getFunctionType())
98  return isa<FunctionProtoType>(FnTy);
99  return isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) || isa<BlockDecl>(D);
100 }
101 
102 /// getFunctionOrMethodNumParams - Return number of function or method
103 /// parameters. It is an error to call this on a K&R function (use
104 /// hasFunctionProto first).
105 static unsigned getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(const Decl *D) {
106  if (const FunctionType *FnTy = D->getFunctionType())
107  return cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnTy)->getNumParams();
108  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D))
109  return BD->getNumParams();
110  return cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->param_size();
111 }
112 
113 static const ParmVarDecl *getFunctionOrMethodParam(const Decl *D,
114  unsigned Idx) {
115  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
116  return FD->getParamDecl(Idx);
117  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
118  return MD->getParamDecl(Idx);
119  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D))
120  return BD->getParamDecl(Idx);
121  return nullptr;
122 }
123 
124 static QualType getFunctionOrMethodParamType(const Decl *D, unsigned Idx) {
125  if (const FunctionType *FnTy = D->getFunctionType())
126  return cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnTy)->getParamType(Idx);
127  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D))
128  return BD->getParamDecl(Idx)->getType();
129 
130  return cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->parameters()[Idx]->getType();
131 }
132 
133 static SourceRange getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(const Decl *D, unsigned Idx) {
134  if (auto *PVD = getFunctionOrMethodParam(D, Idx))
135  return PVD->getSourceRange();
136  return SourceRange();
137 }
138 
139 static QualType getFunctionOrMethodResultType(const Decl *D) {
140  if (const FunctionType *FnTy = D->getFunctionType())
141  return FnTy->getReturnType();
142  return cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->getReturnType();
143 }
144 
145 static SourceRange getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(const Decl *D) {
146  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
147  return FD->getReturnTypeSourceRange();
148  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
149  return MD->getReturnTypeSourceRange();
150  return SourceRange();
151 }
152 
153 static bool isFunctionOrMethodVariadic(const Decl *D) {
154  if (const FunctionType *FnTy = D->getFunctionType())
155  return cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnTy)->isVariadic();
156  if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D))
157  return BD->isVariadic();
158  return cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->isVariadic();
159 }
160 
161 static bool isInstanceMethod(const Decl *D) {
162  if (const auto *MethodDecl = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
163  return MethodDecl->isInstance();
164  return false;
165 }
166 
167 static inline bool isNSStringType(QualType T, ASTContext &Ctx,
168  bool AllowNSAttributedString = false) {
169  const auto *PT = T->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
170  if (!PT)
171  return false;
172 
173  ObjCInterfaceDecl *Cls = PT->getObjectType()->getInterface();
174  if (!Cls)
175  return false;
176 
177  IdentifierInfo* ClsName = Cls->getIdentifier();
178 
179  if (AllowNSAttributedString &&
180  ClsName == &Ctx.Idents.get("NSAttributedString"))
181  return true;
182  // FIXME: Should we walk the chain of classes?
183  return ClsName == &Ctx.Idents.get("NSString") ||
184  ClsName == &Ctx.Idents.get("NSMutableString");
185 }
186 
187 static inline bool isCFStringType(QualType T, ASTContext &Ctx) {
188  const auto *PT = T->getAs<PointerType>();
189  if (!PT)
190  return false;
191 
192  const auto *RT = PT->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>();
193  if (!RT)
194  return false;
195 
196  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
197  if (RD->getTagKind() != TagTypeKind::Struct)
198  return false;
199 
200  return RD->getIdentifier() == &Ctx.Idents.get("__CFString");
201 }

203 static unsigned getNumAttributeArgs(const ParsedAttr &AL) {
204  // FIXME: Include the type in the argument list.
205  return AL.getNumArgs() + AL.hasParsedType();
206 }

208 /// A helper function to provide Attribute Location for the Attr types
209 /// AND the ParsedAttr.
210 template <typename AttrInfo>
211 static std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of_v<Attr, AttrInfo>, SourceLocation>
212 getAttrLoc(const AttrInfo &AL) {
213  return AL.getLocation();
214 }
215 static SourceLocation getAttrLoc(const ParsedAttr &AL) { return AL.getLoc(); }
216 
217 /// If Expr is a valid integer constant, get the value of the integer
218 /// expression and return success or failure. May output an error.
219 ///
220 /// Negative argument is implicitly converted to unsigned, unless
221 /// \p StrictlyUnsigned is true.
222 template <typename AttrInfo>
223 static bool checkUInt32Argument(Sema &S, const AttrInfo &AI, const Expr *Expr,
224  uint32_t &Val, unsigned Idx = UINT_MAX,
225  bool StrictlyUnsigned = false) {
226  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> I = llvm::APSInt(32);
227  if (Expr->isTypeDependent() ||
228  !(I = Expr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
229  if (Idx != UINT_MAX)
230  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
231  << &AI << Idx << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
232  << Expr->getSourceRange();
233  else
234  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
235  << &AI << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << Expr->getSourceRange();
236  return false;
237  }
238 
239  if (!I->isIntN(32)) {
240  S.Diag(Expr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_ice_too_large)
241  << toString(*I, 10, false) << 32 << /* Unsigned */ 1;
242  return false;
243  }
244 
245  if (StrictlyUnsigned && I->isSigned() && I->isNegative()) {
246  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
247  << &AI << /*non-negative*/ 1;
248  return false;
249  }
250 
251  Val = (uint32_t)I->getZExtValue();
252  return true;
253 }
254 
255 /// Wrapper around checkUInt32Argument, with an extra check to be sure
256 /// that the result will fit into a regular (signed) int. All args have the same
257 /// purpose as they do in checkUInt32Argument.
258 template <typename AttrInfo>
259 static bool checkPositiveIntArgument(Sema &S, const AttrInfo &AI, const Expr *Expr,
260  int &Val, unsigned Idx = UINT_MAX) {
261  uint32_t UVal;
262  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AI, Expr, UVal, Idx))
263  return false;
264 
265  if (UVal > (uint32_t)std::numeric_limits<int>::max()) {
266  llvm::APSInt I(32); // for toString
267  I = UVal;
268  S.Diag(Expr->getExprLoc(), diag::err_ice_too_large)
269  << toString(I, 10, false) << 32 << /* Unsigned */ 0;
270  return false;
271  }
272 
273  Val = UVal;
274  return true;
275 }
276 
277 /// Diagnose mutually exclusive attributes when present on a given
278 /// declaration. Returns true if diagnosed.
279 template <typename AttrTy>
280 static bool checkAttrMutualExclusion(Sema &S, Decl *D,
281  const AttributeCommonInfo &AL) {
282  if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AttrTy>()) {
283  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
284  << AL << A
285  << (AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() || A->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
286  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
287  return true;
288  }
289  return false;
290 }
291 
292 template <typename AttrTy>
293 static bool checkAttrMutualExclusion(Sema &S, Decl *D, const Attr &AL) {
294  if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AttrTy>()) {
295  S.Diag(AL.getLocation(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
296  << &AL << A
297  << (AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() || A->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
298  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
299  return true;
300  }
301  return false;
302 }
303 
304 void Sema::DiagnoseDeprecatedAttribute(const ParsedAttr &A, StringRef NewScope,
305  StringRef NewName) {
306  assert((!NewName.empty() || !NewScope.empty()) &&
307  "Deprecated attribute with no new scope or name?");
308  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_spelling_deprecated)
309  << "'" + A.getNormalizedFullName() + "'";
310 
311  FixItHint Fix;
312  std::string NewFullName;
313  if (NewScope.empty() && !NewName.empty()) {
314  // Only have a new name.
315  Fix = FixItHint::CreateReplacement(A.getLoc(), NewName);
316  NewFullName =
317  ((A.hasScope() ? A.getScopeName()->getName() : StringRef("")) +
318  "::" + NewName)
319  .str();
320  } else if (NewName.empty() && !NewScope.empty()) {
321  // Only have a new scope.
322  Fix = FixItHint::CreateReplacement(A.getScopeLoc(), NewScope);
323  NewFullName = (NewScope + "::" + A.getAttrName()->getName()).str();
324  } else {
325  // Have both a new name and a new scope.
326  NewFullName = (NewScope + "::" + NewName).str();
327  Fix = FixItHint::CreateReplacement(A.getRange(), NewFullName);
328  }
329 
330  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_spelling_suggestion)
331  << "'" + NewFullName + "'" << Fix;
332 }
333 
334 void Sema::CheckDeprecatedSYCLAttributeSpelling(const ParsedAttr &A,
335  StringRef NewName) {
336  // Additionally, diagnose the old [[intel::ii]] spelling.
337  if (A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_SYCLIntelInitiationInterval &&
338  A.getAttrName()->isStr("ii")) {
339  DiagnoseDeprecatedAttribute(A, "intel", "initiation_interval");
340  return;
341  }
342 
343  // Diagnose SYCL 2017 spellings in later SYCL modes.
344  if (LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() > LangOptions::SYCL_2017) {
345  // All attributes in the cl vendor namespace are deprecated in favor of a
346  // name in the sycl namespace as of SYCL 2020.
347  if (A.hasScope() && A.getScopeName()->isStr("cl")) {
348  DiagnoseDeprecatedAttribute(A, "sycl", NewName);
349  return;
350  }
351 
352  // All GNU-style spellings are deprecated in favor of a C++-style spelling.
353  if (A.getSyntax() == ParsedAttr::AS_GNU) {
354  // Note: we cannot suggest an automatic fix-it because GNU-style
355  // spellings can appear in locations that are not valid for a C++-style
356  // spelling, and the attribute could be part of an attribute list within
357  // a single __attribute__ specifier. Just tell the user it's deprecated
358  // manually.
359  //
360  // This currently assumes that the GNU-style spelling is the same as the
361  // SYCL 2020 spelling (sans the vendor namespace).
362  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_spelling_deprecated)
363  << "'" + A.getNormalizedFullName() + "'";
364  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_spelling_suggestion)
365  << "'[[sycl::" + A.getNormalizedFullName() + "]]'";
366  return;
367  }
368  }
369 
370  // Diagnose SYCL 2020 spellings used in earlier SYCL modes as being an
371  // extension.
372  if (LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() == LangOptions::SYCL_2017 && A.hasScope() &&
373  A.getScopeName()->isStr("sycl")) {
374  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::ext_sycl_2020_attr_spelling) << A;
375  return;
376  }
377 }
378 
379 /// Check if IdxExpr is a valid parameter index for a function or
380 /// instance method D. May output an error.
381 ///
382 /// \returns true if IdxExpr is a valid index.
383 template <typename AttrInfo>
384 static bool checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(
385  Sema &S, const Decl *D, const AttrInfo &AI, unsigned AttrArgNum,
386  const Expr *IdxExpr, ParamIdx &Idx, bool CanIndexImplicitThis = false) {
387  assert(isFunctionOrMethodOrBlock(D));
388 
389  // In C++ the implicit 'this' function parameter also counts.
390  // Parameters are counted from one.
391  bool HP = hasFunctionProto(D);
392  bool HasImplicitThisParam = isInstanceMethod(D);
393  bool IV = HP && isFunctionOrMethodVariadic(D);
394  unsigned NumParams =
395  (HP ? getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) : 0) + HasImplicitThisParam;
396 
397  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> IdxInt;
398  if (IdxExpr->isTypeDependent() ||
399  !(IdxInt = IdxExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
400  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
401  << &AI << AttrArgNum << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
402  << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
403  return false;
404  }
405 
406  unsigned IdxSource = IdxInt->getLimitedValue(UINT_MAX);
407  if (IdxSource < 1 || (!IV && IdxSource > NumParams)) {
408  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
409  << &AI << AttrArgNum << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
410  return false;
411  }
412  if (HasImplicitThisParam && !CanIndexImplicitThis) {
413  if (IdxSource == 1) {
414  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AI), diag::err_attribute_invalid_implicit_this_argument)
415  << &AI << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
416  return false;
417  }
418  }
419 
420  Idx = ParamIdx(IdxSource, D);
421  return true;
422 }
423 
424 /// Check if the argument \p E is a ASCII string literal. If not emit an error
425 /// and return false, otherwise set \p Str to the value of the string literal
426 /// and return true.
427 bool Sema::checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
428  const Expr *E, StringRef &Str,
429  SourceLocation *ArgLocation) {
430  const auto *Literal = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(E->IgnoreParenCasts());
431  if (ArgLocation)
432  *ArgLocation = E->getBeginLoc();
433 
434  if (!Literal || (!Literal->isUnevaluated() && !Literal->isOrdinary())) {
435  Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
436  << CI << AANT_ArgumentString;
437  return false;
438  }
439 
440  Str = Literal->getString();
441  return true;
442 }
443 
444 /// Check if the argument \p ArgNum of \p Attr is a ASCII string literal.
445 /// If not emit an error and return false. If the argument is an identifier it
446 /// will emit an error with a fixit hint and treat it as if it was a string
447 /// literal.
448 bool Sema::checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(const ParsedAttr &AL, unsigned ArgNum,
449  StringRef &Str,
450  SourceLocation *ArgLocation) {
451  // Look for identifiers. If we have one emit a hint to fix it to a literal.
452  if (AL.isArgIdent(ArgNum)) {
453  IdentifierLoc *Loc = AL.getArgAsIdent(ArgNum);
454  Diag(Loc->Loc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
455  << AL << AANT_ArgumentString
456  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc->Loc, "\"")
457  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(getLocForEndOfToken(Loc->Loc), "\"");
458  Str = Loc->Ident->getName();
459  if (ArgLocation)
460  *ArgLocation = Loc->Loc;
461  return true;
462  }
463 
464  // Now check for an actual string literal.
465  Expr *ArgExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(ArgNum);
466  const auto *Literal = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(ArgExpr->IgnoreParenCasts());
467  if (ArgLocation)
468  *ArgLocation = ArgExpr->getBeginLoc();
469 
470  if (!Literal || (!Literal->isUnevaluated() && !Literal->isOrdinary())) {
471  Diag(ArgExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
472  << AL << AANT_ArgumentString;
473  return false;
474  }
475  Str = Literal->getString();
476  return checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, ArgExpr, Str, ArgLocation);
477 }

479 /// Applies the given attribute to the Decl without performing any
480 /// additional semantic checking.
481 template <typename AttrType>
482 static void handleSimpleAttribute(Sema &S, Decl *D,
483  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
484  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AttrType(S.Context, CI));
485 }
486 
487 template <typename... DiagnosticArgs>
488 static const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder&
489 appendDiagnostics(const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder &Bldr) {
490  return Bldr;
491 }
492 
493 template <typename T, typename... DiagnosticArgs>
494 static const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder&
495 appendDiagnostics(const Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder &Bldr, T &&ExtraArg,
496  DiagnosticArgs &&... ExtraArgs) {
497  return appendDiagnostics(Bldr << std::forward<T>(ExtraArg),
498  std::forward<DiagnosticArgs>(ExtraArgs)...);
499 }
500 
501 /// Add an attribute @c AttrType to declaration @c D, provided that
502 /// @c PassesCheck is true.
503 /// Otherwise, emit diagnostic @c DiagID, passing in all parameters
504 /// specified in @c ExtraArgs.
505 template <typename AttrType, typename... DiagnosticArgs>
506 static void handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose(Sema &S, Decl *D,
507  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
508  bool PassesCheck, unsigned DiagID,
509  DiagnosticArgs &&... ExtraArgs) {
510  if (!PassesCheck) {
511  Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder DB = S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), DiagID);
512  appendDiagnostics(DB, std::forward<DiagnosticArgs>(ExtraArgs)...);
513  return;
514  }
515  handleSimpleAttribute<AttrType>(S, D, CI);
516 }

518 /// Check if the passed-in expression is of type int or bool.
519 static bool isIntOrBool(Expr *Exp) {
520  QualType QT = Exp->getType();
521  return QT->isBooleanType() || QT->isIntegerType();
522 }

524 
525 // Check to see if the type is a smart pointer of some kind. We assume
526 // it's a smart pointer if it defines both operator-> and operator*.
527 static bool threadSafetyCheckIsSmartPointer(Sema &S, const RecordType* RT) {
528  auto IsOverloadedOperatorPresent = [&S](const RecordDecl *Record,
529  OverloadedOperatorKind Op) {
530  DeclContextLookupResult Result =
531  Record->lookup(S.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(Op));
532  return !Result.empty();
533  };
534 
535  const RecordDecl *Record = RT->getDecl();
536  bool foundStarOperator = IsOverloadedOperatorPresent(Record, OO_Star);
537  bool foundArrowOperator = IsOverloadedOperatorPresent(Record, OO_Arrow);
538  if (foundStarOperator && foundArrowOperator)
539  return true;
540 
541  const CXXRecordDecl *CXXRecord = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Record);
542  if (!CXXRecord)
543  return false;
544 
545  for (const auto &BaseSpecifier : CXXRecord->bases()) {
546  if (!foundStarOperator)
547  foundStarOperator = IsOverloadedOperatorPresent(
548  BaseSpecifier.getType()->getAsRecordDecl(), OO_Star);
549  if (!foundArrowOperator)
550  foundArrowOperator = IsOverloadedOperatorPresent(
551  BaseSpecifier.getType()->getAsRecordDecl(), OO_Arrow);
552  }
553 
554  if (foundStarOperator && foundArrowOperator)
555  return true;
556 
557  return false;
558 }
559 
560 /// Check if passed in Decl is a pointer type.
561 /// Note that this function may produce an error message.
562 /// \return true if the Decl is a pointer type; false otherwise
563 static bool threadSafetyCheckIsPointer(Sema &S, const Decl *D,
564  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
565  const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
566  QualType QT = VD->getType();
567  if (QT->isAnyPointerType())
568  return true;
569 
570  if (const auto *RT = QT->getAs<RecordType>()) {
571  // If it's an incomplete type, it could be a smart pointer; skip it.
572  // (We don't want to force template instantiation if we can avoid it,
573  // since that would alter the order in which templates are instantiated.)
574  if (RT->isIncompleteType())
575  return true;
576 
577  if (threadSafetyCheckIsSmartPointer(S, RT))
578  return true;
579  }
580 
581  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_thread_attribute_decl_not_pointer) << AL << QT;
582  return false;
583 }
584 
585 /// Checks that the passed in QualType either is of RecordType or points
586 /// to RecordType. Returns the relevant RecordType, null if it does not exit.
587 static const RecordType *getRecordType(QualType QT) {
588  if (const auto *RT = QT->getAs<RecordType>())
589  return RT;
590 
591  // Now check if we point to record type.
592  if (const auto *PT = QT->getAs<PointerType>())
593  return PT->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>();
594 
595  return nullptr;
596 }
597 
598 template <typename AttrType>
599 static bool checkRecordDeclForAttr(const RecordDecl *RD) {
600  // Check if the record itself has the attribute.
601  if (RD->hasAttr<AttrType>())
602  return true;
603 
604  // Else check if any base classes have the attribute.
605  if (const auto *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
606  if (!CRD->forallBases([](const CXXRecordDecl *Base) {
607  return !Base->hasAttr<AttrType>();
608  }))
609  return true;
610  }
611  return false;
612 }
613 
614 static bool checkRecordTypeForCapability(Sema &S, QualType Ty) {
615  const RecordType *RT = getRecordType(Ty);
616 
617  if (!RT)
618  return false;
619 
620  // Don't check for the capability if the class hasn't been defined yet.
621  if (RT->isIncompleteType())
622  return true;
623 
624  // Allow smart pointers to be used as capability objects.
625  // FIXME -- Check the type that the smart pointer points to.
626  if (threadSafetyCheckIsSmartPointer(S, RT))
627  return true;
628 
629  return checkRecordDeclForAttr<CapabilityAttr>(RT->getDecl());
630 }
631 
632 static bool checkTypedefTypeForCapability(QualType Ty) {
633  const auto *TD = Ty->getAs<TypedefType>();
634  if (!TD)
635  return false;
636 
637  TypedefNameDecl *TN = TD->getDecl();
638  if (!TN)
639  return false;
640 
641  return TN->hasAttr<CapabilityAttr>();
642 }
643 
644 static bool typeHasCapability(Sema &S, QualType Ty) {
645  if (checkTypedefTypeForCapability(Ty))
646  return true;
647 
648  if (checkRecordTypeForCapability(S, Ty))
649  return true;
650 
651  return false;
652 }
653 
654 static bool isCapabilityExpr(Sema &S, const Expr *Ex) {
655  // Capability expressions are simple expressions involving the boolean logic
656  // operators &&, || or !, a simple DeclRefExpr, CastExpr or a ParenExpr. Once
657  // a DeclRefExpr is found, its type should be checked to determine whether it
658  // is a capability or not.
659 
660  if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(Ex))
661  return isCapabilityExpr(S, E->getSubExpr());
662  else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(Ex))
663  return isCapabilityExpr(S, E->getSubExpr());
664  else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Ex)) {
665  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_LNot || E->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf ||
666  E->getOpcode() == UO_Deref)
667  return isCapabilityExpr(S, E->getSubExpr());
668  return false;
669  } else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Ex)) {
670  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_LAnd || E->getOpcode() == BO_LOr)
671  return isCapabilityExpr(S, E->getLHS()) &&
672  isCapabilityExpr(S, E->getRHS());
673  return false;
674  }
675 
676  return typeHasCapability(S, Ex->getType());
677 }
678 
679 /// Checks that all attribute arguments, starting from Sidx, resolve to
680 /// a capability object.
681 /// \param Sidx The attribute argument index to start checking with.
682 /// \param ParamIdxOk Whether an argument can be indexing into a function
683 /// parameter list.
684 static void checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(Sema &S, Decl *D,
685  const ParsedAttr &AL,
686  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Args,
687  unsigned Sidx = 0,
688  bool ParamIdxOk = false) {
689  if (Sidx == AL.getNumArgs()) {
690  // If we don't have any capability arguments, the attribute implicitly
691  // refers to 'this'. So we need to make sure that 'this' exists, i.e. we're
692  // a non-static method, and that the class is a (scoped) capability.
693  const auto *MD = dyn_cast<const CXXMethodDecl>(D);
694  if (MD && !MD->isStatic()) {
695  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD->getParent();
696  // FIXME -- need to check this again on template instantiation
697  if (!checkRecordDeclForAttr<CapabilityAttr>(RD) &&
698  !checkRecordDeclForAttr<ScopedLockableAttr>(RD))
699  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
700  diag::warn_thread_attribute_not_on_capability_member)
701  << AL << MD->getParent();
702  } else {
703  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_thread_attribute_not_on_non_static_member)
704  << AL;
705  }
706  }
707 
708  for (unsigned Idx = Sidx; Idx < AL.getNumArgs(); ++Idx) {
709  Expr *ArgExp = AL.getArgAsExpr(Idx);
710 
711  if (ArgExp->isTypeDependent()) {
712  // FIXME -- need to check this again on template instantiation
713  Args.push_back(ArgExp);
714  continue;
715  }
716 
717  if (const auto *StrLit = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(ArgExp)) {
718  if (StrLit->getLength() == 0 ||
719  (StrLit->isOrdinary() && StrLit->getString() == StringRef("*"))) {
720  // Pass empty strings to the analyzer without warnings.
721  // Treat "*" as the universal lock.
722  Args.push_back(ArgExp);
723  continue;
724  }
725 
726  // We allow constant strings to be used as a placeholder for expressions
727  // that are not valid C++ syntax, but warn that they are ignored.
728  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_thread_attribute_ignored) << AL;
729  Args.push_back(ArgExp);
730  continue;
731  }
732 
733  QualType ArgTy = ArgExp->getType();
734 
735  // A pointer to member expression of the form &MyClass::mu is treated
736  // specially -- we need to look at the type of the member.
737  if (const auto *UOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(ArgExp))
738  if (UOp->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
739  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(UOp->getSubExpr()))
740  if (DRE->getDecl()->isCXXInstanceMember())
741  ArgTy = DRE->getDecl()->getType();
742 
743  // First see if we can just cast to record type, or pointer to record type.
744  const RecordType *RT = getRecordType(ArgTy);
745 
746  // Now check if we index into a record type function param.
747  if(!RT && ParamIdxOk) {
748  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
749  const auto *IL = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(ArgExp);
750  if(FD && IL) {
751  unsigned int NumParams = FD->getNumParams();
752  llvm::APInt ArgValue = IL->getValue();
753  uint64_t ParamIdxFromOne = ArgValue.getZExtValue();
754  uint64_t ParamIdxFromZero = ParamIdxFromOne - 1;
755  if (!ArgValue.isStrictlyPositive() || ParamIdxFromOne > NumParams) {
756  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
757  diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds_extra_info)
758  << AL << Idx + 1 << NumParams;
759  continue;
760  }
761  ArgTy = FD->getParamDecl(ParamIdxFromZero)->getType();
762  }
763  }
764 
765  // If the type does not have a capability, see if the components of the
766  // expression have capabilities. This allows for writing C code where the
767  // capability may be on the type, and the expression is a capability
768  // boolean logic expression. Eg) requires_capability(A || B && !C)
769  if (!typeHasCapability(S, ArgTy) && !isCapabilityExpr(S, ArgExp))
770  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_thread_attribute_argument_not_lockable)
771  << AL << ArgTy;
772 
773  Args.push_back(ArgExp);
774  }
775 }
776 
777 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
778 // Attribute Implementations
779 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
780 
781 static void handlePtGuardedVarAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
782  if (!threadSafetyCheckIsPointer(S, D, AL))
783  return;
784 
785  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PtGuardedVarAttr(S.Context, AL));
786 }
787 
788 static bool checkGuardedByAttrCommon(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
789  Expr *&Arg) {
790  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
791  // check that all arguments are lockable objects
792  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
793  unsigned Size = Args.size();
794  if (Size != 1)
795  return false;
796 
797  Arg = Args[0];
798 
799  return true;
800 }
801 
802 static void handleGuardedByAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
803  Expr *Arg = nullptr;
804  if (!checkGuardedByAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Arg))
805  return;
806 
807  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) GuardedByAttr(S.Context, AL, Arg));
808 }
809 
810 static void handlePtGuardedByAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
811  Expr *Arg = nullptr;
812  if (!checkGuardedByAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Arg))
813  return;
814 
815  if (!threadSafetyCheckIsPointer(S, D, AL))
816  return;
817 
818  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PtGuardedByAttr(S.Context, AL, Arg));
819 }
820 
821 static bool checkAcquireOrderAttrCommon(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
822  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Args) {
823  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
824  return false;
825 
826  // Check that this attribute only applies to lockable types.
827  QualType QT = cast<ValueDecl>(D)->getType();
828  if (!QT->isDependentType() && !typeHasCapability(S, QT)) {
829  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_thread_attribute_decl_not_lockable) << AL;
830  return false;
831  }
832 
833  // Check that all arguments are lockable objects.
834  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
835  if (Args.empty())
836  return false;
837 
838  return true;
839 }
840 
841 static void handleAcquiredAfterAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
842  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
843  if (!checkAcquireOrderAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
844  return;
845 
846  Expr **StartArg = &Args[0];
847  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
848  AcquiredAfterAttr(S.Context, AL, StartArg, Args.size()));
849 }
850 
851 static void handleAcquiredBeforeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
852  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
853  if (!checkAcquireOrderAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
854  return;
855 
856  Expr **StartArg = &Args[0];
857  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
858  AcquiredBeforeAttr(S.Context, AL, StartArg, Args.size()));
859 }
860 
861 static bool checkLockFunAttrCommon(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
862  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Args) {
863  // zero or more arguments ok
864  // check that all arguments are lockable objects
865  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args, 0, /*ParamIdxOk=*/true);
866 
867  return true;
868 }

870 static void handleAssertSharedLockAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
871  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
872  if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
873  return;
874 
875  unsigned Size = Args.size();
876  Expr **StartArg = Size == 0 ? nullptr : &Args[0];
877  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
878  AssertSharedLockAttr(S.Context, AL, StartArg, Size));
879 }

881 static void handleAssertExclusiveLockAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
882  const ParsedAttr &AL) {

884  if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
885  return;
886 
887  unsigned Size = Args.size();
888  Expr **StartArg = Size == 0 ? nullptr : &Args[0];
889  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
890  AssertExclusiveLockAttr(S.Context, AL, StartArg, Size));

892 
893 /// Checks to be sure that the given parameter number is in bounds, and
894 /// is an integral type. Will emit appropriate diagnostics if this returns
895 /// false.
896 ///
897 /// AttrArgNo is used to actually retrieve the argument, so it's base-0.
898 template <typename AttrInfo>
899 static bool checkParamIsIntegerType(Sema &S, const Decl *D, const AttrInfo &AI,
900  unsigned AttrArgNo) {
901  assert(AI.isArgExpr(AttrArgNo) && "Expected expression argument");
902  Expr *AttrArg = AI.getArgAsExpr(AttrArgNo);
903  ParamIdx Idx;
904  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AI, AttrArgNo + 1, AttrArg,
905  Idx))
906  return false;
907 
908  QualType ParamTy = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
909  if (!ParamTy->isIntegerType() && !ParamTy->isCharType()) {
910  SourceLocation SrcLoc = AttrArg->getBeginLoc();
911  S.Diag(SrcLoc, diag::err_attribute_integers_only)
912  << AI << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
913  return false;
914  }
915  return true;
916 }
917 
918 static void handleAllocSizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
919  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1) || !AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 2))
920  return;
921 
922  assert(isFunctionOrMethod(D) && hasFunctionProto(D));
923 
924  QualType RetTy = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
925  if (!RetTy->isPointerType()) {
926  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_return_pointers_only) << AL;
927  return;
928  }
929 
930  const Expr *SizeExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
931  int SizeArgNoVal;
932  // Parameter indices are 1-indexed, hence Index=1
933  if (!checkPositiveIntArgument(S, AL, SizeExpr, SizeArgNoVal, /*Idx=*/1))
934  return;
935  if (!checkParamIsIntegerType(S, D, AL, /*AttrArgNo=*/0))
936  return;
937  ParamIdx SizeArgNo(SizeArgNoVal, D);
938 
939  ParamIdx NumberArgNo;
940  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 2) {
941  const Expr *NumberExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
942  int Val;
943  // Parameter indices are 1-based, hence Index=2
944  if (!checkPositiveIntArgument(S, AL, NumberExpr, Val, /*Idx=*/2))
945  return;
946  if (!checkParamIsIntegerType(S, D, AL, /*AttrArgNo=*/1))
947  return;
948  NumberArgNo = ParamIdx(Val, D);
949  }
950 
951  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
952  AllocSizeAttr(S.Context, AL, SizeArgNo, NumberArgNo));
953 }
954 
955 static bool checkTryLockFunAttrCommon(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
956  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Args) {
957  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
958  return false;
959 
960  if (!isIntOrBool(AL.getArgAsExpr(0))) {
961  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
962  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIntOrBool;
963  return false;
964  }
965 
966  // check that all arguments are lockable objects
967  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args, 1);
968 
969  return true;
970 }
971 
972 static void handleSharedTrylockFunctionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
973  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
974  SmallVector<Expr*, 2> Args;
975  if (!checkTryLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
976  return;
977 
978  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SharedTrylockFunctionAttr(
979  S.Context, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Args.data(), Args.size()));
980 }
981 
982 static void handleExclusiveTrylockFunctionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
983  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
984  SmallVector<Expr*, 2> Args;
985  if (!checkTryLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
986  return;
987 
988  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ExclusiveTrylockFunctionAttr(
989  S.Context, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Args.data(), Args.size()));
990 }
991 
992 static void handleLockReturnedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
993  // check that the argument is lockable object
994  SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
995  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
996  unsigned Size = Args.size();
997  if (Size == 0)
998  return;
999 
1000  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) LockReturnedAttr(S.Context, AL, Args[0]));
1001 }
1002 
1003 static void handleLocksExcludedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1004  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
1005  return;
1006 
1007  // check that all arguments are lockable objects
1008  SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
1009  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
1010  unsigned Size = Args.size();
1011  if (Size == 0)
1012  return;
1013  Expr **StartArg = &Args[0];
1014 
1015  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
1016  LocksExcludedAttr(S.Context, AL, StartArg, Size));
1017 }
1018 
1019 static bool checkFunctionConditionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
1020  Expr *&Cond, StringRef &Msg) {
1021  Cond = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
1022  if (!Cond->isTypeDependent()) {
1023  ExprResult Converted = S.PerformContextuallyConvertToBool(Cond);
1024  if (Converted.isInvalid())
1025  return false;
1026  Cond = Converted.get();
1027  }
1028 
1029  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 1, Msg))
1030  return false;
1031 
1032  if (Msg.empty())
1033  Msg = "<no message provided>";
1034 
1035  SmallVector<PartialDiagnosticAt, 8> Diags;
1036  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D) && !Cond->isValueDependent() &&
1037  !Expr::isPotentialConstantExprUnevaluated(Cond, cast<FunctionDecl>(D),
1038  Diags)) {
1039  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attr_cond_never_constant_expr) << AL;
1040  for (const PartialDiagnosticAt &PDiag : Diags)
1041  S.Diag(PDiag.first, PDiag.second);
1042  return false;
1043  }
1044  return true;
1045 }
1046 
1047 static void handleEnableIfAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1048  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_clang_enable_if);
1049 
1050  Expr *Cond;
1051  StringRef Msg;
1052  if (checkFunctionConditionAttr(S, D, AL, Cond, Msg))
1053  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) EnableIfAttr(S.Context, AL, Cond, Msg));
1054 }
1055 
1056 static void handleErrorAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1057  StringRef NewUserDiagnostic;
1058  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, NewUserDiagnostic))
1059  return;
1060  if (ErrorAttr *EA = S.mergeErrorAttr(D, AL, NewUserDiagnostic))
1061  D->addAttr(EA);
1062 }
1063 
1064 static void handleExcludeFromExplicitInstantiationAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
1065  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1066  const auto *PD = isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D)
1067  ? cast<DeclContext>(D)
1068  : D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
1069  if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(PD); RD && RD->isLocalClass()) {
1070  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
1071  diag::warn_attribute_exclude_from_explicit_instantiation_local_class)
1072  << AL << /*IsMember=*/!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
1073  return;
1074  }
1075  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
1076  ExcludeFromExplicitInstantiationAttr(S.Context, AL));
1077 }
1078 
1079 namespace {
1080 /// Determines if a given Expr references any of the given function's
1081 /// ParmVarDecls, or the function's implicit `this` parameter (if applicable).
1082 class ArgumentDependenceChecker
1083  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<ArgumentDependenceChecker> {
1084 #ifndef NDEBUG
1085  const CXXRecordDecl *ClassType;
1086 #endif
1087  llvm::SmallPtrSet<const ParmVarDecl *, 16> Parms;
1088  bool Result;
1089 
1090 public:
1091  ArgumentDependenceChecker(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
1092 #ifndef NDEBUG
1093  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
1094  ClassType = MD->getParent();
1095  else
1096  ClassType = nullptr;
1097 #endif
1098  Parms.insert(FD->param_begin(), FD->param_end());
1099  }
1100 
1101  bool referencesArgs(Expr *E) {
1102  Result = false;
1103  TraverseStmt(E);
1104  return Result;
1105  }
1106 
1107  bool VisitCXXThisExpr(CXXThisExpr *E) {
1108  assert(E->getType()->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl() == ClassType &&
1109  "`this` doesn't refer to the enclosing class?");
1110  Result = true;
1111  return false;
1112  }
1113 
1114  bool VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *DRE) {
1115  if (const auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
1116  if (Parms.count(PVD)) {
1117  Result = true;
1118  return false;
1119  }
1120  return true;
1121  }
1122 };
1123 }
1124 
1125 static void handleDiagnoseAsBuiltinAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
1126  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1127  const auto *DeclFD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
1128 
1129  if (const auto *MethodDecl = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(DeclFD))
1130  if (!MethodDecl->isStatic()) {
1131  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_no_member_function) << AL;
1132  return;
1133  }
1134 
1135  auto DiagnoseType = [&](unsigned Index, AttributeArgumentNType T) {
1136  SourceLocation Loc = [&]() {
1137  auto Union = AL.getArg(Index - 1);
1138  if (Union.is<Expr *>())
1139  return Union.get<Expr *>()->getBeginLoc();
1140  return Union.get<IdentifierLoc *>()->Loc;
1141  }();
1142 
1143  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type) << AL << Index << T;
1144  };
1145 
1146  FunctionDecl *AttrFD = [&]() -> FunctionDecl * {
1147  if (!AL.isArgExpr(0))
1148  return nullptr;
1149  auto *F = dyn_cast_if_present<DeclRefExpr>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
1150  if (!F)
1151  return nullptr;
1152  return dyn_cast_if_present<FunctionDecl>(F->getFoundDecl());
1153  }();
1154 
1155  if (!AttrFD || !AttrFD->getBuiltinID(true)) {
1156  DiagnoseType(1, AANT_ArgumentBuiltinFunction);
1157  return;
1158  }
1159 
1160  if (AttrFD->getNumParams() != AL.getNumArgs() - 1) {
1161  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments_for)
1162  << AL << AttrFD << AttrFD->getNumParams();
1163  return;
1164  }
1165 
1166  SmallVector<unsigned, 8> Indices;
1167 
1168  for (unsigned I = 1; I < AL.getNumArgs(); ++I) {
1169  if (!AL.isArgExpr(I)) {
1170  DiagnoseType(I + 1, AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant);
1171  return;
1172  }
1173 
1174  const Expr *IndexExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(I);
1175  uint32_t Index;
1176 
1177  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IndexExpr, Index, I + 1, false))
1178  return;
1179 
1180  if (Index > DeclFD->getNumParams()) {
1181  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_bounds_for_function)
1182  << AL << Index << DeclFD << DeclFD->getNumParams();
1183  return;
1184  }
1185 
1186  QualType T1 = AttrFD->getParamDecl(I - 1)->getType();
1187  QualType T2 = DeclFD->getParamDecl(Index - 1)->getType();
1188 
1189  if (T1.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType() !=
1190  T2.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType()) {
1191  S.Diag(IndexExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_parameter_types)
1192  << AL << Index << DeclFD << T2 << I << AttrFD << T1;
1193  return;
1194  }
1195 
1196  Indices.push_back(Index - 1);
1197  }
1198 
1199  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) DiagnoseAsBuiltinAttr(
1200  S.Context, AL, AttrFD, Indices.data(), Indices.size()));
1201 }
1202 
1203 static void handleDiagnoseIfAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1204  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_clang_diagnose_if);
1205 
1206  Expr *Cond;
1207  StringRef Msg;
1208  if (!checkFunctionConditionAttr(S, D, AL, Cond, Msg))
1209  return;
1210 
1211  StringRef DiagTypeStr;
1212  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 2, DiagTypeStr))
1213  return;
1214 
1215  DiagnoseIfAttr::DiagnosticType DiagType;
1216  if (!DiagnoseIfAttr::ConvertStrToDiagnosticType(DiagTypeStr, DiagType)) {
1217  S.Diag(AL.getArgAsExpr(2)->getBeginLoc(),
1218  diag::err_diagnose_if_invalid_diagnostic_type);
1219  return;
1220  }
1221 
1222  bool ArgDependent = false;
1223  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
1224  ArgDependent = ArgumentDependenceChecker(FD).referencesArgs(Cond);
1225  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) DiagnoseIfAttr(
1226  S.Context, AL, Cond, Msg, DiagType, ArgDependent, cast<NamedDecl>(D)));
1227 }
1228 
1229 static void handleNoBuiltinAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1230  static constexpr const StringRef kWildcard = "*";
1231 
1232  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 16> Names;
1233  bool HasWildcard = false;
1234 
1235  const auto AddBuiltinName = [&Names, &HasWildcard](StringRef Name) {
1236  if (Name == kWildcard)
1237  HasWildcard = true;
1238  Names.push_back(Name);
1239  };
1240 
1241  // Add previously defined attributes.
1242  if (const auto *NBA = D->getAttr<NoBuiltinAttr>())
1243  for (StringRef BuiltinName : NBA->builtinNames())
1244  AddBuiltinName(BuiltinName);
1245 
1246  // Add current attributes.
1247  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
1248  AddBuiltinName(kWildcard);
1249  else
1250  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
1251  StringRef BuiltinName;
1252  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
1253  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, BuiltinName, &LiteralLoc))
1254  return;
1255 
1256  if (Builtin::Context::isBuiltinFunc(BuiltinName))
1257  AddBuiltinName(BuiltinName);
1258  else
1259  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_attribute_no_builtin_invalid_builtin_name)
1260  << BuiltinName << AL;
1261  }
1262 
1263  // Repeating the same attribute is fine.
1264  llvm::sort(Names);
1265  Names.erase(std::unique(Names.begin(), Names.end()), Names.end());
1266 
1267  // Empty no_builtin must be on its own.
1268  if (HasWildcard && Names.size() > 1)
1269  S.Diag(D->getLocation(),
1270  diag::err_attribute_no_builtin_wildcard_or_builtin_name)
1271  << AL;
1272 
1273  if (D->hasAttr<NoBuiltinAttr>())
1274  D->dropAttr<NoBuiltinAttr>();
1275  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
1276  NoBuiltinAttr(S.Context, AL, Names.data(), Names.size()));
1277 }
1278 
1279 static void handlePassObjectSizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1280  if (D->hasAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
1281  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_only_once_per_parameter) << AL;
1282  return;
1283  }
1284 
1285  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
1286  uint32_t Type;
1287  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, Type, /*Idx=*/1))
1288  return;
1289 
1290  // pass_object_size's argument is passed in as the second argument of
1291  // __builtin_object_size. So, it has the same constraints as that second
1292  // argument; namely, it must be in the range [0, 3].
1293  if (Type > 3) {
1294  S.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_range)
1295  << AL << 0 << 3 << E->getSourceRange();
1296  return;
1297  }
1298 
1299  // pass_object_size is only supported on constant pointer parameters; as a
1300  // kindness to users, we allow the parameter to be non-const for declarations.
1301  // At this point, we have no clue if `D` belongs to a function declaration or
1302  // definition, so we defer the constness check until later.
1303  if (!cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType()->isPointerType()) {
1304  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_pointers_only) << AL << 1;
1305  return;
1306  }
1307 
1308  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PassObjectSizeAttr(S.Context, AL, (int)Type));
1309 }

1311 static void handleConsumableAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1312  ConsumableAttr::ConsumedState DefaultState;
1313 
1314  if (AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
1315  IdentifierLoc *IL = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
1316  if (!ConsumableAttr::ConvertStrToConsumedState(IL->Ident->getName(),
1317  DefaultState)) {
1318  S.Diag(IL->Loc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL
1319  << IL->Ident;
1320  return;
1321  }
1322  } else {
1323  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
1324  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
1325  return;
1326  }
1327 
1328  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ConsumableAttr(S.Context, AL, DefaultState));
1329 }

1331 static bool checkForConsumableClass(Sema &S, const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
1332  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1333  QualType ThisType = MD->getFunctionObjectParameterType();
1334 
1335  if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = ThisType->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
1336  if (!RD->hasAttr<ConsumableAttr>()) {
1337  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attr_on_unconsumable_class) << RD;
1338 
1339  return false;
1340  }
1341  }
1342 
1343  return true;
1344 }

1346 static void handleCallableWhenAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1347  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
1348  return;
1349 
1350  if (!checkForConsumableClass(S, cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D), AL))
1351  return;
1352 
1353  SmallVector<CallableWhenAttr::ConsumedState, 3> States;
1354  for (unsigned ArgIndex = 0; ArgIndex < AL.getNumArgs(); ++ArgIndex) {
1355  CallableWhenAttr::ConsumedState CallableState;
1356 
1357  StringRef StateString;
1358  SourceLocation Loc;
1359  if (AL.isArgIdent(ArgIndex)) {
1360  IdentifierLoc *Ident = AL.getArgAsIdent(ArgIndex);
1361  StateString = Ident->Ident->getName();
1362  Loc = Ident->Loc;
1363  } else {
1364  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, ArgIndex, StateString, &Loc))
1365  return;
1366  }
1367 
1368  if (!CallableWhenAttr::ConvertStrToConsumedState(StateString,
1369  CallableState)) {
1370  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << StateString;
1371  return;
1372  }
1373 
1374  States.push_back(CallableState);
1375  }
1376 
1377  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
1378  CallableWhenAttr(S.Context, AL, States.data(), States.size()));
1379 }

1475  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
1476  return;

1509 static void handlePackedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1510  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D))
1511  TD->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PackedAttr(S.Context, AL));
1512  else if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
1513  bool BitfieldByteAligned = (!FD->getType()->isDependentType() &&
1514  !FD->getType()->isIncompleteType() &&
1515  FD->isBitField() &&
1516  S.Context.getTypeAlign(FD->getType()) <= 8);
1517 
1518  if (S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isPS()) {
1519  if (BitfieldByteAligned)
1520  // The PS4/PS5 targets need to maintain ABI backwards compatibility.
1521  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored_for_field_of_type)
1522  << AL << FD->getType();
1523  else
1524  FD->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PackedAttr(S.Context, AL));
1525  } else {
1526  // Report warning about changed offset in the newer compiler versions.
1527  if (BitfieldByteAligned)
1528  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_packed_for_bitfield);
1529 
1530  FD->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PackedAttr(S.Context, AL));
1531  }
1532 
1533  } else
1534  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << AL;
1535 }
1536 
1537 static void handlePreferredName(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1538  auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
1539  ClassTemplateDecl *CTD = RD->getDescribedClassTemplate();
1540  assert(CTD && "attribute does not appertain to this declaration");
1541 
1542  ParsedType PT = AL.getTypeArg();
1543  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = nullptr;
1544  QualType T = S.GetTypeFromParser(PT, &TSI);
1545  if (!TSI)
1546  TSI = S.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, AL.getLoc());
1547 
1548  if (!T.hasQualifiers() && T->isTypedefNameType()) {
1549  // Find the template name, if this type names a template specialization.
1550  const TemplateDecl *Template = nullptr;
1551  if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast_if_present<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(
1552  T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())) {
1553  Template = CTSD->getSpecializedTemplate();
1554  } else if (const auto *TST = T->getAs<TemplateSpecializationType>()) {
1555  while (TST && TST->isTypeAlias())
1556  TST = TST->getAliasedType()->getAs<TemplateSpecializationType>();
1557  if (TST)
1558  Template = TST->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl();
1559  }
1560 
1561  if (Template && declaresSameEntity(Template, CTD)) {
1562  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreferredNameAttr(S.Context, AL, TSI));
1563  return;
1564  }
1565  }
1566 
1567  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_preferred_name_arg_invalid)
1568  << T << CTD;
1569  if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
1570  S.Diag(TT->getDecl()->getLocation(), diag::note_entity_declared_at)
1571  << TT->getDecl();
1572 }
1573 
1574 static bool checkIBOutletCommon(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1575  // The IBOutlet/IBOutletCollection attributes only apply to instance
1576  // variables or properties of Objective-C classes. The outlet must also
1577  // have an object reference type.
1578  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarDecl>(D)) {
1579  if (!VD->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
1580  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_iboutlet_object_type)
1581  << AL << VD->getType() << 0;
1582  return false;
1583  }
1584  }
1585  else if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)) {
1586  if (!PD->getType()->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
1587  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_iboutlet_object_type)
1588  << AL << PD->getType() << 1;
1589  return false;
1590  }
1591  }
1592  else {
1593  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_iboutlet) << AL;
1594  return false;
1595  }
1596 
1597  return true;
1598 }
1599 
1600 static void handleIBOutlet(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1601  if (!checkIBOutletCommon(S, D, AL))
1602  return;
1603 
1604  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) IBOutletAttr(S.Context, AL));
1605 }
1606 
1607 static void handleIBOutletCollection(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1608 
1609  // The iboutletcollection attribute can have zero or one arguments.
1610  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
1611  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
1612  return;
1613  }
1614 
1615  if (!checkIBOutletCommon(S, D, AL))
1616  return;
1617 
1618  ParsedType PT;
1619 
1620  if (AL.hasParsedType())
1621  PT = AL.getTypeArg();
1622  else {
1623  PT = S.getTypeName(S.Context.Idents.get("NSObject"), AL.getLoc(),
1624  S.getScopeForContext(D->getDeclContext()->getParent()));
1625  if (!PT) {
1626  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_iboutletcollection_type) << "NSObject";
1627  return;
1628  }
1629  }
1630 
1631  TypeSourceInfo *QTLoc = nullptr;
1632  QualType QT = S.GetTypeFromParser(PT, &QTLoc);
1633  if (!QTLoc)
1634  QTLoc = S.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(QT, AL.getLoc());
1635 
1636  // Diagnose use of non-object type in iboutletcollection attribute.
1637  // FIXME. Gnu attribute extension ignores use of builtin types in
1638  // attributes. So, __attribute__((iboutletcollection(char))) will be
1639  // treated as __attribute__((iboutletcollection())).
1640  if (!QT->isObjCIdType() && !QT->isObjCObjectType()) {
1641  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
1642  QT->isBuiltinType() ? diag::err_iboutletcollection_builtintype
1643  : diag::err_iboutletcollection_type) << QT;
1644  return;
1645  }
1646 
1647  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) IBOutletCollectionAttr(S.Context, AL, QTLoc));
1648 }
1649 
1650 bool Sema::isValidPointerAttrType(QualType T, bool RefOkay) {
1651  if (RefOkay) {
1652  if (T->isReferenceType())
1653  return true;
1654  } else {
1655  T = T.getNonReferenceType();
1656  }
1657 
1658  // The nonnull attribute, and other similar attributes, can be applied to a
1659  // transparent union that contains a pointer type.
1660  if (const RecordType *UT = T->getAsUnionType()) {
1661  if (UT && UT->getDecl()->hasAttr<TransparentUnionAttr>()) {
1662  RecordDecl *UD = UT->getDecl();
1663  for (const auto *I : UD->fields()) {
1664  QualType QT = I->getType();
1665  if (QT->isAnyPointerType() || QT->isBlockPointerType())
1666  return true;
1667  }
1668  }
1669  }
1670 
1671  return T->isAnyPointerType() || T->isBlockPointerType();
1672 }
1673 
1674 static bool attrNonNullArgCheck(Sema &S, QualType T, const ParsedAttr &AL,
1675  SourceRange AttrParmRange,
1676  SourceRange TypeRange,
1677  bool isReturnValue = false) {
1678  if (!S.isValidPointerAttrType(T)) {
1679  if (isReturnValue)
1680  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_return_pointers_only)
1681  << AL << AttrParmRange << TypeRange;
1682  else
1683  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_pointers_only)
1684  << AL << AttrParmRange << TypeRange << 0;
1685  return false;
1686  }
1687  return true;
1688 }
1689 
1690 static void handleNonNullAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1691  SmallVector<ParamIdx, 8> NonNullArgs;
1692  for (unsigned I = 0; I < AL.getNumArgs(); ++I) {
1693  Expr *Ex = AL.getArgAsExpr(I);
1694  ParamIdx Idx;
1695  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, I + 1, Ex, Idx))
1696  return;
1697 
1698  // Is the function argument a pointer type?
1699  if (Idx.getASTIndex() < getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) &&
1700  !attrNonNullArgCheck(
1701  S, getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex()), AL,
1702  Ex->getSourceRange(),
1703  getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, Idx.getASTIndex())))
1704  continue;
1705 
1706  NonNullArgs.push_back(Idx);
1707  }
1708 
1709  // If no arguments were specified to __attribute__((nonnull)) then all pointer
1710  // arguments have a nonnull attribute; warn if there aren't any. Skip this
1711  // check if the attribute came from a macro expansion or a template
1712  // instantiation.
1713  if (NonNullArgs.empty() && AL.getLoc().isFileID() &&
1714  !S.inTemplateInstantiation()) {
1715  bool AnyPointers = isFunctionOrMethodVariadic(D);
1716  for (unsigned I = 0, E = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D);
1717  I != E && !AnyPointers; ++I) {
1718  QualType T = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, I);
1719  if (T->isDependentType() || S.isValidPointerAttrType(T))
1720  AnyPointers = true;
1721  }
1722 
1723  if (!AnyPointers)
1724  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_nonnull_no_pointers);
1725  }
1726 
1727  ParamIdx *Start = NonNullArgs.data();
1728  unsigned Size = NonNullArgs.size();
1729  llvm::array_pod_sort(Start, Start + Size);
1730  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NonNullAttr(S.Context, AL, Start, Size));
1731 }
1732 
1733 static void handleNonNullAttrParameter(Sema &S, ParmVarDecl *D,
1734  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1735  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 0) {
1736  if (D->getFunctionType()) {
1737  handleNonNullAttr(S, D, AL);
1738  } else {
1739  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_nonnull_parm_no_args)
1740  << D->getSourceRange();
1741  }
1742  return;
1743  }
1744 
1745  // Is the argument a pointer type?
1746  if (!attrNonNullArgCheck(S, D->getType(), AL, SourceRange(),
1747  D->getSourceRange()))
1748  return;
1749 
1750  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NonNullAttr(S.Context, AL, nullptr, 0));
1751 }
1752 
1753 static void handleReturnsNonNullAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1754  QualType ResultType = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
1755  SourceRange SR = getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(D);
1756  if (!attrNonNullArgCheck(S, ResultType, AL, SourceRange(), SR,
1757  /* isReturnValue */ true))
1758  return;
1759 
1760  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ReturnsNonNullAttr(S.Context, AL));
1761 }
1762 
1763 static void handleNoEscapeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1764  if (D->isInvalidDecl())
1765  return;
1766 
1767  // noescape only applies to pointer types.
1768  QualType T = cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType();
1769  if (!S.isValidPointerAttrType(T, /* RefOkay */ true)) {
1770  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_pointers_only)
1771  << AL << AL.getRange() << 0;
1772  return;
1773  }
1774 
1775  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoEscapeAttr(S.Context, AL));
1776 }
1777 
1778 static void handleAssumeAlignedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1779  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
1780  *OE = AL.getNumArgs() > 1 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr;
1781  S.AddAssumeAlignedAttr(D, AL, E, OE);
1782 }
1783 
1784 static void handleAllocAlignAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1785  S.AddAllocAlignAttr(D, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
1786 }
1787 
1788 void Sema::AddAssumeAlignedAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI, Expr *E,
1789  Expr *OE) {
1790  QualType ResultType = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
1791  SourceRange SR = getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(D);
1792 
1793  AssumeAlignedAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, E, OE);
1794  SourceLocation AttrLoc = TmpAttr.getLocation();
1795 
1796  if (!isValidPointerAttrType(ResultType, /* RefOkay */ true)) {
1797  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_return_pointers_refs_only)
1798  << &TmpAttr << TmpAttr.getRange() << SR;
1799  return;
1800  }
1801 
1802  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
1803  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> I = llvm::APSInt(64);
1804  if (!(I = E->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context))) {
1805  if (OE)
1806  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
1807  << &TmpAttr << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
1808  << E->getSourceRange();
1809  else
1810  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
1811  << &TmpAttr << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
1812  << E->getSourceRange();
1813  return;
1814  }
1815 
1816  if (!I->isPowerOf2()) {
1817  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
1818  << E->getSourceRange();
1819  return;
1820  }
1821 
1822  if (*I > Sema::MaximumAlignment)
1823  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_assume_aligned_too_great)
1824  << CI.getRange() << Sema::MaximumAlignment;
1825  }
1826 
1827  if (OE && !OE->isValueDependent() && !OE->isIntegerConstantExpr(Context)) {
1828  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
1829  << &TmpAttr << 2 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
1830  << OE->getSourceRange();
1831  return;
1832  }
1833 
1834  D->addAttr(::new (Context) AssumeAlignedAttr(Context, CI, E, OE));
1835 }
1836 
1837 void Sema::AddAllocAlignAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
1838  Expr *ParamExpr) {
1839  QualType ResultType = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
1840 
1841  AllocAlignAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, ParamIdx());
1842  SourceLocation AttrLoc = CI.getLoc();
1843 
1844  if (!ResultType->isDependentType() &&
1845  !isValidPointerAttrType(ResultType, /* RefOkay */ true)) {
1846  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_return_pointers_refs_only)
1847  << &TmpAttr << CI.getRange() << getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(D);
1848  return;
1849  }
1850 
1851  ParamIdx Idx;
1852  const auto *FuncDecl = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
1853  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(*this, FuncDecl, TmpAttr,
1854  /*AttrArgNum=*/1, ParamExpr, Idx))
1855  return;
1856 
1857  QualType Ty = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
1858  if (!Ty->isDependentType() && !Ty->isIntegralType(Context) &&
1859  !Ty->isAlignValT()) {
1860  Diag(ParamExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_integers_only)
1861  << &TmpAttr
1862  << FuncDecl->getParamDecl(Idx.getASTIndex())->getSourceRange();
1863  return;
1864  }
1865 
1866  D->addAttr(::new (Context) AllocAlignAttr(Context, CI, Idx));
1867 }
1868 
1869 /// Check if \p AssumptionStr is a known assumption and warn if not.
1870 static void checkOMPAssumeAttr(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
1871  StringRef AssumptionStr) {
1872  if (llvm::KnownAssumptionStrings.count(AssumptionStr))
1873  return;
1874 
1875  unsigned BestEditDistance = 3;
1876  StringRef Suggestion;
1877  for (const auto &KnownAssumptionIt : llvm::KnownAssumptionStrings) {
1878  unsigned EditDistance =
1879  AssumptionStr.edit_distance(KnownAssumptionIt.getKey());
1880  if (EditDistance < BestEditDistance) {
1881  Suggestion = KnownAssumptionIt.getKey();
1882  BestEditDistance = EditDistance;
1883  }
1884  }
1885 
1886  if (!Suggestion.empty())
1887  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_omp_assume_attribute_string_unknown_suggested)
1888  << AssumptionStr << Suggestion;
1889  else
1890  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_omp_assume_attribute_string_unknown)
1891  << AssumptionStr;
1892 }
1893 
1894 static void handleOMPAssumeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1895  // Handle the case where the attribute has a text message.
1896  StringRef Str;
1897  SourceLocation AttrStrLoc;
1898  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &AttrStrLoc))
1899  return;
1900 
1901  checkOMPAssumeAttr(S, AttrStrLoc, Str);
1902 
1903  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) OMPAssumeAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
1904 }
1905 
1906 /// Normalize the attribute, __foo__ becomes foo.
1907 /// Returns true if normalization was applied.
1908 static bool normalizeName(StringRef &AttrName) {
1909  if (AttrName.size() > 4 && AttrName.starts_with("__") &&
1910  AttrName.ends_with("__")) {
1911  AttrName = AttrName.drop_front(2).drop_back(2);
1912  return true;
1913  }
1914  return false;
1915 }
1916 
1917 static void handleOwnershipAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
1918  // This attribute must be applied to a function declaration. The first
1919  // argument to the attribute must be an identifier, the name of the resource,
1920  // for example: malloc. The following arguments must be argument indexes, the
1921  // arguments must be of integer type for Returns, otherwise of pointer type.
1922  // The difference between Holds and Takes is that a pointer may still be used
1923  // after being held. free() should be __attribute((ownership_takes)), whereas
1924  // a list append function may well be __attribute((ownership_holds)).
1925 
1926  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
1927  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
1928  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
1929  return;
1930  }
1931 
1932  // Figure out our Kind.
1933  OwnershipAttr::OwnershipKind K =
1934  OwnershipAttr(S.Context, AL, nullptr, nullptr, 0).getOwnKind();
1935 
1936  // Check arguments.
1937  switch (K) {
1938  case OwnershipAttr::Takes:
1939  case OwnershipAttr::Holds:
1940  if (AL.getNumArgs() < 2) {
1941  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_few_arguments) << AL << 2;
1942  return;
1943  }
1944  break;
1945  case OwnershipAttr::Returns:
1946  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 2) {
1947  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_many_arguments) << AL << 1;
1948  return;
1949  }
1950  break;
1951  }
1952 
1953  IdentifierInfo *Module = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
1954 
1955  StringRef ModuleName = Module->getName();
1956  if (normalizeName(ModuleName)) {
1957  Module = &S.PP.getIdentifierTable().get(ModuleName);
1958  }
1959 
1960  SmallVector<ParamIdx, 8> OwnershipArgs;
1961  for (unsigned i = 1; i < AL.getNumArgs(); ++i) {
1962  Expr *Ex = AL.getArgAsExpr(i);
1963  ParamIdx Idx;
1964  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, i, Ex, Idx))
1965  return;
1966 
1967  // Is the function argument a pointer type?
1968  QualType T = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
1969  int Err = -1; // No error
1970  switch (K) {
1971  case OwnershipAttr::Takes:
1972  case OwnershipAttr::Holds:
1973  if (!T->isAnyPointerType() && !T->isBlockPointerType())
1974  Err = 0;
1975  break;
1976  case OwnershipAttr::Returns:
1977  if (!T->isIntegerType())
1978  Err = 1;
1979  break;
1980  }
1981  if (-1 != Err) {
1982  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_ownership_type) << AL << Err
1983  << Ex->getSourceRange();
1984  return;
1985  }
1986 
1987  // Check we don't have a conflict with another ownership attribute.
1988  for (const auto *I : D->specific_attrs<OwnershipAttr>()) {
1989  // Cannot have two ownership attributes of different kinds for the same
1990  // index.
1991  if (I->getOwnKind() != K && llvm::is_contained(I->args(), Idx)) {
1992  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
1993  << AL << I
1994  << (AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() ||
1995  I->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
1996  return;
1997  } else if (K == OwnershipAttr::Returns &&
1998  I->getOwnKind() == OwnershipAttr::Returns) {
1999  // A returns attribute conflicts with any other returns attribute using
2000  // a different index.
2001  if (!llvm::is_contained(I->args(), Idx)) {
2002  S.Diag(I->getLocation(), diag::err_ownership_returns_index_mismatch)
2003  << I->args_begin()->getSourceIndex();
2004  if (I->args_size())
2005  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::note_ownership_returns_index_mismatch)
2006  << Idx.getSourceIndex() << Ex->getSourceRange();
2007  return;
2008  }
2009  }
2010  }
2011  OwnershipArgs.push_back(Idx);
2012  }
2013 
2014  ParamIdx *Start = OwnershipArgs.data();
2015  unsigned Size = OwnershipArgs.size();
2016  llvm::array_pod_sort(Start, Start + Size);
2017  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2018  OwnershipAttr(S.Context, AL, Module, Start, Size));
2019 }
2020 
2021 static void handleWeakRefAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2022  // Check the attribute arguments.
2023  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
2024  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
2025  return;
2026  }
2027 
2028  // gcc rejects
2029  // class c {
2030  // static int a __attribute__((weakref ("v2")));
2031  // static int b() __attribute__((weakref ("f3")));
2032  // };
2033  // and ignores the attributes of
2034  // void f(void) {
2035  // static int a __attribute__((weakref ("v2")));
2036  // }
2037  // we reject them
2038  const DeclContext *Ctx = D->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext();
2039  if (!Ctx->isFileContext()) {
2040  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_weakref_not_global_context)
2041  << cast<NamedDecl>(D);
2042  return;
2043  }
2044 
2045  // The GCC manual says
2046  //
2047  // At present, a declaration to which `weakref' is attached can only
2048  // be `static'.
2049  //
2050  // It also says
2051  //
2052  // Without a TARGET,
2053  // given as an argument to `weakref' or to `alias', `weakref' is
2054  // equivalent to `weak'.
2055  //
2056  // gcc 4.4.1 will accept
2057  // int a7 __attribute__((weakref));
2058  // as
2059  // int a7 __attribute__((weak));
2060  // This looks like a bug in gcc. We reject that for now. We should revisit
2061  // it if this behaviour is actually used.
2062 
2063  // GCC rejects
2064  // static ((alias ("y"), weakref)).
2065  // Should we? How to check that weakref is before or after alias?
2066 
2067  // FIXME: it would be good for us to keep the WeakRefAttr as-written instead
2068  // of transforming it into an AliasAttr. The WeakRefAttr never uses the
2069  // StringRef parameter it was given anyway.
2070  StringRef Str;
2071  if (AL.getNumArgs() && S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
2072  // GCC will accept anything as the argument of weakref. Should we
2073  // check for an existing decl?
2074  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AliasAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
2075 
2076  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) WeakRefAttr(S.Context, AL));
2077 }
2078 
2079 // Mark alias/ifunc target as used. Due to name mangling, we look up the
2080 // demangled name ignoring parameters (not supported by microsoftDemangle
2081 // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/88825). This should handle the
2082 // majority of use cases while leaving namespace scope names unmarked.
2083 static void markUsedForAliasOrIfunc(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
2084  StringRef Str) {
2085  std::unique_ptr<char, llvm::FreeDeleter> Demangled;
2086  if (S.getASTContext().getCXXABIKind() != TargetCXXABI::Microsoft)
2087  Demangled.reset(llvm::itaniumDemangle(Str, /*ParseParams=*/false));
2088  std::unique_ptr<MangleContext> MC(S.Context.createMangleContext());
2089  SmallString<256> Name;
2090 
2091  const DeclarationNameInfo Target(
2092  &S.Context.Idents.get(Demangled ? Demangled.get() : Str), AL.getLoc());
2093  LookupResult LR(S, Target, Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
2094  if (S.LookupName(LR, S.TUScope)) {
2095  for (NamedDecl *ND : LR) {
2096  if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(ND) && !isa<VarDecl>(ND))
2097  continue;
2098  if (MC->shouldMangleDeclName(ND)) {
2099  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
2100  Name.clear();
2101  MC->mangleName(GlobalDecl(ND), Out);
2102  } else {
2103  Name = ND->getIdentifier()->getName();
2104  }
2105  if (Name == Str)
2106  ND->markUsed(S.Context);
2107  }
2108  }
2109 }
2110 
2111 static void handleIFuncAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2112  StringRef Str;
2113  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
2114  return;
2115 
2116  // Aliases should be on declarations, not definitions.
2117  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
2118  if (FD->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
2119  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_alias_is_definition) << FD << 1;
2120  return;
2121  }
2122 
2123  markUsedForAliasOrIfunc(S, D, AL, Str);
2124  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) IFuncAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
2125 }
2126 
2127 static void handleAliasAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2128  StringRef Str;
2129  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
2130  return;
2131 
2132  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin()) {
2133  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_alias_not_supported_on_darwin);
2134  return;
2135  }
2136 
2137  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
2138  CudaVersion Version =
2139  ToCudaVersion(S.Context.getTargetInfo().getSDKVersion());
2140  if (Version != CudaVersion::UNKNOWN && Version < CudaVersion::CUDA_100)
2141  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_alias_not_supported_on_nvptx);
2142  }
2143 
2144  // Aliases should be on declarations, not definitions.
2145  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2146  if (FD->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
2147  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_alias_is_definition) << FD << 0;
2148  return;
2149  }
2150  } else {
2151  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
2152  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && VD->isExternallyVisible()) {
2153  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_alias_is_definition) << VD << 0;
2154  return;
2155  }
2156  }
2157 
2158  markUsedForAliasOrIfunc(S, D, AL, Str);
2159  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AliasAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
2160 }
2161 
2162 static void handleTLSModelAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2163  StringRef Model;
2164  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
2165  // Check that it is a string.
2166  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Model, &LiteralLoc))
2167  return;
2168 
2169  // Check that the value.
2170  if (Model != "global-dynamic" && Model != "local-dynamic"
2171  && Model != "initial-exec" && Model != "local-exec") {
2172  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attr_tlsmodel_arg);
2173  return;
2174  }
2175 
2176  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) TLSModelAttr(S.Context, AL, Model));
2177 }

2179 static void handleRestrictAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2180  QualType ResultType = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
2181  if (ResultType->isAnyPointerType() || ResultType->isBlockPointerType()) {
2182  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RestrictAttr(S.Context, AL));
2183  return;
2184  }
2185

2190 static void handleCPUSpecificAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2191  // Ensure we don't combine these with themselves, since that causes some
2192  // confusing behavior.
2193  if (AL.getParsedKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CPUDispatch) {
2194  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CPUSpecificAttr>(S, D, AL))
2195  return;
2196 
2197  if (const auto *Other = D->getAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>()) {
2198  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_disallowed_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
2199  S.Diag(Other->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
2200  return;
2201  }
2202  } else if (AL.getParsedKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CPUSpecific) {
2203  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<CPUDispatchAttr>(S, D, AL))
2204  return;
2205 
2206  if (const auto *Other = D->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>()) {
2207  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_disallowed_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
2208  S.Diag(Other->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
2209  return;
2210  }
2211  }
2212 
2213  FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
2214 
2215  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
2216  if (MD->getParent()->isLambda()) {
2217  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_dll_lambda) << AL;
2218  return;
2219  }
2220  }
2221 
2222  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
2223  return;
2224 
2225  SmallVector<IdentifierInfo *, 8> CPUs;
2226  for (unsigned ArgNo = 0; ArgNo < getNumAttributeArgs(AL); ++ArgNo) {
2227  if (!AL.isArgIdent(ArgNo)) {
2228  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2229  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
2230  return;
2231  }
2232 
2233  IdentifierLoc *CPUArg = AL.getArgAsIdent(ArgNo);
2234  StringRef CPUName = CPUArg->Ident->getName().trim();
2235 
2236  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().validateCPUSpecificCPUDispatch(CPUName)) {
2237  S.Diag(CPUArg->Loc, diag::err_invalid_cpu_specific_dispatch_value)
2238  << CPUName << (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CPUDispatch);
2239  return;
2240  }
2241 
2242  const TargetInfo &Target = S.Context.getTargetInfo();
2243  if (llvm::any_of(CPUs, [CPUName, &Target](const IdentifierInfo *Cur) {
2244  return Target.CPUSpecificManglingCharacter(CPUName) ==
2245  Target.CPUSpecificManglingCharacter(Cur->getName());
2246  })) {
2247  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_multiversion_duplicate_entries);
2248  return;
2249  }
2250  CPUs.push_back(CPUArg->Ident);
2251  }
2252 
2253  FD->setIsMultiVersion(true);
2254  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CPUSpecific)
2255  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2256  CPUSpecificAttr(S.Context, AL, CPUs.data(), CPUs.size()));
2257  else
2258  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
2259  CPUDispatchAttr(S.Context, AL, CPUs.data(), CPUs.size()));
2260 }

2262 static void handleCommonAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2263  if (S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus) {
2264  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_in_lang)
2265  << AL << AttributeLangSupport::Cpp;
2266  return;
2267  }
2268 
2269  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CommonAttr(S.Context, AL));
2270 }

2272 static void handleCmseNSEntryAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2273  if (S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus && !D->getDeclContext()->isExternCContext()) {
2274  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_clinkage) << AL;
2275  return;
2276  }

2278  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
2279  if (!FD->isExternallyVisible()) {
2280  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_cmse_entry_static);

2287 static void handleNakedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2288  if (AL.isDeclspecAttribute()) {
2289  const auto &Triple = S.getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple();
2290  const auto &Arch = Triple.getArch();
2291  if (Arch != llvm::Triple::x86 &&
2292  (Arch != llvm::Triple::arm && Arch != llvm::Triple::thumb)) {
2293  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_on_arch)
2294  << AL << Triple.getArchName();
2295  return;
2296  }
2297 
2298  // This form is not allowed to be written on a member function (static or
2299  // nonstatic) when in Microsoft compatibility mode.
2300  if (S.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
2301  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type_str)
2302  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << "non-member functions";
2303  return;
2304  }
2305  }
2306 
2307  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NakedAttr(S.Context, AL));
2308 }

2310 static void handleNoReturnAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
2311  if (hasDeclarator(D)) return;
2312 
2313  if (!isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
2314  S.Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2315  << Attrs << Attrs.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
2316  << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
2317  return;
2318  }
2319 
2320  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoReturnAttr(S.Context, Attrs));
2321 }
2322 
2323 static void handleStandardNoReturnAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
2324  // The [[_Noreturn]] spelling is deprecated in C23, so if that was used,
2325  // issue an appropriate diagnostic. However, don't issue a diagnostic if the
2326  // attribute name comes from a macro expansion. We don't want to punish users
2327  // who write [[noreturn]] after including <stdnoreturn.h> (where 'noreturn'
2328  // is defined as a macro which expands to '_Noreturn').
2329  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
2330  A.getSemanticSpelling() == CXX11NoReturnAttr::C23_Noreturn &&
2331  !(A.getLoc().isMacroID() &&
2332  S.getSourceManager().isInSystemMacro(A.getLoc())))
2333  S.Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::warn_deprecated_noreturn_spelling) << A.getRange();
2334 
2335  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CXX11NoReturnAttr(S.Context, A));
2336 }
2337 
2338 static void handleNoCfCheckAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
2339  if (!S.getLangOpts().CFProtectionBranch)
2340  S.Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::warn_nocf_check_attribute_ignored);
2341  else
2342  handleSimpleAttribute<AnyX86NoCfCheckAttr>(S, D, Attrs);
2343 }

2345 bool Sema::CheckAttrNoArgs(const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
2346  if (!Attrs.checkExactlyNumArgs(*this, 0)) {
2347  Attrs.setInvalid();
2348  return true;
2349  }
2350 
2351  return false;
2352 }

2354 bool Sema::CheckAttrTarget(const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2355  // Check whether the attribute is valid on the current target.
2356  const TargetInfo *Aux = Context.getAuxTargetInfo();
2357  if (!(AL.existsInTarget(Context.getTargetInfo()) ||
2358  (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
2359  Aux && AL.existsInTarget(*Aux)))) {
2360  Diag(AL.getLoc(), AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
2361  ? diag::err_keyword_not_supported_on_target
2362  : diag::warn_unknown_attribute_ignored)
2363  << AL << AL.getRange();
2364  AL.setInvalid();
2365  return true;
2366  }
2367 
2368  return false;
2369 }
