2371 static void handleAnalyzerNoReturnAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2372 
2373  // The checking path for 'noreturn' and 'analyzer_noreturn' are different
2374  // because 'analyzer_noreturn' does not impact the type.
2375  if (!isFunctionOrMethodOrBlock(D)) {
2376  ValueDecl *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D);
2377  if (!VD || (!VD->getType()->isBlockPointerType() &&
2378  !VD->getType()->isFunctionPointerType())) {
2379  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), AL.isStandardAttributeSyntax()
2380  ? diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type
2381  : diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
2382  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
2383  << ExpectedFunctionMethodOrBlock;
2384  return;
2385  }
2386  }
2387 
2388  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AnalyzerNoReturnAttr(S.Context, AL));
2389 }
2390 
2391 // PS3 PPU-specific.
2392 static void handleVecReturnAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2393  /*
2394  Returning a Vector Class in Registers
2395 
2396  According to the PPU ABI specifications, a class with a single member of
2397  vector type is returned in memory when used as the return value of a
2398  function.
2399  This results in inefficient code when implementing vector classes. To return
2400  the value in a single vector register, add the vecreturn attribute to the
2401  class definition. This attribute is also applicable to struct types.
2402 
2403  Example:
2404 
2405  struct Vector
2406  {
2407  __vector float xyzw;
2408  } __attribute__((vecreturn));
2409 
2410  Vector Add(Vector lhs, Vector rhs)
2411  {
2412  Vector result;
2413  result.xyzw = vec_add(lhs.xyzw, rhs.xyzw);
2414  return result; // This will be returned in a register
2415  }
2416  */
2417  if (VecReturnAttr *A = D->getAttr<VecReturnAttr>()) {
2418  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_repeat_attribute) << A;
2419  return;
2420  }
2421 
2422  const auto *R = cast<RecordDecl>(D);
2423  int count = 0;
2424 
2425  if (!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(R)) {
2426  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_vecreturn_only_vector_member);
2427  return;
2428  }
2429 
2430  if (!cast<CXXRecordDecl>(R)->isPOD()) {
2431  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_vecreturn_only_pod_record);
2432  return;
2433  }
2434 
2435  for (const auto *I : R->fields()) {
2436  if ((count == 1) || !I->getType()->isVectorType()) {
2437  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_vecreturn_only_vector_member);
2438  return;
2439  }
2440  count++;
2441  }
2442 
2443  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) VecReturnAttr(S.Context, AL));
2444 }
2445 
2446 static void handleDependencyAttr(Sema &S, Scope *Scope, Decl *D,
2447  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2448  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
2449  // [[carries_dependency]] can only be applied to a parameter if it is a
2450  // parameter of a function declaration or lambda.
2451  if (!(Scope->getFlags() & clang::Scope::FunctionDeclarationScope)) {
2452  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
2453  diag::err_carries_dependency_param_not_function_decl);
2454  return;
2455  }
2456  }
2457 
2458  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CarriesDependencyAttr(S.Context, AL));
2459 }

2461 static void handleUnusedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2462  bool IsCXX17Attr = AL.isCXX11Attribute() && !AL.getScopeName();
2463 
2464  // If this is spelled as the standard C++17 attribute, but not in C++17, warn
2465  // about using it as an extension.
2466  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 && IsCXX17Attr)
2467  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx17_attr) << AL;
2468 
2469  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) UnusedAttr(S.Context, AL));
2470 }

2472 static void handleConstructorAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {

2479  !checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), priority))
2480  return;

2492 }

2499  return;

2514 
2515 static bool checkAvailabilityAttr(Sema &S, SourceRange Range,
2516  IdentifierInfo *Platform,
2517  VersionTuple Introduced,
2518  VersionTuple Deprecated,
2519  VersionTuple Obsoleted) {
2520  StringRef PlatformName
2521  = AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName());
2522  if (PlatformName.empty())
2523  PlatformName = Platform->getName();
2524 
2525  // Ensure that Introduced <= Deprecated <= Obsoleted (although not all
2526  // of these steps are needed).
2527  if (!Introduced.empty() && !Deprecated.empty() &&
2528  !(Introduced <= Deprecated)) {
2529  S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2530  << 1 << PlatformName << Deprecated.getAsString()
2531  << 0 << Introduced.getAsString();
2532  return true;
2533  }
2534 
2535  if (!Introduced.empty() && !Obsoleted.empty() &&
2536  !(Introduced <= Obsoleted)) {
2537  S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2538  << 2 << PlatformName << Obsoleted.getAsString()
2539  << 0 << Introduced.getAsString();
2540  return true;
2541  }
2542 
2543  if (!Deprecated.empty() && !Obsoleted.empty() &&
2544  !(Deprecated <= Obsoleted)) {
2545  S.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::warn_availability_version_ordering)
2546  << 2 << PlatformName << Obsoleted.getAsString()
2547  << 1 << Deprecated.getAsString();
2548  return true;
2549  }
2550 
2551  return false;
2552 }
2553 
2554 /// Check whether the two versions match.
2555 ///
2556 /// If either version tuple is empty, then they are assumed to match. If
2557 /// \p BeforeIsOkay is true, then \p X can be less than or equal to \p Y.
2558 static bool versionsMatch(const VersionTuple &X, const VersionTuple &Y,
2559  bool BeforeIsOkay) {
2560  if (X.empty() || Y.empty())
2561  return true;
2562 
2563  if (X == Y)
2564  return true;
2565 
2566  if (BeforeIsOkay && X < Y)
2567  return true;
2568 
2569  return false;
2570 }
2571 
2572 AvailabilityAttr *Sema::mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2573  NamedDecl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI, IdentifierInfo *Platform,
2574  bool Implicit, VersionTuple Introduced, VersionTuple Deprecated,
2575  VersionTuple Obsoleted, bool IsUnavailable, StringRef Message,
2576  bool IsStrict, StringRef Replacement, AvailabilityMergeKind AMK,
2577  int Priority) {
2578  VersionTuple MergedIntroduced = Introduced;
2579  VersionTuple MergedDeprecated = Deprecated;
2580  VersionTuple MergedObsoleted = Obsoleted;
2581  bool FoundAny = false;
2582  bool OverrideOrImpl = false;
2583  switch (AMK) {
2584  case AMK_None:
2585  case AMK_Redeclaration:
2586  OverrideOrImpl = false;
2587  break;
2588 
2589  case AMK_Override:
2590  case AMK_ProtocolImplementation:
2591  case AMK_OptionalProtocolImplementation:
2592  OverrideOrImpl = true;
2593  break;
2594  }
2595 
2596  if (D->hasAttrs()) {
2597  AttrVec &Attrs = D->getAttrs();
2598  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Attrs.size(); i != e;) {
2599  const auto *OldAA = dyn_cast<AvailabilityAttr>(Attrs[i]);
2600  if (!OldAA) {
2601  ++i;
2602  continue;
2603  }
2604 
2605  IdentifierInfo *OldPlatform = OldAA->getPlatform();
2606  if (OldPlatform != Platform) {
2607  ++i;
2608  continue;
2609  }
2610 
2611  // If there is an existing availability attribute for this platform that
2612  // has a lower priority use the existing one and discard the new
2613  // attribute.
2614  if (OldAA->getPriority() < Priority)
2615  return nullptr;
2616 
2617  // If there is an existing attribute for this platform that has a higher
2618  // priority than the new attribute then erase the old one and continue
2619  // processing the attributes.
2620  if (OldAA->getPriority() > Priority) {
2621  Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2622  --e;
2623  continue;
2624  }
2625 
2626  FoundAny = true;
2627  VersionTuple OldIntroduced = OldAA->getIntroduced();
2628  VersionTuple OldDeprecated = OldAA->getDeprecated();
2629  VersionTuple OldObsoleted = OldAA->getObsoleted();
2630  bool OldIsUnavailable = OldAA->getUnavailable();
2631 
2632  if (!versionsMatch(OldIntroduced, Introduced, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2633  !versionsMatch(Deprecated, OldDeprecated, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2634  !versionsMatch(Obsoleted, OldObsoleted, OverrideOrImpl) ||
2635  !(OldIsUnavailable == IsUnavailable ||
2636  (OverrideOrImpl && !OldIsUnavailable && IsUnavailable))) {
2637  if (OverrideOrImpl) {
2638  int Which = -1;
2639  VersionTuple FirstVersion;
2640  VersionTuple SecondVersion;
2641  if (!versionsMatch(OldIntroduced, Introduced, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2642  Which = 0;
2643  FirstVersion = OldIntroduced;
2644  SecondVersion = Introduced;
2645  } else if (!versionsMatch(Deprecated, OldDeprecated, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2646  Which = 1;
2647  FirstVersion = Deprecated;
2648  SecondVersion = OldDeprecated;
2649  } else if (!versionsMatch(Obsoleted, OldObsoleted, OverrideOrImpl)) {
2650  Which = 2;
2651  FirstVersion = Obsoleted;
2652  SecondVersion = OldObsoleted;
2653  }
2654 
2655  if (Which == -1) {
2656  Diag(OldAA->getLocation(),
2657  diag::warn_mismatched_availability_override_unavail)
2658  << AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName())
2659  << (AMK == AMK_Override);
2660  } else if (Which != 1 && AMK == AMK_OptionalProtocolImplementation) {
2661  // Allow different 'introduced' / 'obsoleted' availability versions
2662  // on a method that implements an optional protocol requirement. It
2663  // makes less sense to allow this for 'deprecated' as the user can't
2664  // see if the method is 'deprecated' as 'respondsToSelector' will
2665  // still return true when the method is deprecated.
2666  ++i;
2667  continue;
2668  } else {
2669  Diag(OldAA->getLocation(),
2670  diag::warn_mismatched_availability_override)
2671  << Which
2672  << AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(Platform->getName())
2673  << FirstVersion.getAsString() << SecondVersion.getAsString()
2674  << (AMK == AMK_Override);
2675  }
2676  if (AMK == AMK_Override)
2677  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_overridden_method);
2678  else
2679  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_protocol_method);
2680  } else {
2681  Diag(OldAA->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_availability);
2682  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
2683  }
2684 
2685  Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2686  --e;
2687  continue;
2688  }
2689 
2690  VersionTuple MergedIntroduced2 = MergedIntroduced;
2691  VersionTuple MergedDeprecated2 = MergedDeprecated;
2692  VersionTuple MergedObsoleted2 = MergedObsoleted;
2693 
2694  if (MergedIntroduced2.empty())
2695  MergedIntroduced2 = OldIntroduced;
2696  if (MergedDeprecated2.empty())
2697  MergedDeprecated2 = OldDeprecated;
2698  if (MergedObsoleted2.empty())
2699  MergedObsoleted2 = OldObsoleted;
2700 
2701  if (checkAvailabilityAttr(*this, OldAA->getRange(), Platform,
2702  MergedIntroduced2, MergedDeprecated2,
2703  MergedObsoleted2)) {
2704  Attrs.erase(Attrs.begin() + i);
2705  --e;
2706  continue;
2707  }
2708 
2709  MergedIntroduced = MergedIntroduced2;
2710  MergedDeprecated = MergedDeprecated2;
2711  MergedObsoleted = MergedObsoleted2;
2712  ++i;
2713  }
2714  }
2715 
2716  if (FoundAny &&
2717  MergedIntroduced == Introduced &&
2718  MergedDeprecated == Deprecated &&
2719  MergedObsoleted == Obsoleted)
2720  return nullptr;
2721 
2722  // Only create a new attribute if !OverrideOrImpl, but we want to do
2723  // the checking.
2724  if (!checkAvailabilityAttr(*this, CI.getRange(), Platform, MergedIntroduced,
2725  MergedDeprecated, MergedObsoleted) &&
2726  !OverrideOrImpl) {
2727  auto *Avail = ::new (Context) AvailabilityAttr(
2728  Context, CI, Platform, Introduced, Deprecated, Obsoleted, IsUnavailable,
2729  Message, IsStrict, Replacement, Priority);
2730  Avail->setImplicit(Implicit);
2731  return Avail;
2732  }
2733  return nullptr;
2734 }
2735 
2736 static void handleAvailabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
2737  if (isa<UsingDecl, UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl, UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(
2738  D)) {
2739  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_deprecated_ignored_on_using)
2740  << AL;
2741  return;
2742  }
2743 
2744  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
2745  return;
2746  IdentifierLoc *Platform = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
2747 
2748  IdentifierInfo *II = Platform->Ident;
2749  if (AvailabilityAttr::getPrettyPlatformName(II->getName()).empty())
2750  S.Diag(Platform->Loc, diag::warn_availability_unknown_platform)
2751  << Platform->Ident;
2752 
2753  auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
2754  if (!ND) // We warned about this already, so just return.
2755  return;
2756 
2757  AvailabilityChange Introduced = AL.getAvailabilityIntroduced();
2758  AvailabilityChange Deprecated = AL.getAvailabilityDeprecated();
2759  AvailabilityChange Obsoleted = AL.getAvailabilityObsoleted();
2760  bool IsUnavailable = AL.getUnavailableLoc().isValid();
2761  bool IsStrict = AL.getStrictLoc().isValid();
2762  StringRef Str;
2763  if (const auto *SE = dyn_cast_if_present<StringLiteral>(AL.getMessageExpr()))
2764  Str = SE->getString();
2765  StringRef Replacement;
2766  if (const auto *SE =
2767  dyn_cast_if_present<StringLiteral>(AL.getReplacementExpr()))
2768  Replacement = SE->getString();
2769 
2770  if (II->isStr("swift")) {
2771  if (Introduced.isValid() || Obsoleted.isValid() ||
2772  (!IsUnavailable && !Deprecated.isValid())) {
2773  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
2774  diag::warn_availability_swift_unavailable_deprecated_only);
2775  return;
2776  }
2777  }
2778 
2779  if (II->isStr("fuchsia")) {
2780  std::optional<unsigned> Min, Sub;
2781  if ((Min = Introduced.Version.getMinor()) ||
2782  (Sub = Introduced.Version.getSubminor())) {
2783  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_availability_fuchsia_unavailable_minor);
2784  return;
2785  }
2786  }
2787 
2788  int PriorityModifier = AL.isPragmaClangAttribute()
2789  ? Sema::AP_PragmaClangAttribute
2790  : Sema::AP_Explicit;
2791  AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2792  ND, AL, II, false /*Implicit*/, Introduced.Version, Deprecated.Version,
2793  Obsoleted.Version, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict, Replacement,
2794  Sema::AMK_None, PriorityModifier);
2795  if (NewAttr)
2796  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2797 
2798  // Transcribe "ios" to "watchos" (and add a new attribute) if the versioning
2799  // matches before the start of the watchOS platform.
2800  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isWatchOS()) {
2801  IdentifierInfo *NewII = nullptr;
2802  if (II->getName() == "ios")
2803  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("watchos");
2804  else if (II->getName() == "ios_app_extension")
2805  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("watchos_app_extension");
2806 
2807  if (NewII) {
2808  const auto *SDKInfo = S.getDarwinSDKInfoForAvailabilityChecking();
2809  const auto *IOSToWatchOSMapping =
2810  SDKInfo ? SDKInfo->getVersionMapping(
2811  DarwinSDKInfo::OSEnvPair::iOStoWatchOSPair())
2812  : nullptr;
2813 
2814  auto adjustWatchOSVersion =
2815  [IOSToWatchOSMapping](VersionTuple Version) -> VersionTuple {
2816  if (Version.empty())
2817  return Version;
2818  auto MinimumWatchOSVersion = VersionTuple(2, 0);
2819 
2820  if (IOSToWatchOSMapping) {
2821  if (auto MappedVersion = IOSToWatchOSMapping->map(
2822  Version, MinimumWatchOSVersion, std::nullopt)) {
2823  return *MappedVersion;
2824  }
2825  }
2826 
2827  auto Major = Version.getMajor();
2828  auto NewMajor = Major >= 9 ? Major - 7 : 0;
2829  if (NewMajor >= 2) {
2830  if (Version.getMinor()) {
2831  if (Version.getSubminor())
2832  return VersionTuple(NewMajor, *Version.getMinor(),
2833  *Version.getSubminor());
2834  else
2835  return VersionTuple(NewMajor, *Version.getMinor());
2836  }
2837  return VersionTuple(NewMajor);
2838  }
2839 
2840  return MinimumWatchOSVersion;
2841  };
2842 
2843  auto NewIntroduced = adjustWatchOSVersion(Introduced.Version);
2844  auto NewDeprecated = adjustWatchOSVersion(Deprecated.Version);
2845  auto NewObsoleted = adjustWatchOSVersion(Obsoleted.Version);
2846 
2847  AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2848  ND, AL, NewII, true /*Implicit*/, NewIntroduced, NewDeprecated,
2849  NewObsoleted, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict, Replacement,
2850  Sema::AMK_None,
2851  PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform);
2852  if (NewAttr)
2853  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2854  }
2855  } else if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isTvOS()) {
2856  // Transcribe "ios" to "tvos" (and add a new attribute) if the versioning
2857  // matches before the start of the tvOS platform.
2858  IdentifierInfo *NewII = nullptr;
2859  if (II->getName() == "ios")
2860  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("tvos");
2861  else if (II->getName() == "ios_app_extension")
2862  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("tvos_app_extension");
2863 
2864  if (NewII) {
2865  const auto *SDKInfo = S.getDarwinSDKInfoForAvailabilityChecking();
2866  const auto *IOSToTvOSMapping =
2867  SDKInfo ? SDKInfo->getVersionMapping(
2868  DarwinSDKInfo::OSEnvPair::iOStoTvOSPair())
2869  : nullptr;
2870 
2871  auto AdjustTvOSVersion =
2872  [IOSToTvOSMapping](VersionTuple Version) -> VersionTuple {
2873  if (Version.empty())
2874  return Version;
2875 
2876  if (IOSToTvOSMapping) {
2877  if (auto MappedVersion = IOSToTvOSMapping->map(
2878  Version, VersionTuple(0, 0), std::nullopt)) {
2879  return *MappedVersion;
2880  }
2881  }
2882  return Version;
2883  };
2884 
2885  auto NewIntroduced = AdjustTvOSVersion(Introduced.Version);
2886  auto NewDeprecated = AdjustTvOSVersion(Deprecated.Version);
2887  auto NewObsoleted = AdjustTvOSVersion(Obsoleted.Version);
2888 
2889  AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2890  ND, AL, NewII, true /*Implicit*/, NewIntroduced, NewDeprecated,
2891  NewObsoleted, IsUnavailable, Str, IsStrict, Replacement,
2892  Sema::AMK_None,
2893  PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform);
2894  if (NewAttr)
2895  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2896  }
2897  } else if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getOS() ==
2898  llvm::Triple::IOS &&
2899  S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isMacCatalystEnvironment()) {
2900  auto GetSDKInfo = [&]() {
2901  return S.getDarwinSDKInfoForAvailabilityChecking(AL.getRange().getBegin(),
2902  "macOS");
2903  };
2904 
2905  // Transcribe "ios" to "maccatalyst" (and add a new attribute).
2906  IdentifierInfo *NewII = nullptr;
2907  if (II->getName() == "ios")
2908  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("maccatalyst");
2909  else if (II->getName() == "ios_app_extension")
2910  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("maccatalyst_app_extension");
2911  if (NewII) {
2912  auto MinMacCatalystVersion = [](const VersionTuple &V) {
2913  if (V.empty())
2914  return V;
2915  if (V.getMajor() < 13 ||
2916  (V.getMajor() == 13 && V.getMinor() && *V.getMinor() < 1))
2917  return VersionTuple(13, 1); // The min Mac Catalyst version is 13.1.
2918  return V;
2919  };
2920  AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2921  ND, AL, NewII, true /*Implicit*/,
2922  MinMacCatalystVersion(Introduced.Version),
2923  MinMacCatalystVersion(Deprecated.Version),
2924  MinMacCatalystVersion(Obsoleted.Version), IsUnavailable, Str,
2925  IsStrict, Replacement, Sema::AMK_None,
2926  PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform);
2927  if (NewAttr)
2928  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2929  } else if (II->getName() == "macos" && GetSDKInfo() &&
2930  (!Introduced.Version.empty() || !Deprecated.Version.empty() ||
2931  !Obsoleted.Version.empty())) {
2932  if (const auto *MacOStoMacCatalystMapping =
2933  GetSDKInfo()->getVersionMapping(
2934  DarwinSDKInfo::OSEnvPair::macOStoMacCatalystPair())) {
2935  // Infer Mac Catalyst availability from the macOS availability attribute
2936  // if it has versioned availability. Don't infer 'unavailable'. This
2937  // inferred availability has lower priority than the other availability
2938  // attributes that are inferred from 'ios'.
2939  NewII = &S.Context.Idents.get("maccatalyst");
2940  auto RemapMacOSVersion =
2941  [&](const VersionTuple &V) -> std::optional<VersionTuple> {
2942  if (V.empty())
2943  return std::nullopt;
2944  // API_TO_BE_DEPRECATED is 100000.
2945  if (V.getMajor() == 100000)
2946  return VersionTuple(100000);
2947  // The minimum iosmac version is 13.1
2948  return MacOStoMacCatalystMapping->map(V, VersionTuple(13, 1),
2949  std::nullopt);
2950  };
2951  std::optional<VersionTuple> NewIntroduced =
2952  RemapMacOSVersion(Introduced.Version),
2953  NewDeprecated =
2954  RemapMacOSVersion(Deprecated.Version),
2955  NewObsoleted =
2956  RemapMacOSVersion(Obsoleted.Version);
2957  if (NewIntroduced || NewDeprecated || NewObsoleted) {
2958  auto VersionOrEmptyVersion =
2959  [](const std::optional<VersionTuple> &V) -> VersionTuple {
2960  return V ? *V : VersionTuple();
2961  };
2962  AvailabilityAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeAvailabilityAttr(
2963  ND, AL, NewII, true /*Implicit*/,
2964  VersionOrEmptyVersion(NewIntroduced),
2965  VersionOrEmptyVersion(NewDeprecated),
2966  VersionOrEmptyVersion(NewObsoleted), /*IsUnavailable=*/false, Str,
2967  IsStrict, Replacement, Sema::AMK_None,
2968  PriorityModifier + Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform +
2969  Sema::AP_InferredFromOtherPlatform);
2970  if (NewAttr)
2971  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
2972  }
2973  }
2974  }
2975  }
2976 }

2981  return;

2990  StringRef USR;

2992  USR = SE->getString();

2998 template <class T>
2999 static T *mergeVisibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
3000  typename T::VisibilityType value) {
3001  T *existingAttr = D->getAttr<T>();
3002  if (existingAttr) {
3003  typename T::VisibilityType existingValue = existingAttr->getVisibility();
3004  if (existingValue == value)
3005  return nullptr;
3006  S.Diag(existingAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_visibility);
3007  S.Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3008  D->dropAttr<T>();
3009  }
3010  return ::new (S.Context) T(S.Context, CI, value);
3011 }

3025 static void handleVisibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL,
3026  bool isTypeVisibility) {
3027  // Visibility attributes don't mean anything on a typedef.
3028  if (isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
3029  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << AL;
3030  return;
3031  }
3032 
3033  // 'type_visibility' can only go on a type or namespace.
3034  if (isTypeVisibility && !(isa<TagDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) ||
3035  isa<NamespaceDecl>(D))) {
3036  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
3037  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedTypeOrNamespace;
3038  return;
3039  }
3040 
3041  // Check that the argument is a string literal.
3042  StringRef TypeStr;
3043  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
3044  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, TypeStr, &LiteralLoc))
3045  return;
3046 
3047  VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType type;
3048  if (!VisibilityAttr::ConvertStrToVisibilityType(TypeStr, type)) {
3049  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL
3050  << TypeStr;
3051  return;
3052  }
3053 
3054  // Complain about attempts to use protected visibility on targets
3055  // (like Darwin) that don't support it.
3056  if (type == VisibilityAttr::Protected &&
3057  !S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasProtectedVisibility()) {
3058  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_protected_visibility);
3059  type = VisibilityAttr::Default;
3060  }
3061 
3062  Attr *newAttr;
3063  if (isTypeVisibility) {
3064  newAttr = S.mergeTypeVisibilityAttr(
3065  D, AL, (TypeVisibilityAttr::VisibilityType)type);
3066  } else {
3067  newAttr = S.mergeVisibilityAttr(D, AL, type);
3068  }
3069  if (newAttr)
3070  D->addAttr(newAttr);
3071 }

3180 static void handleSentinelAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3181  unsigned sentinel = (unsigned)SentinelAttr::DefaultSentinel;
3182  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 0) {
3183  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
3184  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> Idx = llvm::APSInt(32);
3185  if (E->isTypeDependent() || !(Idx = E->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
3186  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
3187  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
3188  return;
3189  }
3190 
3191  if (Idx->isSigned() && Idx->isNegative()) {
3192  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_sentinel_less_than_zero)
3193  << E->getSourceRange();
3194  return;
3195  }
3196 
3197  sentinel = Idx->getZExtValue();
3198  }
3199 
3200  unsigned nullPos = (unsigned)SentinelAttr::DefaultNullPos;
3201  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
3202  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
3203  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> Idx = llvm::APSInt(32);
3204  if (E->isTypeDependent() || !(Idx = E->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
3205  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
3206  << AL << 2 << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
3207  return;
3208  }
3209  nullPos = Idx->getZExtValue();
3210 
3211  if ((Idx->isSigned() && Idx->isNegative()) || nullPos > 1) {
3212  // FIXME: This error message could be improved, it would be nice
3213  // to say what the bounds actually are.
3214  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_sentinel_not_zero_or_one)
3215  << E->getSourceRange();
3216  return;
3217  }
3218  }
3219 
3220  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3221  const FunctionType *FT = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
3222  if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(FT)) {
3223  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_named_arguments);
3224  return;
3225  }
3226 
3227  if (!cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)->isVariadic()) {
3228  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 0;
3229  return;
3230  }
3231  } else if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
3232  if (!MD->isVariadic()) {
3233  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 0;
3234  return;
3235  }
3236  } else if (const auto *BD = dyn_cast<BlockDecl>(D)) {
3237  if (!BD->isVariadic()) {
3238  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << 1;
3239  return;
3240  }
3241  } else if (const auto *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
3242  QualType Ty = V->getType();
3243  if (Ty->isBlockPointerType() || Ty->isFunctionPointerType()) {
3244  const FunctionType *FT = Ty->isFunctionPointerType()
3245  ? D->getFunctionType()
3246  : Ty->castAs<BlockPointerType>()
3247  ->getPointeeType()
3248  ->castAs<FunctionType>();
3249  if (!cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)->isVariadic()) {
3250  int m = Ty->isFunctionPointerType() ? 0 : 1;
3251  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_sentinel_not_variadic) << m;
3252  return;
3253  }
3254  } else {
3255  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
3256  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
3257  << ExpectedFunctionMethodOrBlock;
3258  return;
3259  }
3260  } else {
3261  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
3262  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
3263  << ExpectedFunctionMethodOrBlock;
3264  return;
3265  }
3266  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SentinelAttr(S.Context, AL, sentinel, nullPos));
3267 }

3269 static void handleWarnUnusedResult(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3270  if (D->getFunctionType() &&
3271  D->getFunctionType()->getReturnType()->isVoidType() &&
3272  !isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(D)) {
3273  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_void_function_method) << AL << 0;
3274  return;
3275  }
3276  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
3277  if (MD->getReturnType()->isVoidType()) {
3278  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_void_function_method) << AL << 1;
3279  return;
3280  }
3281 
3282  StringRef Str;
3283  if (AL.isStandardAttributeSyntax() && !AL.getScopeName()) {
3284  // The standard attribute cannot be applied to variable declarations such
3285  // as a function pointer.
3286  if (isa<VarDecl>(D))
3287  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type_str)
3288  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
3289  << "functions, classes, or enumerations";
3290 
3291  // If this is spelled as the standard C++17 attribute, but not in C++17,
3292  // warn about using it as an extension. If there are attribute arguments,
3293  // then claim it's a C++20 extension instead.
3294  // FIXME: If WG14 does not seem likely to adopt the same feature, add an
3295  // extension warning for C23 mode.
3296  const LangOptions &LO = S.getLangOpts();
3297  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 1) {
3298  if (LO.CPlusPlus && !LO.CPlusPlus20)
3299  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx20_attr) << AL;
3300 
3301  // Since this is spelled [[nodiscard]], get the optional string
3302  // literal. If in C++ mode, but not in C++20 mode, diagnose as an
3303  // extension.
3304  // FIXME: C23 should support this feature as well, even as an extension.
3305  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, nullptr))
3306  return;
3307  } else if (LO.CPlusPlus && !LO.CPlusPlus17)
3308  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx17_attr) << AL;
3309  }
3310 
3311  if ((!AL.isGNUAttribute() &&
3312  !(AL.isStandardAttributeSyntax() && AL.isClangScope())) &&
3313  isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
3314  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_unused_result_typedef_unsupported_spelling)
3315  << AL.isGNUScope();
3316  return;
3317  }
3318 
3319  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) WarnUnusedResultAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
3320 }

3322 static void handleWeakImportAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {

3326  if (isDef)

3328  << "weak_import";
3329  else if (isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) ||
3330  (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin() &&
3331  (isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) || isa<EnumDecl>(D)))) {
3332  // Nothing to warn about here.
3333  } else
3334  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
3335  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedVariableOrFunction;
3336 
3337  return;

3343 // Handles reqd_work_group_size and work_group_size_hint.
3344 template <typename WorkGroupAttr>
3345 static void handleWorkGroupSize(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3346  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 3))
3347  return;
3348 
3349  uint32_t WGSize[3];
3350  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
3351  const Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(i);
3352  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, WGSize[i], i,
3353  /*StrictlyUnsigned=*/true))
3354  return;
3355  if (WGSize[i] == 0) {
3356  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_is_zero)
3357  << AL << E->getSourceRange();
3358  return;
3359  }
3360  }
3361 
3362  WorkGroupAttr *Existing = D->getAttr<WorkGroupAttr>();
3363  if (Existing && !(Existing->getXDim() == WGSize[0] &&
3364  Existing->getYDim() == WGSize[1] &&
3365  Existing->getZDim() == WGSize[2]))
3366  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
3367 
3368  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
3369  WorkGroupAttr(S.Context, AL, WGSize[0], WGSize[1], WGSize[2]));
3370 }
3371 
3372 // Returns a DupArgResult value; Same means the args have the same value,
3373 // Different means the args do not have the same value, and Unknown means that
3374 // the args cannot (yet) be compared.
3375 enum class DupArgResult { Unknown, Same, Different };
3376 static DupArgResult AreArgValuesIdentical(const Expr *LHS, const Expr *RHS) {
3377  // If both operands are nullptr they are unspecified and are considered the
3378  // same.
3379  if (!LHS && !RHS)
3380  return DupArgResult::Same;
3381 
3382  // Otherwise, if either operand is nullptr they are considered different.
3383  if (!LHS || !RHS)
3384  return DupArgResult::Different;
3385 
3386  // Otherwise, if either operand is still value dependent, we can't test
3387  // anything.
3388  const auto *LHSCE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(LHS);
3389  const auto *RHSCE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(RHS);
3390  if (!LHSCE || !RHSCE)
3391  return DupArgResult::Unknown;
3392 
3393  // Otherwise, test that the values.
3394  return LHSCE->getResultAsAPSInt() == RHSCE->getResultAsAPSInt()
3395  ? DupArgResult::Same
3396  : DupArgResult::Different;
3397 }
3398 
3399 // Returns true if any of the specified dimensions (X,Y,Z) differ between the
3400 // arguments.
3401 bool Sema::AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(const Expr *LHSXDim, const Expr *LHSYDim,
3402  const Expr *LHSZDim, const Expr *RHSXDim,
3403  const Expr *RHSYDim, const Expr *RHSZDim) {
3404  DupArgResult Results[] = {AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSXDim, RHSXDim),
3405  AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSYDim, RHSYDim),
3406  AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSZDim, RHSZDim)};
3407  return llvm::is_contained(Results, DupArgResult::Different);
3408 }
3409 
3410 // Returns true if all of the specified dimensions (X,Y,Z) are the same between
3411 // the arguments.
3412 bool Sema::AllWorkGroupSizesSame(const Expr *LHSXDim, const Expr *LHSYDim,
3413  const Expr *LHSZDim, const Expr *RHSXDim,
3414  const Expr *RHSYDim, const Expr *RHSZDim) {
3415  DupArgResult Results[] = {AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSXDim, RHSXDim),
3416  AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSYDim, RHSYDim),
3417  AreArgValuesIdentical(LHSZDim, RHSZDim)};
3418  return llvm::all_of(Results,
3419  [](DupArgResult V) { return V == DupArgResult::Same; });
3420 }
3421 
3422 void Sema::AddSYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
3423  Expr *XDim, Expr *YDim, Expr *ZDim) {
3424  // Returns nullptr if diagnosing, otherwise returns the original expression
3425  // or the original expression converted to a constant expression.
3426  auto CheckAndConvertArg = [&](Expr *E) -> std::optional<Expr *> {
3427  // We can only check if the expression is not value dependent.
3428  if (E && !E->isValueDependent()) {
3429  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
3430  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
3431  if (Res.isInvalid())
3432  return std::nullopt;
3433  E = Res.get();
3434 
3435  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
3436  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
3437  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
3438  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
3439  return std::nullopt;
3440  }
3441  }
3442 
3443  return E;
3444  };
3445 
3446  // Check all three argument values, and if any are bad, bail out. This will
3447  // convert the given expressions into constant expressions when possible.
3448  std::optional<Expr *> XDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(XDim);
3449  std::optional<Expr *> YDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(YDim);
3450  std::optional<Expr *> ZDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(ZDim);
3451  if (!XDimConvert || !YDimConvert || !ZDimConvert)
3452  return;
3453  XDim = XDimConvert.value();
3454  YDim = YDimConvert.value();
3455  ZDim = ZDimConvert.value();
3456 
3457  // If the attribute was already applied with different arguments, then
3458  // diagnose the second attribute as a duplicate and don't add it.
3459  if (const auto *Existing = D->getAttr<SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr>()) {
3460  // If any of the results are known to be different, we can diagnose at this
3461  // point and drop the attribute.
3462  if (AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3463  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim())) {
3464  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
3465  Diag(Existing->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3466  return;
3467  }
3468  // If all of the results are known to be the same, we can silently drop the
3469  // attribute. Otherwise, we have to add the attribute and resolve its
3470  // differences later.
3471  if (AllWorkGroupSizesSame(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3472  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim()))
3473  return;
3474  }
3475 
3476  D->addAttr(::new (Context)
3477  SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(Context, CI, XDim, YDim, ZDim));
3478 }
3479 
3480 SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr *
3481 Sema::MergeSYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(Decl *D,
3482  const SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr &A) {
3483  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute already applied.
3484  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr>()) {
3485  // If any of the results are known to be different, we can diagnose at this
3486  // point and drop the attribute.
3487  if (AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3488  DeclAttr->getZDim(), A.getXDim(), A.getYDim(),
3489  A.getZDim())) {
3490  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
3491  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3492  return nullptr;
3493  }
3494  // If all of the results are known to be the same, we can silently drop the
3495  // attribute. Otherwise, we have to add the attribute and resolve its
3496  // differences later.
3497  if (AllWorkGroupSizesSame(DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3498  DeclAttr->getZDim(), A.getXDim(), A.getYDim(),
3499  A.getZDim()))
3500  return nullptr;
3501  }
3502  return ::new (Context) SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(Context, A, A.getXDim(),
3503  A.getYDim(), A.getZDim());
3504 }

3506 // Handles SYCL work_group_size_hint.
3507 static void handleSYCLWorkGroupSizeHint(Sema &S, Decl *D,
3508  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3509  S.CheckDeprecatedSYCLAttributeSpelling(AL);
3510 
3511  // __attribute__((work_group_size_hint) requires exactly three arguments.
3512  if (AL.getSyntax() == ParsedAttr::AS_GNU || !AL.hasScope() ||
3513  (AL.hasScope() && !AL.getScopeName()->isStr("sycl"))) {
3514  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 3))
3515  return;
3516  } else if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1) || !AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 3))
3517  return;
3518 
3519  size_t NumArgs = AL.getNumArgs();
3520  Expr *XDimExpr = NumArgs > 0 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(0) : nullptr;
3521  Expr *YDimExpr = NumArgs > 1 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr;
3522  Expr *ZDimExpr = NumArgs > 2 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(2) : nullptr;
3523  S.AddSYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(D, AL, XDimExpr, YDimExpr, ZDimExpr);
3524 }
3525 
3526 static void handleWorkGroupSizeHint(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
3527  // Handle the attribute based on whether we are targeting SYCL or not.
3528  if (S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice || S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsHost)
3529  handleSYCLWorkGroupSizeHint(S, D, AL);
3530  else
3531  handleWorkGroupSize<WorkGroupSizeHintAttr>(S, D, AL);
3532 }
3533 
3534 // Checks correctness of mutual usage of different work_group_size attributes:
3535 // reqd_work_group_size, max_work_group_size, and max_global_work_dim.
3536 //
3537 // If [[intel::max_work_group_size(X, Y, Z)]] or
3538 // [[sycl::reqd_work_group_size(X, Y, Z)]] or
3539 // [[cl::reqd_work_group_size(X, Y, Z)]]
3540 // or __attribute__((reqd_work_group_size)) attribute is specified on a
3541 // declaration along with [[intel::max_global_work_dim()]] attribute, check to
3542 // see if all arguments of 'max_work_group_size' or different spellings of
3543 // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute hold value 1 in case the argument of
3544 // [[intel::max_global_work_dim()]] attribute value equals to 0.
3545 static bool InvalidWorkGroupSizeAttrs(Sema &S, const Expr *MGValue,
3546  const Expr *XDim, const Expr *YDim,
3547  const Expr *ZDim) {
3548  // If any of the operand is still value dependent, we can't test anything.
3549  const auto *MGValueExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(MGValue);
3550  const auto *XDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(XDim);
3551 
3552  if (!MGValueExpr || !XDimExpr)
3553  return false;
3554 
3555  // Y and Z may be optional so we allow them to be null and consider them
3556  // dependent if the original epxression was not null while the result of the
3557  // cast is.
3558  const auto *YDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(YDim);
3559  const auto *ZDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(ZDim);
3560 
3561  if ((!YDimExpr && YDim) || (!ZDimExpr && ZDim))
3562  return false;
3563 
3564  // Otherwise, check if the attribute values are equal to one.
3565  // Y and Z dimensions are optional and are considered trivially 1 if
3566  // unspecified.
3567  return (MGValueExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() == 0 &&
3568  (XDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != 1 ||
3569  (YDimExpr && YDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != 1) ||
3570  (ZDimExpr && ZDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != 1)));
3571 }
3572 
3573 // Checks correctness of mutual usage of different work_group_size attributes:
3574 // reqd_work_group_size and max_work_group_size.
3575 //
3576 // If the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration along
3577 // with 'max_work_group_size' attribute, check to see if values of
3578 // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments are equal to or less than values
3579 // of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3580 //
3581 // The arguments to reqd_work_group_size are ordered based on which index
3582 // increments the fastest. In OpenCL, the first argument is the index that
3583 // increments the fastest, and in SYCL, the last argument is the index that
3584 // increments the fastest.
3585 //
3586 // __attribute__((reqd_work_group_size)) follows the OpenCL rules in OpenCL
3587 // mode. All spellings of reqd_work_group_size attribute (regardless of
3588 // syntax used) follow the SYCL rules when in SYCL mode.
3589 bool Sema::CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(
3590  const Expr *RWGSXDim, const Expr *RWGSYDim, const Expr *RWGSZDim,
3591  const Expr *MWGSXDim, const Expr *MWGSYDim, const Expr *MWGSZDim) {
3592  // If any of the operand is still value dependent, we can't test anything.
3593  const auto *RWGSXDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(RWGSXDim);
3594  const auto *MWGSXDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(MWGSXDim);
3595  const auto *MWGSYDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(MWGSYDim);
3596  const auto *MWGSZDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(MWGSZDim);
3597 
3598  if (!RWGSXDimExpr || !MWGSXDimExpr || !MWGSYDimExpr || !MWGSZDimExpr)
3599  return false;
3600 
3601  // Y and Z may be optional so we allow them to be null and consider them
3602  // dependent if the original epxression was not null while the result of the
3603  // cast is.
3604  const auto *RWGSYDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(RWGSYDim);
3605  const auto *RWGSZDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(RWGSZDim);
3606 
3607  if ((!RWGSYDimExpr && RWGSYDim) || (!RWGSZDimExpr && RWGSZDim))
3608  return false;
3609 
3610  // SYCL reorders arguments based on the dimensionality.
3611  // If we only have the X-dimension, there is no change to the expressions,
3612  // otherwise the last specified dimension acts as the first dimension in the
3613  // work-group size.
3614  const ConstantExpr *FirstRWGDimExpr = RWGSXDimExpr;
3615  const ConstantExpr *SecondRWGDimExpr = RWGSYDimExpr;
3616  const ConstantExpr *ThirdRWGDimExpr = RWGSZDimExpr;
3617  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice && RWGSYDim)
3618  std::swap(FirstRWGDimExpr, RWGSZDim ? ThirdRWGDimExpr : SecondRWGDimExpr);
3619 
3620  // Check if values of 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments are greater
3621  // than values of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3622  bool CheckFirstArgument =
3623  FirstRWGDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue() >
3624  MWGSZDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue();
3625 
3626  bool CheckSecondArgument =
3627  SecondRWGDimExpr && SecondRWGDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue() >
3628  MWGSYDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue();
3629 
3630  bool CheckThirdArgument =
3631  ThirdRWGDimExpr && ThirdRWGDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue() >
3632  MWGSXDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue();
3633 
3634  return CheckFirstArgument || CheckSecondArgument || CheckThirdArgument;
3635 }
3636 
3637 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr(Decl *D,
3638  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
3639  Expr *XDim, Expr *YDim,
3640  Expr *ZDim) {
3641  // Returns nullptr if diagnosing, otherwise returns the original expression
3642  // or the original expression converted to a constant expression.
3643  auto CheckAndConvertArg = [&](Expr *E) -> Expr * {
3644  // Check if the expression is not value dependent.
3645  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
3646  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
3647  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
3648  if (Res.isInvalid())
3649  return nullptr;
3650  E = Res.get();
3651 
3652  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
3653  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
3654  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
3655  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
3656  return nullptr;
3657  }
3658  }
3659  return E;
3660  };
3661 
3662  // Check all three argument values, and if any are bad, bail out. This will
3663  // convert the given expressions into constant expressions when possible.
3664  XDim = CheckAndConvertArg(XDim);
3665  YDim = CheckAndConvertArg(YDim);
3666  ZDim = CheckAndConvertArg(ZDim);
3667  if (!XDim || !YDim || !ZDim)
3668  return;
3669 
3670  // If the 'max_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration along
3671  // with 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute, check to see if values of
3672  // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments are equal to or less than values
3673  // of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3674  //
3675  // We emit diagnostic if values of 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments
3676  // are greater than values of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3677  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3678  if (CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3679  DeclAttr->getZDim(), XDim, YDim, ZDim)) {
3680  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_conflicting_sycl_function_attributes)
3681  << CI << DeclAttr;
3682  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3683  return;
3684  }
3685  }
3686 
3687  // If the declaration has a SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if
3688  // the attribute holds values equal to (1, 1, 1) in case the value of
3689  // SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr equals to 0.
3690  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>()) {
3691  if (InvalidWorkGroupSizeAttrs(*this, DeclAttr->getValue(), XDim, YDim,
3692  ZDim)) {
3693  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_x_y_z_arguments_must_be_one)
3694  << CI << DeclAttr;
3695  return;
3696  }
3697  }
3698 
3699  // If the attribute was already applied with different arguments, then
3700  // diagnose the second attribute as a duplicate and don't add it.
3701  if (const auto *Existing = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3702  // If any of the results are known to be different, we can diagnose at this
3703  // point and drop the attribute.
3704  if (AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3705  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim())) {
3706  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
3707  Diag(Existing->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3708  return;
3709  }
3710  // If all of the results are known to be the same, we can silently drop the
3711  // attribute. Otherwise, we have to add the attribute and resolve its
3712  // differences later.
3713  if (AllWorkGroupSizesSame(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3714  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim()))
3715  return;
3716  }
3717 
3718  D->addAttr(::new (Context)
3719  SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr(Context, CI, XDim, YDim, ZDim));
3720 }

3798 // Handles reqd_work_group_size.
3799 // If the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration along
3800 // with 'num_simd_work_items' attribute, the required work group size specified
3801 // by 'num_simd_work_items' attribute must evenly divide the index that
3802 // increments fastest in the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute.
3803 //
3804 // The arguments to reqd_work_group_size are ordered based on which index
3805 // increments the fastest. In OpenCL, the first argument is the index that
3806 // increments the fastest, and in SYCL, the last argument is the index that
3807 // increments the fastest.
3808 //
3809 // __attribute__((reqd_work_group_size)) follows the OpenCL rules in OpenCL
3810 // mode. All spellings of reqd_work_group_size attribute (regardless of
3811 // syntax used) follow the SYCL rules when in SYCL mode.
3812 static bool CheckWorkGroupSize(Sema &S, const Expr *NSWIValue,
3813  const Expr *RWGSXDim, const Expr *RWGSYDim,
3814  const Expr *RWGSZDim) {
3815  // If any of the operand is still value dependent, we can't test anything.
3816  const auto *NSWIValueExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(NSWIValue);
3817  const auto *RWGSXDimExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(RWGSXDim);
3818 
3819  if (!NSWIValueExpr || !RWGSXDimExpr)
3820  return false;
3821 
3822  // Y and Z may be optional so we allow them to be null and consider them
3823  // dependent if the original epxression was not null while the result of the
3824  // cast is.
3825  const auto *RWGSYDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(RWGSYDim);
3826  const auto *RWGSZDimExpr = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantExpr>(RWGSZDim);
3827 
3828  if ((!RWGSYDimExpr && RWGSYDim) || (!RWGSZDimExpr && RWGSZDim))
3829  return false;
3830 
3831  // Otherwise, check which argument increments the fastest.
3832  const ConstantExpr *LastRWGSDimExpr =
3833  RWGSZDim ? RWGSZDimExpr : (RWGSYDim ? RWGSYDimExpr : RWGSXDimExpr);
3834  unsigned WorkGroupSize = LastRWGSDimExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue();
3835 
3836  // Check if the required work group size specified by 'num_simd_work_items'
3837  // attribute evenly divides the index that increments fastest in the
3838  // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute.
3839  return WorkGroupSize % NSWIValueExpr->getResultAsAPSInt().getZExtValue() != 0;
3840 }
3841 
3842 void Sema::AddSYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
3843  Expr *XDim, Expr *YDim, Expr *ZDim) {
3844  // Returns nullptr if diagnosing, otherwise returns the original expression
3845  // or the original expression converted to a constant expression.
3846  auto CheckAndConvertArg = [&](Expr *E) -> std::optional<Expr *> {
3847  // Check if the expression is not value dependent.
3848  if (E && !E->isValueDependent()) {
3849  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
3850  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
3851  if (Res.isInvalid())
3852  return std::nullopt;
3853  E = Res.get();
3854 
3855  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
3856  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
3857  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
3858  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
3859  return std::nullopt;
3860  }
3861  }
3862  return E;
3863  };
3864 
3865  // Check all three argument values, and if any are bad, bail out. This will
3866  // convert the given expressions into constant expressions when possible.
3867  std::optional<Expr *> XDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(XDim);
3868  std::optional<Expr *> YDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(YDim);
3869  std::optional<Expr *> ZDimConvert = CheckAndConvertArg(ZDim);
3870  if (!XDimConvert || !YDimConvert || !ZDimConvert)
3871  return;
3872  XDim = XDimConvert.value();
3873  YDim = YDimConvert.value();
3874  ZDim = ZDimConvert.value();
3875 
3876  // If the declaration has a ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if
3877  // the attribute holds values equal to (1, 1, 1) in case the value of
3878  // SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr equals to 0.
3879  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>()) {
3880  if (InvalidWorkGroupSizeAttrs(*this, DeclAttr->getValue(), XDim, YDim,
3881  ZDim)) {
3882  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_x_y_z_arguments_must_be_one)
3883  << CI << DeclAttr;
3884  }
3885  }
3886 
3887  // If the 'max_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration along
3888  // with 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute, check to see if values of
3889  // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments are equal to or less than values
3890  // of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3891  //
3892  // We emit diagnostic if values of 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments
3893  // are greater than values of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3894  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3895  if (CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(XDim, YDim, ZDim, DeclAttr->getXDim(),
3896  DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3897  DeclAttr->getZDim())) {
3898  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_conflicting_sycl_function_attributes)
3899  << CI << DeclAttr;
3900  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3901  return;
3902  }
3903  }
3904 
3905  // If the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration
3906  // along with 'num_simd_work_items' attribute, the required work group size
3907  // specified by 'num_simd_work_items' attribute must evenly divide the index
3908  // that increments fastest in the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute.
3909  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr>()) {
3910  if (CheckWorkGroupSize(*this, DeclAttr->getValue(), XDim, YDim, ZDim)) {
3911  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_num_kernel_wrong_reqd_wg_size)
3912  << DeclAttr << CI;
3913  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3914  return;
3915  }
3916  }
3917 
3918  // If the attribute was already applied with different arguments, then
3919  // diagnose the second attribute as a duplicate and don't add it.
3920  if (const auto *Existing = D->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3921  // If any of the results are known to be different, we can diagnose at this
3922  // point and drop the attribute.
3923  if (AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3924  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim())) {
3925  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
3926  Diag(Existing->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3927  return;
3928  }
3929 
3930  // If all of the results are known to be the same, we can silently drop the
3931  // attribute. Otherwise, we have to add the attribute and resolve its
3932  // differences later.
3933  if (AllWorkGroupSizesSame(XDim, YDim, ZDim, Existing->getXDim(),
3934  Existing->getYDim(), Existing->getZDim()))
3935  return;
3936  }
3937 
3938  D->addAttr(::new (Context)
3939  SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(Context, CI, XDim, YDim, ZDim));
3940 }
3941 
3942 SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr *
3943 Sema::MergeSYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(Decl *D,
3944  const SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr &A) {
3945  // If the declaration has a SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if the
3946  // attribute holds values equal to (1, 1, 1) in case the value of
3947  // SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr equals to 0.
3948  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>()) {
3949  if (InvalidWorkGroupSizeAttrs(*this, DeclAttr->getValue(), A.getXDim(),
3950  A.getYDim(), A.getZDim())) {
3951  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_x_y_z_arguments_must_be_one)
3952  << &A << DeclAttr;
3953  return nullptr;
3954  }
3955  }
3956 
3957  // If the 'max_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration along
3958  // with 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute, check to see if values of
3959  // 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments are equal or less than values
3960  // of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3961  //
3962  // We emit diagnostic if values of 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute arguments
3963  // are greater than values of 'max_work_group_size' attribute arguments.
3964  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3965  if (CheckMaxAllowedWorkGroupSize(A.getXDim(), A.getYDim(), A.getZDim(),
3966  DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3967  DeclAttr->getZDim())) {
3968  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::err_conflicting_sycl_function_attributes)
3969  << DeclAttr << &A;
3970  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3971  return nullptr;
3972  }
3973  }
3974 
3975  // If the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute is specified on a declaration
3976  // along with 'num_simd_work_items' attribute, the required work group size
3977  // specified by 'num_simd_work_items' attribute must evenly divide the index
3978  // that increments fastest in the 'reqd_work_group_size' attribute.
3979  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr>()) {
3980  if (CheckWorkGroupSize(*this, DeclAttr->getValue(), A.getXDim(),
3981  A.getYDim(), A.getZDim())) {
3982  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_num_kernel_wrong_reqd_wg_size)
3983  << DeclAttr << &A;
3984  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
3985  return nullptr;
3986  }
3987  }
3988 
3989  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute already applied.
3990  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>()) {
3991  // If any of the results are known to be different, we can diagnose at this
3992  // point and drop the attribute.
3993  if (AnyWorkGroupSizesDiffer(DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
3994  DeclAttr->getZDim(), A.getXDim(), A.getYDim(),
3995  A.getZDim())) {
3996  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::err_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
3997  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
3998  return nullptr;
3999  }
4000 
4001  // If all of the results are known to be the same, we can silently drop the
4002  // attribute. Otherwise, we have to add the attribute and resolve its
4003  // differences later.
4004  if (AllWorkGroupSizesSame(DeclAttr->getXDim(), DeclAttr->getYDim(),
4005  DeclAttr->getZDim(), A.getXDim(), A.getYDim(),
4006  A.getZDim()))
4007  return nullptr;
4008  }
4009 
4010  return ::new (Context) SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(Context, A, A.getXDim(),
4011  A.getYDim(), A.getZDim());
4012 }
4013 
4014 static void handleSYCLReqdWorkGroupSize(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL){
4015  S.CheckDeprecatedSYCLAttributeSpelling(AL);
4016 
4017  // __attribute__((reqd_work_group_size)) and [[cl::reqd_work_group_size]]
4018  // all require exactly three arguments.
4019  if ((AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ReqdWorkGroupSize &&
4020  AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex() ==
4021  SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr::CXX11_cl_reqd_work_group_size) ||
4022  AL.getSyntax() == ParsedAttr::AS_GNU) {
4023  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 3))
4024  return;
4025  } else if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1) || !AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 3))
4026  return;
4027 
4028  size_t NumArgs = AL.getNumArgs();
4029  Expr *XDimExpr = NumArgs > 0 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(0) : nullptr;
4030  Expr *YDimExpr = NumArgs > 1 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr;
4031  Expr *ZDimExpr = NumArgs > 2 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(2) : nullptr;
4032  S.AddSYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(D, AL, XDimExpr, YDimExpr, ZDimExpr);
4033 }
4034 
4035 static void handleReqdWorkGroupSize(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4036  // Handle the attribute based on whether we are targeting SYCL or not.
4037  if (S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice || S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsHost)
4038  handleSYCLReqdWorkGroupSize(S, D, AL);
4039  else
4040  handleWorkGroupSize<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(S, D, AL);
4041 }

4043 void Sema::AddIntelReqdSubGroupSize(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
4044  Expr *E) {
4045  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
4046  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
4047  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
4048  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
4049  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
4050  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
4051  if (Res.isInvalid())
4052  return;
4053  E = Res.get();
4054 
4055  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
4056  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
4057  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
4058  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
4059  return;
4060  }
4061  auto &TI = Context.getTargetInfo();
4062  if (TI.getTriple().isNVPTX() && ArgVal != 32)
4063  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_reqd_sub_group_attribute_n)
4064  << ArgVal.getSExtValue() << TI.getTriple().getArchName() << 32;
4065  if (TI.getTriple().isAMDGPU()) {
4066  const auto HasWaveFrontSize64 =
4067  TI.getTargetOpts().FeatureMap["wavefrontsize64"];
4068  const auto HasWaveFrontSize32 =
4069  TI.getTargetOpts().FeatureMap["wavefrontsize32"];
4070 
4071  // CDNA supports only 64 wave front size, for those GPUs allow subgroup
4072  // size of 64. Some GPUs support both 32 and 64, for those (and the rest)
4073  // only allow 32. Warn on incompatible sizes.
4074  const auto SupportedWaveFrontSize =
4075  HasWaveFrontSize64 && !HasWaveFrontSize32 ? 64 : 32;
4076  if (ArgVal != SupportedWaveFrontSize)
4077  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_reqd_sub_group_attribute_n)
4078  << ArgVal.getSExtValue() << TI.getTriple().getArchName()
4079  << SupportedWaveFrontSize;
4080  }
4081 
4082  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4083  // already applied to the declaration.
4084  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4085  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
4086  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
4087  // whether this is a null pointer.
4088  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
4089  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
4090  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
4091  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4092  }
4093  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
4094  return;
4095  }
4096  }
4097  }
4098 
4099  D->addAttr(::new (Context) IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr(Context, CI, E));
4100 }

4102 IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr *
4103 Sema::MergeIntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr(Decl *D,
4104  const IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr &A) {
4105  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4106  // already applied to the declaration.
4107  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>()) {
4108  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
4109  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue())) {
4110  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
4111  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
4112  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4113  return nullptr;
4114  }
4115  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
4116  return nullptr;
4117  }
4118  }
4119  }
4120  return ::new (Context) IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
4121 }

4412 // Handles max_global_work_dim.
4413 // Returns a OneArgResult value; EqualToOne means all argument values are
4414 // equal to one, NotEqualToOne means at least one argument value is not
4415 // equal to one, and Unknown means that at least one of the argument values
4416 // could not be determined.
4417 enum class OneArgResult { Unknown, EqualToOne, NotEqualToOne };
4418 static OneArgResult AreAllArgsOne(const Expr *Args[], size_t Count) {
4419 
4420  for (size_t Idx = 0; Idx < Count; ++Idx) {
4421  const Expr *Arg = Args[Idx];
4422  // Optional arguments are considered trivially one.
4423  if (!Arg)
4424  return OneArgResult::EqualToOne;
4425  const auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Args[Idx]);
4426  if (!CE)
4427  return OneArgResult::Unknown;
4428  if (CE->getResultAsAPSInt() != 1)
4429  return OneArgResult::NotEqualToOne;
4430  }
4431  return OneArgResult::EqualToOne;
4432 }
4433 
4434 // If the declaration has a SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr or
4435 // ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if they hold equal values
4436 // (1, 1, 1). Returns true if diagnosed.
4437 template <typename AttrTy>
4438 static bool checkWorkGroupSizeAttrExpr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
4439  const AttributeCommonInfo &AL) {
4440  if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<AttrTy>()) {
4441  const Expr *Args[3] = {A->getXDim(), A->getYDim(), A->getZDim()};
4442  if (OneArgResult::NotEqualToOne == AreAllArgsOne(Args, 3)) {
4443  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::err_sycl_x_y_z_arguments_must_be_one)
4444  << A << AL;
4445  return true;
4446  }
4447  }
4448  return false;
4449 }
4450 
4451 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr(Decl *D,
4452  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
4453  Expr *E) {
4454  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
4455  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
4456  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
4457  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
4458  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
4459  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
4460  if (Res.isInvalid())
4461  return;
4462  E = Res.get();
4463 
4464  // This attribute must be in the range [0, 3].
4465  if (ArgVal < 0 || ArgVal > 3) {
4466  Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_range)
4467  << CI << 0 << 3 << E->getSourceRange();
4468  return;
4469  }
4470 
4471  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4472  // already applied to the declaration.
4473  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>()) {
4474  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
4475  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
4476  // whether this is a null pointer.
4477  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
4478  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
4479  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
4480  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4481  }
4482  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
4483  return;
4484  }
4485  }
4486 
4487  // If the declaration has a SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr or
4488  // SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if the attribute holds values
4489  // equal to (1, 1, 1) in case the value of SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr
4490  // equals to 0.
4491  if (ArgVal == 0) {
4492  if (checkWorkGroupSizeAttrExpr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>(*this, D,
4493  CI) ||
4494  checkWorkGroupSizeAttrExpr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(*this, D, CI))
4495  return;
4496  }
4497  }
4498 
4499  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr(Context, CI, E));
4500 }

4502 // Check that the value is a non-negative integer constant that can fit in
4503 // 32-bits. Issue correct error message and return false on failure.
4504 bool static check32BitInt(const Expr *E, Sema &S, llvm::APSInt &I,
4505  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
4506  if (!I.isIntN(32)) {
4507  S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_ice_too_large)
4508  << llvm::toString(I, 10, false) << 32 << /* Unsigned */ 1;
4509  return false;
4510  }
4511 
4512  if (I.isSigned() && I.isNegative()) {
4513  S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
4514  << CI << /* Non-negative */ 1;
4515  return false;
4516  }
4517 
4518  return true;
4519 }

4623 SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr *Sema::MergeSYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr(
4624  Decl *D, const SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr &A) {
4625  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4626  // already applied to the declaration.
4627  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>()) {
4628  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
4629  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue())) {
4630  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
4631  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
4632  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4633  }
4634  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
4635  return nullptr;
4636  }
4637  }
4638  }
4639 
4640  // If the declaration has a SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr or
4641  // SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr, check to see if the attribute holds values equal
4642  // to (1, 1, 1) in case the value of SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr equals to
4643  // 0.
4644  const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue());
4645  if (MergeExpr && MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() == 0) {
4646  if (checkWorkGroupSizeAttrExpr<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>(*this, D,
4647  A) ||
4648  checkWorkGroupSizeAttrExpr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(*this, D, A))
4649  return nullptr;
4650  }
4651 
4652  return ::new (Context)
4653  SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
4654 }

4708 // Handles [[intel::loop_fuse]] and [[intel::loop_fuse_independent]].
4709 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
4710  Expr *E) {
4711  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
4712  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
4713  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
4714  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
4715  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
4716  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
4717  if (Res.isInvalid())
4718  return;
4719  E = Res.get();
4720 
4721  // This attribute requires a non-negative value.
4722  if (ArgVal < 0) {
4723  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
4724  << CI << /*non-negative*/ 1;
4725  return;
4726  }
4727  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4728  // already applied to the declaration.
4729  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr>()) {
4730  // [[intel::loop_fuse]] and [[intel::loop_fuse_independent]] are
4731  // incompatible.
4732  // FIXME: If additional spellings are provided for this attribute,
4733  // this code will do the wrong thing.
4734  if (DeclAttr->getAttributeSpellingListIndex() !=
4735  CI.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()) {
4736  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
4737  << CI << DeclAttr << CI.isRegularKeywordAttribute();
4738  Diag(DeclAttr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
4739  return;
4740  }
4741  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
4742  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
4743  // whether this is a null pointer.
4744  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
4745  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
4746  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
4747  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4748  }
4749  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
4750  return;
4751  }
4752  }
4753  }
4754 
4755  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr(Context, CI, E));
4756 }

4758 SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr *
4759 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr(Decl *D, const SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr &A) {
4760  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
4761  // already applied to the declaration.
4762  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr>()) {
4763  // [[intel::loop_fuse]] and [[intel::loop_fuse_independent]] are
4764  // incompatible.
4765  // FIXME: If additional spellings are provided for this attribute,
4766  // this code will do the wrong thing.
4767  if (DeclAttr->getAttributeSpellingListIndex() !=
4768  A.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()) {
4769  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)

4771  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);

4780  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.

4783  }
4784  }

4789 static void handleSYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
4790  // If no attribute argument is specified, set to default value '1'.
4791  Expr *E = A.isArgExpr(0)
4792  ? A.getArgAsExpr(0)
4793  : IntegerLiteral::Create(S.Context, llvm::APInt(32, 1),
4794  S.Context.IntTy, A.getLoc());

4799 static void handleVecTypeHint(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4800  // This attribute is deprecated without replacement in SYCL 2020 mode.
4801  // Ignore the attribute in SYCL 2020.
4802  if (S.LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() > LangOptions::SYCL_2017) {
4803  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_deprecated_ignored) << AL;
4804  return;
4805  }
4806 
4807  // If the attribute is used with the [[sycl::vec_type_hint]] spelling in SYCL
4808  // 2017 mode, we want to warn about using the newer name in the older
4809  // standard as a compatibility extension.
4810  if (S.LangOpts.getSYCLVersion() == LangOptions::SYCL_2017 && AL.hasScope())
4811  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_sycl_2020_attr_spelling) << AL;
4812 
4813  if (!AL.hasParsedType()) {
4814  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
4815  return;
4816  }
4817 
4818  TypeSourceInfo *ParmTSI = nullptr;
4819  QualType ParmType = S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getTypeArg(), &ParmTSI);
4820  assert(ParmTSI && "no type source info for attribute argument");
4821 
4822  if (!ParmType->isExtVectorType() && !ParmType->isFloatingType() &&
4823  (ParmType->isBooleanType() ||
4824  !ParmType->isIntegralType(S.getASTContext()))) {
4825  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_invalid_argument) << 2 << AL;
4826  return;
4827  }
4828 
4829  if (VecTypeHintAttr *A = D->getAttr<VecTypeHintAttr>()) {
4830  if (!S.Context.hasSameType(A->getTypeHint(), ParmType)) {
4831  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
4832  return;
4833  }
4834  }
4835 
4836  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) VecTypeHintAttr(S.Context, AL, ParmTSI));
4837 }

4839 SectionAttr *Sema::mergeSectionAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
4840  StringRef Name) {
4841  // Explicit or partial specializations do not inherit
4842  // the section attribute from the primary template.
4843  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4844  if (CI.getAttributeSpellingListIndex() == SectionAttr::Declspec_allocate &&
4845  FD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
4846  return nullptr;
4847  }
4848  if (SectionAttr *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
4849  if (ExistingAttr->getName() == Name)
4850  return nullptr;
4851  Diag(ExistingAttr->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_section)
4852  << 1 /*section*/;
4853  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4854  return nullptr;
4855  }
4856  return ::new (Context) SectionAttr(Context, CI, Name);
4857 }
4858 
4859 /// Used to implement to perform semantic checking on
4860 /// attribute((section("foo"))) specifiers.
4861 ///
4862 /// In this case, "foo" is passed in to be checked. If the section
4863 /// specifier is invalid, return an Error that indicates the problem.
4864 ///
4865 /// This is a simple quality of implementation feature to catch errors
4866 /// and give good diagnostics in cases when the assembler or code generator
4867 /// would otherwise reject the section specifier.
4868 llvm::Error Sema::isValidSectionSpecifier(StringRef SecName) {
4869  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin())
4870  return llvm::Error::success();
4871 
4872  // Let MCSectionMachO validate this.
4873  StringRef Segment, Section;
4874  unsigned TAA, StubSize;
4875  bool HasTAA;
4876  return llvm::MCSectionMachO::ParseSectionSpecifier(SecName, Segment, Section,
4877  TAA, HasTAA, StubSize);
4878 }
4879 
4880 bool Sema::checkSectionName(SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef SecName) {
4881  if (llvm::Error E = isValidSectionSpecifier(SecName)) {
4882  Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_section_invalid_for_target)
4883  << toString(std::move(E)) << 1 /*'section'*/;
4884  return false;
4885  }
4886  return true;
4887 }
4888 
4889 static void handleSectionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4890  // Make sure that there is a string literal as the sections's single
4891  // argument.
4892  StringRef Str;
4893  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
4894  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc))
4895  return;
4896 
4897  if (!S.checkSectionName(LiteralLoc, Str))
4898  return;
4899 
4900  SectionAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeSectionAttr(D, AL, Str);
4901  if (NewAttr) {
4902  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
4903  if (isa<FunctionDecl, FunctionTemplateDecl, ObjCMethodDecl,
4904  ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))
4905  S.UnifySection(NewAttr->getName(),
4906  ASTContext::PSF_Execute | ASTContext::PSF_Read,
4907  cast<NamedDecl>(D));
4908  }
4909 }

4911 static void handleCodeModelAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4912  StringRef Str;
4913  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
4914  // Check that it is a string.
4915  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc))
4916  return;
4917 
4918  llvm::CodeModel::Model CM;
4919  if (!CodeModelAttr::ConvertStrToModel(Str, CM)) {
4920  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attr_codemodel_arg) << Str;
4921  return;
4922  }
4923 
4924  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CodeModelAttr(S.Context, AL, CM));
4925 }
