4927 // This is used for `__declspec(code_seg("segname"))` on a decl.
4928 // `#pragma code_seg("segname")` uses checkSectionName() instead.
4929 static bool checkCodeSegName(Sema &S, SourceLocation LiteralLoc,
4930  StringRef CodeSegName) {
4931  if (llvm::Error E = S.isValidSectionSpecifier(CodeSegName)) {
4932  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_section_invalid_for_target)
4933  << toString(std::move(E)) << 0 /*'code-seg'*/;
4934  return false;
4935  }
4936 
4937  return true;
4938 }
4939 
4940 CodeSegAttr *Sema::mergeCodeSegAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
4941  StringRef Name) {
4942  // Explicit or partial specializations do not inherit
4943  // the code_seg attribute from the primary template.
4944  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4945  if (FD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization())
4946  return nullptr;
4947  }
4948  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>()) {
4949  if (ExistingAttr->getName() == Name)
4950  return nullptr;
4951  Diag(ExistingAttr->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_section)
4952  << 0 /*codeseg*/;
4953  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
4954  return nullptr;
4955  }
4956  return ::new (Context) CodeSegAttr(Context, CI, Name);
4957 }
4958 
4959 static void handleCodeSegAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
4960  StringRef Str;
4961  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
4962  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc))
4963  return;
4964  if (!checkCodeSegName(S, LiteralLoc, Str))
4965  return;
4966  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>()) {
4967  if (!ExistingAttr->isImplicit()) {
4968  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
4969  ExistingAttr->getName() == Str
4970  ? diag::warn_duplicate_codeseg_attribute
4971  : diag::err_conflicting_codeseg_attribute);
4972  return;
4973  }
4974  D->dropAttr<CodeSegAttr>();
4975  }
4976  if (CodeSegAttr *CSA = S.mergeCodeSegAttr(D, AL, Str))
4977  D->addAttr(CSA);
4978 }
4979 
4980 // Check for things we'd like to warn about. Multiversioning issues are
4981 // handled later in the process, once we know how many exist.
4982 bool Sema::checkTargetAttr(SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef AttrStr) {
4983  enum FirstParam { Unsupported, Duplicate, Unknown };
4984  enum SecondParam { None, CPU, Tune };
4985  enum ThirdParam { Target, TargetClones };
4986  if (AttrStr.contains("fpmath="))
4987  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
4988  << Unsupported << None << "fpmath=" << Target;
4989 
4990  // Diagnose use of tune if target doesn't support it.
4991  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().supportsTargetAttributeTune() &&
4992  AttrStr.contains("tune="))
4993  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
4994  << Unsupported << None << "tune=" << Target;
4995 
4996  ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttrs =
4997  Context.getTargetInfo().parseTargetAttr(AttrStr);
4998 
4999  if (!ParsedAttrs.CPU.empty() &&
5000  !Context.getTargetInfo().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttrs.CPU))
5001  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5002  << Unknown << CPU << ParsedAttrs.CPU << Target;
5003 
5004  if (!ParsedAttrs.Tune.empty() &&
5005  !Context.getTargetInfo().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttrs.Tune))
5006  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5007  << Unknown << Tune << ParsedAttrs.Tune << Target;
5008 
5009  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isRISCV() &&
5010  ParsedAttrs.Duplicate != "")
5011  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_duplicate_target_attribute)
5012  << Duplicate << None << ParsedAttrs.Duplicate << Target;
5013 
5014  if (ParsedAttrs.Duplicate != "")
5015  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5016  << Duplicate << None << ParsedAttrs.Duplicate << Target;
5017 
5018  for (const auto &Feature : ParsedAttrs.Features) {
5019  auto CurFeature = StringRef(Feature).drop_front(); // remove + or -.
5020  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().isValidFeatureName(CurFeature))
5021  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5022  << Unsupported << None << CurFeature << Target;
5023  }
5024 
5025  TargetInfo::BranchProtectionInfo BPI;
5026  StringRef DiagMsg;
5027  if (ParsedAttrs.BranchProtection.empty())
5028  return false;
5029  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().validateBranchProtection(
5030  ParsedAttrs.BranchProtection, ParsedAttrs.CPU, BPI, DiagMsg)) {
5031  if (DiagMsg.empty())
5032  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5033  << Unsupported << None << "branch-protection" << Target;
5034  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_invalid_branch_protection_spec)
5035  << DiagMsg;
5036  }
5037  if (!DiagMsg.empty())
5038  Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_branch_protection_spec) << DiagMsg;
5039 
5040  return false;
5041 }
5042 
5043 static bool hasArmStreamingInterface(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
5044  if (const auto *T = FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
5045  if (T->getAArch64SMEAttributes() & FunctionType::SME_PStateSMEnabledMask)
5046  return true;
5047  return false;
5048 }
5049 
5050 // Check Target Version attrs
5051 bool Sema::checkTargetVersionAttr(SourceLocation LiteralLoc, Decl *D,
5052  StringRef &AttrStr, bool &isDefault) {
5053  enum FirstParam { Unsupported };
5054  enum SecondParam { None };
5055  enum ThirdParam { Target, TargetClones, TargetVersion };
5056  if (AttrStr.trim() == "default")
5057  isDefault = true;
5058  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 8> Features;
5059  AttrStr.split(Features, "+");
5060  for (auto &CurFeature : Features) {
5061  CurFeature = CurFeature.trim();
5062  if (CurFeature == "default")
5063  continue;
5064  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().validateCpuSupports(CurFeature))
5065  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5066  << Unsupported << None << CurFeature << TargetVersion;
5067  }
5068  if (hasArmStreamingInterface(cast<FunctionDecl>(D)))
5069  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_sme_streaming_cannot_be_multiversioned);
5070  return false;
5071 }
5072 
5073 static void handleTargetVersionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5074  StringRef Str;
5075  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
5076  bool isDefault = false;
5077  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc) ||
5078  S.checkTargetVersionAttr(LiteralLoc, D, Str, isDefault))
5079  return;
5080  // Do not create default only target_version attribute
5081  if (!isDefault) {
5082  TargetVersionAttr *NewAttr =
5083  ::new (S.Context) TargetVersionAttr(S.Context, AL, Str);
5084  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
5085  }
5086 }
5087 
5088 static void handleTargetAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5089  StringRef Str;
5090  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
5091  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &LiteralLoc) ||
5092  S.checkTargetAttr(LiteralLoc, Str))
5093  return;
5094 
5095  TargetAttr *NewAttr = ::new (S.Context) TargetAttr(S.Context, AL, Str);
5096  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
5097 }
5098 
5099 bool Sema::checkTargetClonesAttrString(
5100  SourceLocation LiteralLoc, StringRef Str, const StringLiteral *Literal,
5101  Decl *D, bool &HasDefault, bool &HasCommas, bool &HasNotDefault,
5102  SmallVectorImpl<SmallString<64>> &StringsBuffer) {
5103  enum FirstParam { Unsupported, Duplicate, Unknown };
5104  enum SecondParam { None, CPU, Tune };
5105  enum ThirdParam { Target, TargetClones };
5106  HasCommas = HasCommas || Str.contains(',');
5107  const TargetInfo &TInfo = Context.getTargetInfo();
5108  // Warn on empty at the beginning of a string.
5109  if (Str.size() == 0)
5110  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5111  << Unsupported << None << "" << TargetClones;
5112 
5113  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Parts = {{}, Str};
5114  while (!Parts.second.empty()) {
5115  Parts = Parts.second.split(',');
5116  StringRef Cur = Parts.first.trim();
5117  SourceLocation CurLoc =
5118  Literal->getLocationOfByte(Cur.data() - Literal->getString().data(),
5119  getSourceManager(), getLangOpts(), TInfo);
5120 
5121  bool DefaultIsDupe = false;
5122  bool HasCodeGenImpact = false;
5123  if (Cur.empty())
5124  return Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5125  << Unsupported << None << "" << TargetClones;
5126 
5127  if (TInfo.getTriple().isAArch64()) {
5128  // AArch64 target clones specific
5129  if (Cur == "default") {
5130  DefaultIsDupe = HasDefault;
5131  HasDefault = true;
5132  if (llvm::is_contained(StringsBuffer, Cur) || DefaultIsDupe)
5133  Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_target_clone_duplicate_options);
5134  else
5135  StringsBuffer.push_back(Cur);
5136  } else {
5137  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> CurParts = {{}, Cur};
5138  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 8> CurFeatures;
5139  while (!CurParts.second.empty()) {
5140  CurParts = CurParts.second.split('+');
5141  StringRef CurFeature = CurParts.first.trim();
5142  if (!TInfo.validateCpuSupports(CurFeature)) {
5143  Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5144  << Unsupported << None << CurFeature << TargetClones;
5145  continue;
5146  }
5147  if (TInfo.doesFeatureAffectCodeGen(CurFeature))
5148  HasCodeGenImpact = true;
5149  CurFeatures.push_back(CurFeature);
5150  }
5151  // Canonize TargetClones Attributes
5152  llvm::sort(CurFeatures);
5153  SmallString<64> Res;
5154  for (auto &CurFeat : CurFeatures) {
5155  if (!Res.equals(""))
5156  Res.append("+");
5157  Res.append(CurFeat);
5158  }
5159  if (llvm::is_contained(StringsBuffer, Res) || DefaultIsDupe)
5160  Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_target_clone_duplicate_options);
5161  else if (!HasCodeGenImpact)
5162  // Ignore features in target_clone attribute that don't impact
5163  // code generation
5164  Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_target_clone_no_impact_options);
5165  else if (!Res.empty()) {
5166  StringsBuffer.push_back(Res);
5167  HasNotDefault = true;
5168  }
5169  }
5170  if (hasArmStreamingInterface(cast<FunctionDecl>(D)))
5171  return Diag(LiteralLoc,
5172  diag::err_sme_streaming_cannot_be_multiversioned);
5173  } else {
5174  // Other targets ( currently X86 )
5175  if (Cur.starts_with("arch=")) {
5176  if (!Context.getTargetInfo().isValidCPUName(
5177  Cur.drop_front(sizeof("arch=") - 1)))
5178  return Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5179  << Unsupported << CPU << Cur.drop_front(sizeof("arch=") - 1)
5180  << TargetClones;
5181  } else if (Cur == "default") {
5182  DefaultIsDupe = HasDefault;
5183  HasDefault = true;
5184  } else if (!Context.getTargetInfo().isValidFeatureName(Cur))
5185  return Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5186  << Unsupported << None << Cur << TargetClones;
5187  if (llvm::is_contained(StringsBuffer, Cur) || DefaultIsDupe)
5188  Diag(CurLoc, diag::warn_target_clone_duplicate_options);
5189  // Note: Add even if there are duplicates, since it changes name mangling.
5190  StringsBuffer.push_back(Cur);
5191  }
5192  }
5193 
5194  if (Str.rtrim().ends_with(","))
5195  return Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unsupported_target_attribute)
5196  << Unsupported << None << "" << TargetClones;
5197  return false;
5198 }
5199 
5200 static void handleTargetClonesAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5201  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64() &&
5202  !S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("fmv"))
5203  return;
5204 
5205  // Ensure we don't combine these with themselves, since that causes some
5206  // confusing behavior.
5207  if (const auto *Other = D->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>()) {
5208  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_disallowed_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
5209  S.Diag(Other->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
5210  return;
5211  }
5212  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<TargetClonesAttr>(S, D, AL))
5213  return;
5214 
5215  SmallVector<StringRef, 2> Strings;
5216  SmallVector<SmallString<64>, 2> StringsBuffer;
5217  bool HasCommas = false, HasDefault = false, HasNotDefault = false;
5218 
5219  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
5220  StringRef CurStr;
5221  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
5222  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, CurStr, &LiteralLoc) ||
5223  S.checkTargetClonesAttrString(
5224  LiteralLoc, CurStr,
5225  cast<StringLiteral>(AL.getArgAsExpr(I)->IgnoreParenCasts()), D,
5226  HasDefault, HasCommas, HasNotDefault, StringsBuffer))
5227  return;
5228  }
5229 
5230  for (auto &SmallStr : StringsBuffer)
5231  Strings.push_back(SmallStr.str());
5232 
5233  if (HasCommas && AL.getNumArgs() > 1)
5234  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_target_clone_mixed_values);
5235 
5236  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64() && !HasDefault) {
5237  // Add default attribute if there is no one
5238  HasDefault = true;
5239  Strings.push_back("default");
5240  }
5241 
5242  if (!HasDefault) {
5243  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_target_clone_must_have_default);
5244  return;
5245  }
5246 
5247  // FIXME: We could probably figure out how to get this to work for lambdas
5248  // someday.
5249  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
5250  if (MD->getParent()->isLambda()) {
5251  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_multiversion_doesnt_support)
5252  << static_cast<unsigned>(MultiVersionKind::TargetClones)
5253  << /*Lambda*/ 9;
5254  return;
5255  }
5256  }
5257 
5258  // No multiversion if we have default version only.
5259  if (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64() && !HasNotDefault)
5260  return;
5261 
5262  cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->setIsMultiVersion();
5263  TargetClonesAttr *NewAttr = ::new (S.Context)
5264  TargetClonesAttr(S.Context, AL, Strings.data(), Strings.size());
5265  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
5266 }
5267 
5268 static void handleMinVectorWidthAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5269  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
5270  uint32_t VecWidth;
5271  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, VecWidth)) {
5272  AL.setInvalid();
5273  return;
5274  }
5275 
5276  MinVectorWidthAttr *Existing = D->getAttr<MinVectorWidthAttr>();
5277  if (Existing && Existing->getVectorWidth() != VecWidth) {
5278  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
5279  return;
5280  }
5281 
5282  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MinVectorWidthAttr(S.Context, AL, VecWidth));
5283 }
5284 
5285 static void handleCleanupAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5286  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
5287  SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
5288  FunctionDecl *FD = nullptr;
5289  DeclarationNameInfo NI;
5290 
5291  // gcc only allows for simple identifiers. Since we support more than gcc, we
5292  // will warn the user.
5293  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
5294  if (DRE->hasQualifier())
5295  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_cleanup_ext);
5296  FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
5297  NI = DRE->getNameInfo();
5298  if (!FD) {
5299  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 1
5300  << NI.getName();
5301  return;
5302  }
5303  } else if (auto *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E)) {
5304  if (ULE->hasExplicitTemplateArgs())
5305  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_cleanup_ext);
5306  FD = S.ResolveSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(ULE, true);
5307  NI = ULE->getNameInfo();
5308  if (!FD) {
5309  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 2
5310  << NI.getName();
5311  if (ULE->getType() == S.Context.OverloadTy)
5312  S.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(ULE);
5313  return;
5314  }
5315  } else {
5316  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_arg_not_function) << 0;
5317  return;
5318  }
5319 
5320  if (FD->getNumParams() != 1) {
5321  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_func_must_take_one_arg)
5322  << NI.getName();
5323  return;
5324  }
5325 
5326  // We're currently more strict than GCC about what function types we accept.
5327  // If this ever proves to be a problem it should be easy to fix.
5328  QualType Ty = S.Context.getPointerType(cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType());
5329  QualType ParamTy = FD->getParamDecl(0)->getType();
5330  if (S.CheckAssignmentConstraints(FD->getParamDecl(0)->getLocation(),
5331  ParamTy, Ty) != Sema::Compatible) {
5332  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attribute_cleanup_func_arg_incompatible_type)
5333  << NI.getName() << ParamTy << Ty;
5334  return;
5335  }
5336  VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
5337  // Create a reference to the variable declaration. This is a fake/dummy
5338  // reference.
5339  DeclRefExpr *VariableReference = DeclRefExpr::Create(
5340  S.Context, NestedNameSpecifierLoc{}, FD->getLocation(), VD, false,
5341  DeclarationNameInfo{VD->getDeclName(), VD->getLocation()}, VD->getType(),
5342  VK_LValue);
5343 
5344  // Create a unary operator expression that represents taking the address of
5345  // the variable. This is a fake/dummy expression.
5346  Expr *AddressOfVariable = UnaryOperator::Create(
5347  S.Context, VariableReference, UnaryOperatorKind::UO_AddrOf,
5348  S.Context.getPointerType(VD->getType()), VK_PRValue, OK_Ordinary, Loc,
5349  +false, FPOptionsOverride{});
5350 
5351  // Create a function call expression. This is a fake/dummy call expression.
5352  CallExpr *FunctionCallExpression =
5353  CallExpr::Create(S.Context, E, ArrayRef{AddressOfVariable},
5354  S.Context.VoidTy, VK_PRValue, Loc, FPOptionsOverride{});
5355 
5356  if (S.CheckFunctionCall(FD, FunctionCallExpression,
5357  FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())) {
5358  return;
5359  }
5360 
5361  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CleanupAttr(S.Context, AL, FD));
5362 }
5363 
5364 static void handleEnumExtensibilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
5365  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5366  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
5367  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
5368  << AL << 0 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
5369  return;
5370  }
5371 
5372  EnumExtensibilityAttr::Kind ExtensibilityKind;
5373  IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
5374  if (!EnumExtensibilityAttr::ConvertStrToKind(II->getName(),
5375  ExtensibilityKind)) {
5376  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << II;
5377  return;
5378  }
5379 
5380  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
5381  EnumExtensibilityAttr(S.Context, AL, ExtensibilityKind));
5382 }
5383 
5384 /// Handle __attribute__((format_arg((idx)))) attribute based on
5385 /// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Function-Attributes.html
5386 static void handleFormatArgAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5387  const Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
5388  ParamIdx Idx;
5389  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 1, IdxExpr, Idx))
5390  return;
5391 
5392  // Make sure the format string is really a string.
5393  QualType Ty = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
5394 
5395  bool NotNSStringTy = !isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context);
5396  if (NotNSStringTy &&
5397  !isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
5398  (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
5399  !Ty->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType())) {
5400  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
5401  << IdxExpr->getSourceRange() << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0);
5402  return;
5403  }
5404  Ty = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
5405  // replace instancetype with the class type
5406  auto Instancetype = S.Context.getObjCInstanceTypeDecl()->getTypeForDecl();
5407  if (Ty->getAs<TypedefType>() == Instancetype)
5408  if (auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
5409  if (auto *Interface = OMD->getClassInterface())
5410  Ty = S.Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(
5411  QualType(Interface->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
5412  if (!isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context, /*AllowNSAttributedString=*/true) &&
5413  !isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
5414  (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
5415  !Ty->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType())) {
5416  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_result_not)
5417  << (NotNSStringTy ? "string type" : "NSString")
5418  << IdxExpr->getSourceRange() << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0);
5419  return;
5420  }
5421 
5422  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) FormatArgAttr(S.Context, AL, Idx));
5423 }
5424 
5425 enum FormatAttrKind {
5426  CFStringFormat,
5427  NSStringFormat,
5428  StrftimeFormat,
5429  SupportedFormat,
5430  IgnoredFormat,
5431  InvalidFormat
5432 };
5433 
5434 /// getFormatAttrKind - Map from format attribute names to supported format
5435 /// types.
5436 static FormatAttrKind getFormatAttrKind(StringRef Format) {
5437  return llvm::StringSwitch<FormatAttrKind>(Format)
5438  // Check for formats that get handled specially.
5439  .Case("NSString", NSStringFormat)
5440  .Case("CFString", CFStringFormat)
5441  .Case("strftime", StrftimeFormat)
5442 
5443  // Otherwise, check for supported formats.
5444  .Cases("scanf", "printf", "printf0", "strfmon", SupportedFormat)
5445  .Cases("cmn_err", "vcmn_err", "zcmn_err", SupportedFormat)
5446  .Case("kprintf", SupportedFormat) // OpenBSD.
5447  .Case("freebsd_kprintf", SupportedFormat) // FreeBSD.
5448  .Case("os_trace", SupportedFormat)
5449  .Case("os_log", SupportedFormat)
5450 
5451  .Cases("gcc_diag", "gcc_cdiag", "gcc_cxxdiag", "gcc_tdiag", IgnoredFormat)
5452  .Default(InvalidFormat);
5453 }
5454 
5455 /// Handle __attribute__((init_priority(priority))) attributes based on
5456 /// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/C_002b_002b-Attributes.html
5457 static void handleInitPriorityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5458  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5459  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << AL;
5460  return;
5461  }
5462 
5463  if (S.getLangOpts().HLSL) {
5464  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_hlsl_init_priority_unsupported);
5465  return;
5466  }
5467 
5468  if (S.getCurFunctionOrMethodDecl()) {
5469  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_init_priority_object_attr);
5470  AL.setInvalid();
5471  return;
5472  }
5473  QualType T = cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType();
5474  if (S.Context.getAsArrayType(T))
5475  T = S.Context.getBaseElementType(T);
5476  if (!T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
5477  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_init_priority_object_attr);
5478  AL.setInvalid();
5479  return;
5480  }
5481 
5482  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
5483  uint32_t prioritynum;
5484  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, prioritynum)) {
5485  AL.setInvalid();
5486  return;
5487  }
5488 
5489  // Only perform the priority check if the attribute is outside of a system
5490  // header. Values <= 100 are reserved for the implementation, and libc++
5491  // benefits from being able to specify values in that range.
5492  if ((prioritynum < 101 || prioritynum > 65535) &&
5493  !S.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(AL.getLoc())) {
5494  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_range)
5495  << E->getSourceRange() << AL << 101 << 65535;
5496  AL.setInvalid();
5497  return;
5498  }
5499  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) InitPriorityAttr(S.Context, AL, prioritynum));
5500 }
5501 
5502 ErrorAttr *Sema::mergeErrorAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
5503  StringRef NewUserDiagnostic) {
5504  if (const auto *EA = D->getAttr<ErrorAttr>()) {
5505  std::string NewAttr = CI.getNormalizedFullName();
5506  assert((NewAttr == "error" || NewAttr == "warning") &&
5507  "unexpected normalized full name");
5508  bool Match = (EA->isError() && NewAttr == "error") ||
5509  (EA->isWarning() && NewAttr == "warning");
5510  if (!Match) {
5511  Diag(EA->getLocation(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
5512  << CI << EA
5513  << (CI.isRegularKeywordAttribute() ||
5514  EA->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
5515  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
5516  return nullptr;
5517  }
5518  if (EA->getUserDiagnostic() != NewUserDiagnostic) {
5519  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << EA;
5520  Diag(EA->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
5521  }
5522  D->dropAttr<ErrorAttr>();
5523  }
5524  return ::new (Context) ErrorAttr(Context, CI, NewUserDiagnostic);
5525 }
5526 
5527 FormatAttr *Sema::mergeFormatAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
5528  IdentifierInfo *Format, int FormatIdx,
5529  int FirstArg) {
5530  // Check whether we already have an equivalent format attribute.
5531  for (auto *F : D->specific_attrs<FormatAttr>()) {
5532  if (F->getType() == Format &&
5533  F->getFormatIdx() == FormatIdx &&
5534  F->getFirstArg() == FirstArg) {
5535  // If we don't have a valid location for this attribute, adopt the
5536  // location.
5537  if (F->getLocation().isInvalid())
5538  F->setRange(CI.getRange());
5539  return nullptr;
5540  }
5541  }
5542 
5543  return ::new (Context) FormatAttr(Context, CI, Format, FormatIdx, FirstArg);
5544 }
5545 
5546 /// Handle __attribute__((format(type,idx,firstarg))) attributes based on
5547 /// http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Function-Attributes.html
5548 static void handleFormatAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5549  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
5550  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
5551  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
5552  return;
5553  }
5554 
5555  // In C++ the implicit 'this' function parameter also counts, and they are
5556  // counted from one.
5557  bool HasImplicitThisParam = isInstanceMethod(D);
5558  unsigned NumArgs = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) + HasImplicitThisParam;
5559 
5560  IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
5561  StringRef Format = II->getName();
5562 
5563  if (normalizeName(Format)) {
5564  // If we've modified the string name, we need a new identifier for it.
5565  II = &S.Context.Idents.get(Format);
5566  }
5567 
5568  // Check for supported formats.
5569  FormatAttrKind Kind = getFormatAttrKind(Format);
5570 
5571  if (Kind == IgnoredFormat)
5572  return;
5573 
5574  if (Kind == InvalidFormat) {
5575  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
5576  << AL << II->getName();
5577  return;
5578  }
5579 
5580  // checks for the 2nd argument
5581  Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
5582  uint32_t Idx;
5583  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IdxExpr, Idx, 2))
5584  return;
5585 
5586  if (Idx < 1 || Idx > NumArgs) {
5587  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5588  << AL << 2 << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
5589  return;
5590  }
5591 
5592  // FIXME: Do we need to bounds check?
5593  unsigned ArgIdx = Idx - 1;
5594 
5595  if (HasImplicitThisParam) {
5596  if (ArgIdx == 0) {
5597  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
5598  diag::err_format_attribute_implicit_this_format_string)
5599  << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
5600  return;
5601  }
5602  ArgIdx--;
5603  }
5604 
5605  // make sure the format string is really a string
5606  QualType Ty = getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, ArgIdx);
5607 
5608  if (!isNSStringType(Ty, S.Context, true) &&
5609  !isCFStringType(Ty, S.Context) &&
5610  (!Ty->isPointerType() ||
5611  !Ty->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->isCharType())) {
5612  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_attribute_not)
5613  << IdxExpr->getSourceRange() << getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, ArgIdx);
5614  return;
5615  }
5616 
5617  // check the 3rd argument
5618  Expr *FirstArgExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(2);
5619  uint32_t FirstArg;
5620  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, FirstArgExpr, FirstArg, 3))
5621  return;
5622 
5623  // FirstArg == 0 is is always valid.
5624  if (FirstArg != 0) {
5625  if (Kind == StrftimeFormat) {
5626  // If the kind is strftime, FirstArg must be 0 because strftime does not
5627  // use any variadic arguments.
5628  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_format_strftime_third_parameter)
5629  << FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange()
5630  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange(), "0");
5631  return;
5632  } else if (isFunctionOrMethodVariadic(D)) {
5633  // Else, if the function is variadic, then FirstArg must be 0 or the
5634  // "position" of the ... parameter. It's unusual to use 0 with variadic
5635  // functions, so the fixit proposes the latter.
5636  if (FirstArg != NumArgs + 1) {
5637  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5638  << AL << 3 << FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange()
5639  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange(),
5640  std::to_string(NumArgs + 1));
5641  return;
5642  }
5643  } else {
5644  // Inescapable GCC compatibility diagnostic.
5645  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_gcc_requires_variadic_function) << AL;
5646  if (FirstArg <= Idx) {
5647  // Else, the function is not variadic, and FirstArg must be 0 or any
5648  // parameter after the format parameter. We don't offer a fixit because
5649  // there are too many possible good values.
5650  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5651  << AL << 3 << FirstArgExpr->getSourceRange();
5652  return;
5653  }
5654  }
5655  }
5656 
5657  FormatAttr *NewAttr = S.mergeFormatAttr(D, AL, II, Idx, FirstArg);
5658  if (NewAttr)
5659  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
5660 }
5661 
5662 /// Handle __attribute__((callback(CalleeIdx, PayloadIdx0, ...))) attributes.
5663 static void handleCallbackAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5664  // The index that identifies the callback callee is mandatory.
5665  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0) {
5666  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_no_callee)
5667  << AL.getRange();
5668  return;
5669  }
5670 
5671  bool HasImplicitThisParam = isInstanceMethod(D);
5672  int32_t NumArgs = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D);
5673 
5674  FunctionDecl *FD = D->getAsFunction();
5675  assert(FD && "Expected a function declaration!");
5676 
5677  llvm::StringMap<int> NameIdxMapping;
5678  NameIdxMapping["__"] = -1;
5679 
5680  NameIdxMapping["this"] = 0;
5681 
5682  int Idx = 1;
5683  for (const ParmVarDecl *PVD : FD->parameters())
5684  NameIdxMapping[PVD->getName()] = Idx++;
5685 
5686  auto UnknownName = NameIdxMapping.end();
5687 
5688  SmallVector<int, 8> EncodingIndices;
5689  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I < E; ++I) {
5690  SourceRange SR;
5691  int32_t ArgIdx;
5692 
5693  if (AL.isArgIdent(I)) {
5694  IdentifierLoc *IdLoc = AL.getArgAsIdent(I);
5695  auto It = NameIdxMapping.find(IdLoc->Ident->getName());
5696  if (It == UnknownName) {
5697  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_argument_unknown)
5698  << IdLoc->Ident << IdLoc->Loc;
5699  return;
5700  }
5701 
5702  SR = SourceRange(IdLoc->Loc);
5703  ArgIdx = It->second;
5704  } else if (AL.isArgExpr(I)) {
5705  Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(I);
5706 
5707  // If the expression is not parseable as an int32_t we have a problem.
5708  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IdxExpr, (uint32_t &)ArgIdx, I + 1,
5709  false)) {
5710  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5711  << AL << (I + 1) << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
5712  return;
5713  }
5714 
5715  // Check oob, excluding the special values, 0 and -1.
5716  if (ArgIdx < -1 || ArgIdx > NumArgs) {
5717  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
5718  << AL << (I + 1) << IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
5719  return;
5720  }
5721 
5722  SR = IdxExpr->getSourceRange();
5723  } else {
5724  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected ParsedAttr argument type!");
5725  }
5726 
5727  if (ArgIdx == 0 && !HasImplicitThisParam) {
5728  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_implicit_this_not_available)
5729  << (I + 1) << SR;
5730  return;
5731  }
5732 
5733  // Adjust for the case we do not have an implicit "this" parameter. In this
5734  // case we decrease all positive values by 1 to get LLVM argument indices.
5735  if (!HasImplicitThisParam && ArgIdx > 0)
5736  ArgIdx -= 1;
5737 
5738  EncodingIndices.push_back(ArgIdx);
5739  }
5740 
5741  int CalleeIdx = EncodingIndices.front();
5742  // Check if the callee index is proper, thus not "this" and not "unknown".
5743  // This means the "CalleeIdx" has to be non-negative if "HasImplicitThisParam"
5744  // is false and positive if "HasImplicitThisParam" is true.
5745  if (CalleeIdx < (int)HasImplicitThisParam) {
5746  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_invalid_callee)
5747  << AL.getRange();
5748  return;
5749  }
5750 
5751  // Get the callee type, note the index adjustment as the AST doesn't contain
5752  // the this type (which the callee cannot reference anyway!).
5753  const Type *CalleeType =
5754  getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, CalleeIdx - HasImplicitThisParam)
5755  .getTypePtr();
5756  if (!CalleeType || !CalleeType->isFunctionPointerType()) {
5757  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_no_function_type)
5758  << AL.getRange();
5759  return;
5760  }
5761 
5762  const Type *CalleeFnType =
5763  CalleeType->getPointeeType()->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
5764 
5765  // TODO: Check the type of the callee arguments.
5766 
5767  const auto *CalleeFnProtoType = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(CalleeFnType);
5768  if (!CalleeFnProtoType) {
5769  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_no_function_type)
5770  << AL.getRange();
5771  return;
5772  }
5773 
5774  if (CalleeFnProtoType->getNumParams() > EncodingIndices.size() - 1) {
5775  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
5776  << AL << (unsigned)(EncodingIndices.size() - 1);
5777  return;
5778  }
5779 
5780  if (CalleeFnProtoType->getNumParams() < EncodingIndices.size() - 1) {
5781  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
5782  << AL << (unsigned)(EncodingIndices.size() - 1);
5783  return;
5784  }
5785 
5786  if (CalleeFnProtoType->isVariadic()) {
5787  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_callee_is_variadic) << AL.getRange();
5788  return;
5789  }
5790 
5791  // Do not allow multiple callback attributes.
5792  if (D->hasAttr<CallbackAttr>()) {
5793  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_callback_attribute_multiple) << AL.getRange();
5794  return;
5795  }
5796 
5797  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CallbackAttr(
5798  S.Context, AL, EncodingIndices.data(), EncodingIndices.size()));
5799 }
5800 
5801 static bool isFunctionLike(const Type &T) {
5802  // Check for explicit function types.
5803  // 'called_once' is only supported in Objective-C and it has
5804  // function pointers and block pointers.
5805  return T.isFunctionPointerType() || T.isBlockPointerType();
5806 }
5807 
5808 /// Handle 'called_once' attribute.
5809 static void handleCalledOnceAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5810  // 'called_once' only applies to parameters representing functions.
5811  QualType T = cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType();
5812 
5813  if (!isFunctionLike(*T)) {
5814  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_called_once_attribute_wrong_type);
5815  return;
5816  }
5817 
5818  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CalledOnceAttr(S.Context, AL));
5819 }
5820 
5821 static void handleTransparentUnionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5822  // Try to find the underlying union declaration.
5823  RecordDecl *RD = nullptr;
5824  const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D);
5825  if (TD && TD->getUnderlyingType()->isUnionType())
5826  RD = TD->getUnderlyingType()->getAsUnionType()->getDecl();
5827  else
5828  RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D);
5829 
5830  if (!RD || !RD->isUnion()) {
5831  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
5832  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedUnion;
5833  return;
5834  }
5835 
5836  if (!RD->isCompleteDefinition()) {
5837  if (!RD->isBeingDefined())
5838  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
5839  diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_not_definition);
5840  return;
5841  }
5842 
5843  RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = RD->field_begin(),
5844  FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
5845  if (Field == FieldEnd) {
5846  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_zero_fields);
5847  return;
5848  }
5849 
5850  FieldDecl *FirstField = *Field;
5851  QualType FirstType = FirstField->getType();
5852  if (FirstType->hasFloatingRepresentation() || FirstType->isVectorType()) {
5853  S.Diag(FirstField->getLocation(),
5854  diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_floating)
5855  << FirstType->isVectorType() << FirstType;
5856  return;
5857  }
5858 
5859  if (FirstType->isIncompleteType())
5860  return;
5861  uint64_t FirstSize = S.Context.getTypeSize(FirstType);
5862  uint64_t FirstAlign = S.Context.getTypeAlign(FirstType);
5863  for (; Field != FieldEnd; ++Field) {
5864  QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
5865  if (FieldType->isIncompleteType())
5866  return;
5867  // FIXME: this isn't fully correct; we also need to test whether the
5868  // members of the union would all have the same calling convention as the
5869  // first member of the union. Checking just the size and alignment isn't
5870  // sufficient (consider structs passed on the stack instead of in registers
5871  // as an example).
5872  if (S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType) != FirstSize ||
5873  S.Context.getTypeAlign(FieldType) > FirstAlign) {
5874  // Warn if we drop the attribute.
5875  bool isSize = S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType) != FirstSize;
5876  unsigned FieldBits = isSize ? S.Context.getTypeSize(FieldType)
5877  : S.Context.getTypeAlign(FieldType);
5878  S.Diag(Field->getLocation(),
5879  diag::warn_transparent_union_attribute_field_size_align)
5880  << isSize << *Field << FieldBits;
5881  unsigned FirstBits = isSize ? FirstSize : FirstAlign;
5882  S.Diag(FirstField->getLocation(),
5883  diag::note_transparent_union_first_field_size_align)
5884  << isSize << FirstBits;
5885  return;
5886  }
5887  }
5888 
5889  RD->addAttr(::new (S.Context) TransparentUnionAttr(S.Context, AL));
5890 }
5891 
5892 void Sema::AddAnnotationAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
5893  StringRef Str, MutableArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
5894  auto *Attr = AnnotateAttr::Create(Context, Str, Args.data(), Args.size(), CI);
5895  if (ConstantFoldAttrArgs(
5896  CI, MutableArrayRef<Expr *>(Attr->args_begin(), Attr->args_end()))) {
5897  D->addAttr(Attr);
5898  }
5899 }
5900 
5901 static void handleAnnotateAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5902  // Make sure that there is a string literal as the annotation's first
5903  // argument.
5904  StringRef Str;
5905  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
5906  return;
5907 
5908  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Args;
5909  Args.reserve(AL.getNumArgs() - 1);
5910  for (unsigned Idx = 1; Idx < AL.getNumArgs(); Idx++) {
5911  assert(!AL.isArgIdent(Idx));
5912  Args.push_back(AL.getArgAsExpr(Idx));
5913  }
5914 
5915  S.AddAnnotationAttr(D, AL, Str, Args);
5916 }
5917 
5918 static void handleAlignValueAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5919  S.AddAlignValueAttr(D, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
5920 }
5921 
5922 void Sema::AddAlignValueAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI, Expr *E) {
5923  AlignValueAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, E);
5924  SourceLocation AttrLoc = CI.getLoc();
5925 
5926  QualType T;
5927  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
5928  T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
5929  else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D))
5930  T = VD->getType();
5931  else
5932  llvm_unreachable("Unknown decl type for align_value");
5933 
5934  if (!T->isDependentType() && !T->isAnyPointerType() &&
5935  !T->isReferenceType() && !T->isMemberPointerType()) {
5936  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_pointer_or_reference_only)
5937  << &TmpAttr << T << D->getSourceRange();
5938  return;
5939  }
5940 
5941  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
5942  llvm::APSInt Alignment;
5943  ExprResult ICE = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(
5944  E, &Alignment, diag::err_align_value_attribute_argument_not_int);
5945  if (ICE.isInvalid())
5946  return;
5947 
5948  if (!Alignment.isPowerOf2()) {
5949  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
5950  << E->getSourceRange();
5951  return;
5952  }
5953 
5954  D->addAttr(::new (Context) AlignValueAttr(Context, CI, ICE.get()));
5955  return;
5956  }
5957 
5958  // Save dependent expressions in the AST to be instantiated.
5959  D->addAttr(::new (Context) AlignValueAttr(Context, CI, E));
5960 }
5961 
5962 static void handleAlignedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
5963  if (AL.hasParsedType()) {
5964  const ParsedType &TypeArg = AL.getTypeArg();
5965  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo;
5966  (void)S.GetTypeFromParser(
5967  ParsedType::getFromOpaquePtr(TypeArg.getAsOpaquePtr()), &TInfo);
5968  if (AL.isPackExpansion() &&
5969  !TInfo->getType()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
5970  S.Diag(AL.getEllipsisLoc(),
5971  diag::err_pack_expansion_without_parameter_packs);
5972  return;
5973  }
5974 
5975  if (!AL.isPackExpansion() &&
5976  S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
5977  TInfo, Sema::UPPC_Expression))
5978  return;
5979 
5980  S.AddAlignedAttr(D, AL, TInfo, AL.isPackExpansion());
5981  return;
5982  }
5983 
5984  // check the attribute arguments.
5985  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
5986  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
5987  return;
5988  }
5989 
5990  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0) {
5991  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AlignedAttr(S.Context, AL, true, nullptr));
5992  return;
5993  }
5994 
5995  Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
5996  if (AL.isPackExpansion() && !E->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
5997  S.Diag(AL.getEllipsisLoc(),
5998  diag::err_pack_expansion_without_parameter_packs);
5999  return;
6000  }
6001 
6002  if (!AL.isPackExpansion() && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(E))
6003  return;
6004 
6005  S.AddAlignedAttr(D, AL, E, AL.isPackExpansion());
6006 }
6007 
6008 /// Perform checking of type validity
6009 ///
6010 /// C++11 [dcl.align]p1:
6011 /// An alignment-specifier may be applied to a variable or to a class
6012 /// data member, but it shall not be applied to a bit-field, a function
6013 /// parameter, the formal parameter of a catch clause, or a variable
6014 /// declared with the register storage class specifier. An
6015 /// alignment-specifier may also be applied to the declaration of a class
6016 /// or enumeration type.
6017 /// CWG 2354:
6018 /// CWG agreed to remove permission for alignas to be applied to
6019 /// enumerations.
6020 /// C11 6.7.5/2:
6021 /// An alignment attribute shall not be specified in a declaration of
6022 /// a typedef, or a bit-field, or a function, or a parameter, or an
6023 /// object declared with the register storage-class specifier.
6024 static bool validateAlignasAppliedType(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6025  const AlignedAttr &Attr,
6026  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
6027  int DiagKind = -1;
6028  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
6029  DiagKind = 0;
6030  } else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6031  if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register)
6032  DiagKind = 1;
6033  if (VD->isExceptionVariable())
6034  DiagKind = 2;
6035  } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
6036  if (FD->isBitField())
6037  DiagKind = 3;
6038  } else if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
6039  if (ED->getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
6040  DiagKind = 4;
6041  } else if (!isa<TagDecl>(D)) {
6042  return S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6043  << &Attr << Attr.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
6044  << (Attr.isC11() ? ExpectedVariableOrField
6045  : ExpectedVariableFieldOrTag);
6046  }
6047  if (DiagKind != -1) {
6048  return S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignas_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6049  << &Attr << DiagKind;
6050  }
6051  return false;
6052 }
6053 
6054 void Sema::AddAlignedAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI, Expr *E,
6055  bool IsPackExpansion) {
6056  AlignedAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, true, E);
6057  SourceLocation AttrLoc = CI.getLoc();
6058 
6059  // C++11 alignas(...) and C11 _Alignas(...) have additional requirements.
6060  if (TmpAttr.isAlignas() &&
6061  validateAlignasAppliedType(*this, D, TmpAttr, AttrLoc))
6062  return;
6063 
6064  if (E->isValueDependent()) {
6065  // We can't support a dependent alignment on a non-dependent type,
6066  // because we have no way to model that a type is "alignment-dependent"
6067  // but not dependent in any other way.
6068  if (const auto *TND = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
6069  if (!TND->getUnderlyingType()->isDependentType()) {
6070  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_dependent_typedef_name)
6071  << E->getSourceRange();
6072  return;
6073  }
6074  }
6075 
6076  // Save dependent expressions in the AST to be instantiated.
6077  AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(Context, CI, true, E);
6078  AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
6079  D->addAttr(AA);
6080  return;
6081  }
6082 
6083  // FIXME: Cache the number on the AL object?
6084  llvm::APSInt Alignment;
6085  ExprResult ICE = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(
6086  E, &Alignment, diag::err_aligned_attribute_argument_not_int);
6087  if (ICE.isInvalid())
6088  return;
6089 
6090  uint64_t MaximumAlignment = Sema::MaximumAlignment;
6091  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF())
6092  MaximumAlignment = std::min(MaximumAlignment, uint64_t(8192));
6093  if (Alignment > MaximumAlignment) {
6094  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_aligned_too_great)
6095  << MaximumAlignment << E->getSourceRange();
6096  return;
6097  }
6098 
6099  uint64_t AlignVal = Alignment.getZExtValue();
6100  // C++11 [dcl.align]p2:
6101  // -- if the constant expression evaluates to zero, the alignment
6102  // specifier shall have no effect
6103  // C11 6.7.5p6:
6104  // An alignment specification of zero has no effect.
6105  if (!(TmpAttr.isAlignas() && !Alignment)) {
6106  if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(AlignVal)) {
6107  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_not_power_of_two)
6108  << E->getSourceRange();
6109  return;
6110  }
6111  }
6112 
6113  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
6114  if (VD) {
6115  unsigned MaxTLSAlign =
6116  Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Context.getTargetInfo().getMaxTLSAlign())
6117  .getQuantity();
6118  if (MaxTLSAlign && AlignVal > MaxTLSAlign &&
6119  VD->getTLSKind() != VarDecl::TLS_None) {
6120  Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::err_tls_var_aligned_over_maximum)
6121  << (unsigned)AlignVal << VD << MaxTLSAlign;
6122  return;
6123  }
6124  }
6125 
6126  // On AIX, an aligned attribute can not decrease the alignment when applied
6127  // to a variable declaration with vector type.
6128  if (VD && Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSAIX()) {
6129  const Type *Ty = VD->getType().getTypePtr();
6130  if (Ty->isVectorType() && AlignVal < 16) {
6131  Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_aligned_attr_underaligned)
6132  << VD->getType() << 16;
6133  return;
6134  }
6135  }
6136 
6137  AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(Context, CI, true, ICE.get());
6138  AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
6139  AA->setCachedAlignmentValue(
6140  static_cast<unsigned>(AlignVal * Context.getCharWidth()));
6141  D->addAttr(AA);
6142 }
6143 
6144 void Sema::AddAlignedAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
6145  TypeSourceInfo *TS, bool IsPackExpansion) {
6146  AlignedAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, false, TS);
6147  SourceLocation AttrLoc = CI.getLoc();
6148 
6149  // C++11 alignas(...) and C11 _Alignas(...) have additional requirements.
6150  if (TmpAttr.isAlignas() &&
6151  validateAlignasAppliedType(*this, D, TmpAttr, AttrLoc))
6152  return;
6153 
6154  if (TS->getType()->isDependentType()) {
6155  // We can't support a dependent alignment on a non-dependent type,
6156  // because we have no way to model that a type is "type-dependent"
6157  // but not dependent in any other way.
6158  if (const auto *TND = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
6159  if (!TND->getUnderlyingType()->isDependentType()) {
6160  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_alignment_dependent_typedef_name)
6161  << TS->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
6162  return;
6163  }
6164  }
6165 
6166  AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(Context, CI, false, TS);
6167  AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
6168  D->addAttr(AA);
6169  return;
6170  }
6171 
6172  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
6173  unsigned AlignVal = TmpAttr.getAlignment(Context);
6174  // On AIX, an aligned attribute can not decrease the alignment when applied
6175  // to a variable declaration with vector type.
6176  if (VD && Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSAIX()) {
6177  const Type *Ty = VD->getType().getTypePtr();
6178  if (Ty->isVectorType() &&
6179  Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(AlignVal).getQuantity() < 16) {
6180  Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_aligned_attr_underaligned)
6181  << VD->getType() << 16;
6182  return;
6183  }
6184  }
6185 
6186  AlignedAttr *AA = ::new (Context) AlignedAttr(Context, CI, false, TS);
6187  AA->setPackExpansion(IsPackExpansion);
6188  AA->setCachedAlignmentValue(AlignVal);
6189  D->addAttr(AA);
6190 }
6191 
6192 void Sema::CheckAlignasUnderalignment(Decl *D) {
6193  assert(D->hasAttrs() && "no attributes on decl");
6194 
6195  QualType UnderlyingTy, DiagTy;
6196  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D)) {
6197  UnderlyingTy = DiagTy = VD->getType();
6198  } else {
6199  UnderlyingTy = DiagTy = Context.getTagDeclType(cast<TagDecl>(D));
6200  if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D))
6201  UnderlyingTy = ED->getIntegerType();
6202  }
6203  if (DiagTy->isDependentType() || DiagTy->isIncompleteType())
6204  return;
6205 
6206  // C++11 [dcl.align]p5, C11 6.7.5/4:
6207  // The combined effect of all alignment attributes in a declaration shall
6208  // not specify an alignment that is less strict than the alignment that
6209  // would otherwise be required for the entity being declared.
6210  AlignedAttr *AlignasAttr = nullptr;
6211  AlignedAttr *LastAlignedAttr = nullptr;
6212  unsigned Align = 0;
6213  for (auto *I : D->specific_attrs<AlignedAttr>()) {
6214  if (I->isAlignmentDependent())
6215  return;
6216  if (I->isAlignas())
6217  AlignasAttr = I;
6218  Align = std::max(Align, I->getAlignment(Context));
6219  LastAlignedAttr = I;
6220  }
6221 
6222  if (Align && DiagTy->isSizelessType()) {
6223  Diag(LastAlignedAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_sizeless_type)
6224  << LastAlignedAttr << DiagTy;
6225  } else if (AlignasAttr && Align) {
6226  CharUnits RequestedAlign = Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
6227  CharUnits NaturalAlign = Context.getTypeAlignInChars(UnderlyingTy);
6228  if (NaturalAlign > RequestedAlign)
6229  Diag(AlignasAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_alignas_underaligned)
6230  << DiagTy << (unsigned)NaturalAlign.getQuantity();
6231  }
6232 }
6233 
6234 bool Sema::checkMSInheritanceAttrOnDefinition(
6235  CXXRecordDecl *RD, SourceRange Range, bool BestCase,
6236  MSInheritanceModel ExplicitModel) {
6237  assert(RD->hasDefinition() && "RD has no definition!");
6238 
6239  // We may not have seen base specifiers or any virtual methods yet. We will
6240  // have to wait until the record is defined to catch any mismatches.
6241  if (!RD->getDefinition()->isCompleteDefinition())
6242  return false;
6243 
6244  // The unspecified model never matches what a definition could need.
6245  if (ExplicitModel == MSInheritanceModel::Unspecified)
6246  return false;
6247 
6248  if (BestCase) {
6249  if (RD->calculateInheritanceModel() == ExplicitModel)
6250  return false;
6251  } else {
6252  if (RD->calculateInheritanceModel() <= ExplicitModel)
6253  return false;
6254  }
6255 
6256  Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::err_mismatched_ms_inheritance)
6257  << 0 /*definition*/;
6258  Diag(RD->getDefinition()->getLocation(), diag::note_defined_here) << RD;
6259  return true;
6260 }
6261 
6262 /// parseModeAttrArg - Parses attribute mode string and returns parsed type
6263 /// attribute.
6264 static void parseModeAttrArg(Sema &S, StringRef Str, unsigned &DestWidth,
6265  bool &IntegerMode, bool &ComplexMode,
6266  FloatModeKind &ExplicitType) {
6267  IntegerMode = true;
6268  ComplexMode = false;
6269  ExplicitType = FloatModeKind::NoFloat;
6270  switch (Str.size()) {
6271  case 2:
6272  switch (Str[0]) {
6273  case 'Q':
6274  DestWidth = 8;
6275  break;
6276  case 'H':
6277  DestWidth = 16;
6278  break;
6279  case 'S':
6280  DestWidth = 32;
6281  break;
6282  case 'D':
6283  DestWidth = 64;
6284  break;
6285  case 'X':
6286  DestWidth = 96;
6287  break;
6288  case 'K': // KFmode - IEEE quad precision (__float128)
6289  ExplicitType = FloatModeKind::Float128;
6290  DestWidth = Str[1] == 'I' ? 0 : 128;
6291  break;
6292  case 'T':
6293  ExplicitType = FloatModeKind::LongDouble;
6294  DestWidth = 128;
6295  break;
6296  case 'I':
6297  ExplicitType = FloatModeKind::Ibm128;
6298  DestWidth = Str[1] == 'I' ? 0 : 128;
6299  break;
6300  }
6301  if (Str[1] == 'F') {
6302  IntegerMode = false;
6303  } else if (Str[1] == 'C') {
6304  IntegerMode = false;
6305  ComplexMode = true;
6306  } else if (Str[1] != 'I') {
6307  DestWidth = 0;
6308  }
6309  break;
6310  case 4:
6311  // FIXME: glibc uses 'word' to define register_t; this is narrower than a
6312  // pointer on PIC16 and other embedded platforms.
6313  if (Str == "word")
6314  DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getRegisterWidth();
6315  else if (Str == "byte")
6316  DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getCharWidth();
6317  break;
6318  case 7:
6319  if (Str == "pointer")
6320  DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default);
6321  break;
6322  case 11:
6323  if (Str == "unwind_word")
6324  DestWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getUnwindWordWidth();
6325  break;
6326  }
6327 }
6328 
6329 /// handleModeAttr - This attribute modifies the width of a decl with primitive
6330 /// type.
6331 ///
6332 /// Despite what would be logical, the mode attribute is a decl attribute, not a
6333 /// type attribute: 'int ** __attribute((mode(HI))) *G;' tries to make 'G' be
6334 /// HImode, not an intermediate pointer.
6335 static void handleModeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6336  // This attribute isn't documented, but glibc uses it. It changes
6337  // the width of an int or unsigned int to the specified size.
6338  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
6339  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6340  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
6341  return;
6342  }
6343 
6344  IdentifierInfo *Name = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
6345 
6346  S.AddModeAttr(D, AL, Name);
6347 }
6348 
6349 void Sema::AddModeAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
6350  IdentifierInfo *Name, bool InInstantiation) {
6351  StringRef Str = Name->getName();
6352  normalizeName(Str);
6353  SourceLocation AttrLoc = CI.getLoc();
6354 
6355  unsigned DestWidth = 0;
6356  bool IntegerMode = true;
6357  bool ComplexMode = false;
6358  FloatModeKind ExplicitType = FloatModeKind::NoFloat;
6359  llvm::APInt VectorSize(64, 0);
6360  if (Str.size() >= 4 && Str[0] == 'V') {
6361  // Minimal length of vector mode is 4: 'V' + NUMBER(>=1) + TYPE(>=2).
6362  size_t StrSize = Str.size();
6363  size_t VectorStringLength = 0;
6364  while ((VectorStringLength + 1) < StrSize &&
6365  isdigit(Str[VectorStringLength + 1]))
6366  ++VectorStringLength;
6367  if (VectorStringLength &&
6368  !Str.substr(1, VectorStringLength).getAsInteger(10, VectorSize) &&
6369  VectorSize.isPowerOf2()) {
6370  parseModeAttrArg(*this, Str.substr(VectorStringLength + 1), DestWidth,
6371  IntegerMode, ComplexMode, ExplicitType);
6372  // Avoid duplicate warning from template instantiation.
6373  if (!InInstantiation)
6374  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_vector_mode_deprecated);
6375  } else {
6376  VectorSize = 0;
6377  }
6378  }
6379 
6380  if (!VectorSize)
6381  parseModeAttrArg(*this, Str, DestWidth, IntegerMode, ComplexMode,
6382  ExplicitType);
6383 
6384  // FIXME: Sync this with InitializePredefinedMacros; we need to match int8_t
6385  // and friends, at least with glibc.
6386  // FIXME: Make sure floating-point mappings are accurate
6387  // FIXME: Support XF and TF types
6388  if (!DestWidth) {
6389  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_machine_mode) << 0 /*Unknown*/ << Name;
6390  return;
6391  }
6392 
6393  QualType OldTy;
6394  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
6395  OldTy = TD->getUnderlyingType();
6396  else if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
6397  // Something like 'typedef enum { X } __attribute__((mode(XX))) T;'.
6398  // Try to get type from enum declaration, default to int.
6399  OldTy = ED->getIntegerType();
6400  if (OldTy.isNull())
6401  OldTy = Context.IntTy;
6402  } else
6403  OldTy = cast<ValueDecl>(D)->getType();
6404 
6405  if (OldTy->isDependentType()) {
6406  D->addAttr(::new (Context) ModeAttr(Context, CI, Name));
6407  return;
6408  }
6409 
6410  // Base type can also be a vector type (see PR17453).
6411  // Distinguish between base type and base element type.
6412  QualType OldElemTy = OldTy;
6413  if (const auto *VT = OldTy->getAs<VectorType>())
6414  OldElemTy = VT->getElementType();
6415 
6416  // GCC allows 'mode' attribute on enumeration types (even incomplete), except
6417  // for vector modes. So, 'enum X __attribute__((mode(QI)));' forms a complete
6418  // type, 'enum { A } __attribute__((mode(V4SI)))' is rejected.
6419  if ((isa<EnumDecl>(D) || OldElemTy->getAs<EnumType>()) &&
6420  VectorSize.getBoolValue()) {
6421  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_enum_mode_vector_type) << Name << CI.getRange();
6422  return;
6423  }
6424  bool IntegralOrAnyEnumType = (OldElemTy->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
6425  !OldElemTy->isBitIntType()) ||
6426  OldElemTy->getAs<EnumType>();
6427 
6428  if (!OldElemTy->getAs<BuiltinType>() && !OldElemTy->isComplexType() &&
6429  !IntegralOrAnyEnumType)
6430  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_not_primitive);
6431  else if (IntegerMode) {
6432  if (!IntegralOrAnyEnumType)
6433  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
6434  } else if (ComplexMode) {
6435  if (!OldElemTy->isComplexType())
6436  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
6437  } else {
6438  if (!OldElemTy->isFloatingType())
6439  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
6440  }
6441 
6442  QualType NewElemTy;
6443 
6444  if (IntegerMode)
6445  NewElemTy = Context.getIntTypeForBitwidth(DestWidth,
6446  OldElemTy->isSignedIntegerType());
6447  else
6448  NewElemTy = Context.getRealTypeForBitwidth(DestWidth, ExplicitType);
6449 
6450  if (NewElemTy.isNull()) {
6451  // Only emit diagnostic on host for 128-bit mode attribute
6452  if (!(DestWidth == 128 && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice))
6453  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_machine_mode) << 1 /*Unsupported*/ << Name;
6454  return;
6455  }
6456 
6457  if (ComplexMode) {
6458  NewElemTy = Context.getComplexType(NewElemTy);
6459  }
6460 
6461  QualType NewTy = NewElemTy;
6462  if (VectorSize.getBoolValue()) {
6463  NewTy = Context.getVectorType(NewTy, VectorSize.getZExtValue(),
6464  VectorKind::Generic);
6465  } else if (const auto *OldVT = OldTy->getAs<VectorType>()) {
6466  // Complex machine mode does not support base vector types.
6467  if (ComplexMode) {
6468  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_complex_mode_vector_type);
6469  return;
6470  }
6471  unsigned NumElements = Context.getTypeSize(OldElemTy) *
6472  OldVT->getNumElements() /
6473  Context.getTypeSize(NewElemTy);
6474  NewTy =
6475  Context.getVectorType(NewElemTy, NumElements, OldVT->getVectorKind());
6476  }
6477 
6478  if (NewTy.isNull()) {
6479  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_mode_wrong_type);
6480  return;
6481  }
6482 
6483  // Install the new type.
6484  if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D))
6485  TD->setModedTypeSourceInfo(TD->getTypeSourceInfo(), NewTy);
6486  else if (auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D))
6487  ED->setIntegerType(NewTy);
6488  else
6489  cast<ValueDecl>(D)->setType(NewTy);
6490 
6491  D->addAttr(::new (Context) ModeAttr(Context, CI, Name));
6492 }
6493

6495  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoDebugAttr(S.Context, AL));

6513 InternalLinkageAttr *Sema::mergeInternalLinkageAttr(Decl *D,
6514  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6515  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6516  // Attribute applies to Var but not any subclass of it (like ParmVar,
6517  // ImplicitParm or VarTemplateSpecialization).
6518  if (VD->getKind() != Decl::Var) {
6519  Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6520  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
6521  << (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ExpectedFunctionVariableOrClass
6522  : ExpectedVariableOrFunction);
6523  return nullptr;
6524  }
6525  // Attribute does not apply to non-static local variables.
6526  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
6527  Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_internal_linkage_local_storage);
6528  return nullptr;
6529  }
6530  }
6531 
6532  return ::new (Context) InternalLinkageAttr(Context, AL);
6533 }

6538  // ImplicitParm or VarTemplateSpecialization).
6539  if (VD->getKind() != Decl::Var) {
6540  Diag(AL.getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6541  << &AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
6542  << (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? ExpectedFunctionVariableOrClass
6543  : ExpectedVariableOrFunction);
6544  return nullptr;

6546  // Attribute does not apply to non-static local variables.

6548  Diag(VD->getLocation(), diag::warn_internal_linkage_local_storage);

6656 static void handleSYCLGlobalVarAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6657  if (!S.Context.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(D->getLocation())) {
6658  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_only_system_header) << AL;

6661 
6662  handleSimpleAttribute<SYCLGlobalVarAttr>(S, D, AL);
6663 }
6664 
6665 static void handleSYCLRegisterNumAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6666  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
6667  return;
6668  uint32_t RegNo = 0;
6669  const Expr *E = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
6670  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, E, RegNo, 0, /*StrictlyUnsigned=*/true))
6671  return;
6672  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SYCLRegisterNumAttr(S.Context, AL, RegNo));
6673 }
6674 
6675 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(Decl *D,
6676  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
6677  Expr *E) {
6678  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
6679  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
6680  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
6681  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
6682  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
6683  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
6684  if (Res.isInvalid())
6685  return;
6686  E = Res.get();
6687 
6688  if (ArgVal != 8 && ArgVal != 16 && ArgVal != 32) {
6689  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sycl_esimd_vectorize_unsupported_value)
6690  << CI;
6691  return;
6692  }
6693 
6694  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
6695  // already applied to the declaration.
6696  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr>()) {
6697  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
6698  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
6699  // whether this is a null pointer.
6700  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
6701  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
6702  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
6703  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
6704  }
6705  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
6706  return;
6707  }
6708  }
6709  }
6710 
6711  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(Context, CI, E));
6712 }
6713 
6714 SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr *
6715 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(Decl *D,
6716  const SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr &A) {
6717  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
6718  // already applied to the declaration.
6719  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr>()) {
6720  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
6721  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue())) {
6722  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
6723  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
6724  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
6725  }
6726  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
6727  return nullptr;
6728  }
6729  }
6730  }
6731  return ::new (Context) SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
6732 }
6733 
6734 static void handleSYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
6735  const ParsedAttr &A) {
6736  S.CheckDeprecatedSYCLAttributeSpelling(A);
6737 
6738  Expr *E = A.getArgAsExpr(0);
6739  S.AddSYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(D, A, E);
6740 }
6741 
6742 static void handleConstantAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6743  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
6744  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
6745  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_nonstatic_constdev);
6746  return;
6747  }
6748  // constexpr variable may already get an implicit constant attr, which should
6749  // be replaced by the explicit constant attr.
6750  if (auto *A = D->getAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>()) {
6751  if (!A->isImplicit())
6752  return;
6753  D->dropAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>();
6754  }
6755  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDAConstantAttr(S.Context, AL));
6756 }
6757 
6758 static void handleSharedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6759  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
6760  // extern __shared__ is only allowed on arrays with no length (e.g.
6761  // "int x[]").
6762  if (!S.getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode && VD->hasExternalStorage() &&
6763  !isa<IncompleteArrayType>(VD->getType())) {
6764  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_extern_shared) << VD;
6765  return;
6766  }
6767  if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA && VD->hasLocalStorage() &&
6768  S.CUDA().DiagIfHostCode(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_host_shared)
6769  << llvm::to_underlying(S.CUDA().CurrentTarget()))
6770  return;
6771  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDASharedAttr(S.Context, AL));
6772 }
6773 
6774 static void handleGlobalAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6775  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
6776  if (!FD->getReturnType()->isVoidType() &&
6777  !FD->getReturnType()->getAs<AutoType>() &&
6778  !FD->getReturnType()->isInstantiationDependentType()) {
6779  SourceRange RTRange = FD->getReturnTypeSourceRange();
6780  S.Diag(FD->getTypeSpecStartLoc(), diag::err_kern_type_not_void_return)
6781  << FD->getType()
6782  << (RTRange.isValid() ? FixItHint::CreateReplacement(RTRange, "void")
6783  : FixItHint());
6784  return;
6785  }
6786  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
6787  if (Method->isInstance()) {
6788  S.Diag(Method->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_kern_is_nonstatic_method)
6789  << Method;
6790  return;
6791  }
6792  S.Diag(Method->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_kern_is_method) << Method;
6793  }
6794  // Only warn for "inline" when compiling for host, to cut down on noise.
6795  if (FD->isInlineSpecified() && !S.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
6796  S.Diag(FD->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_kern_is_inline) << FD;
6797 
6798  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NVPTXKernel)
6799  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NVPTXKernelAttr(S.Context, AL));
6800  else
6801  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDAGlobalAttr(S.Context, AL));
6802  // In host compilation the kernel is emitted as a stub function, which is
6803  // a helper function for launching the kernel. The instructions in the helper
6804  // function has nothing to do with the source code of the kernel. Do not emit
6805  // debug info for the stub function to avoid confusing the debugger.
6806  if (S.LangOpts.HIP && !S.LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
6807  D->addAttr(NoDebugAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
6808 }
6809 
6810 static void handleDeviceAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6811  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6812  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
6813  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_nonstatic_constdev);
6814  return;
6815  }
6816  }
6817 
6818  if (auto *A = D->getAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
6819  if (!A->isImplicit())
6820  return;
6821  D->dropAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>();
6822  }
6823  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CUDADeviceAttr(S.Context, AL));
6824 }
6825 
6826 static void handleManagedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6827  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6828  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
6829  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_cuda_nonstatic_constdev);
6830  return;
6831  }
6832  }
6833  if (!D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>())
6834  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) HIPManagedAttr(S.Context, AL));
6835  if (!D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
6836  D->addAttr(CUDADeviceAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
6837 }
