6839 static void handleGNUInlineAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6840  const auto *Fn = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
6841  if (!Fn->isInlineSpecified()) {
6842  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_gnu_inline_attribute_requires_inline);
6843  return;
6844  }
6845 
6846  if (S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus && Fn->getStorageClass() != SC_Extern)
6847  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_gnu_inline_cplusplus_without_extern);
6848 
6849  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) GNUInlineAttr(S.Context, AL));
6850 }
6851 
6852 static void handleCallConvAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6853  if (hasDeclarator(D)) return;
6854 
6855  // Diagnostic is emitted elsewhere: here we store the (valid) AL
6856  // in the Decl node for syntactic reasoning, e.g., pretty-printing.
6857  CallingConv CC;
6858  if (S.CheckCallingConvAttr(
6859  AL, CC, /*FD*/ nullptr,
6860  S.CUDA().IdentifyTarget(dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))))
6861  return;
6862 
6863  if (!isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
6864  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
6865  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
6866  return;
6867  }
6868 
6869  switch (AL.getKind()) {
6870  case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall:
6871  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) FastCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6872  return;
6873  case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall:
6874  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) StdCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6875  return;
6876  case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall:
6877  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ThisCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6878  return;
6879  case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl:
6880  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CDeclAttr(S.Context, AL));
6881  return;
6882  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal:
6883  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PascalAttr(S.Context, AL));
6884  return;
6885  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall:
6886  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6887  return;
6888  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftAsyncCall:
6889  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftAsyncCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6890  return;
6891  case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall:
6892  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) VectorCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6893  return;
6894  case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI:
6895  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MSABIAttr(S.Context, AL));
6896  return;
6897  case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI:
6898  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SysVABIAttr(S.Context, AL));
6899  return;
6900  case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall:
6901  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RegCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6902  return;
6903  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: {
6904  PcsAttr::PCSType PCS;
6905  switch (CC) {
6906  case CC_AAPCS:
6907  PCS = PcsAttr::AAPCS;
6908  break;
6909  case CC_AAPCS_VFP:
6910  PCS = PcsAttr::AAPCS_VFP;
6911  break;
6912  default:
6913  llvm_unreachable("unexpected calling convention in pcs attribute");
6914  }
6915 
6916  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PcsAttr(S.Context, AL, PCS));
6917  return;
6918  }
6919  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs:
6920  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AArch64VectorPcsAttr(S.Context, AL));
6921  return;
6922  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64SVEPcs:
6923  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AArch64SVEPcsAttr(S.Context, AL));
6924  return;
6925  case ParsedAttr::AT_AMDGPUKernelCall:
6926  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AMDGPUKernelCallAttr(S.Context, AL));
6927  return;
6928  case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc:
6929  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) IntelOclBiccAttr(S.Context, AL));
6930  return;
6931  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost:
6932  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreserveMostAttr(S.Context, AL));
6933  return;
6934  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll:
6935  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreserveAllAttr(S.Context, AL));
6936  return;
6937  case ParsedAttr::AT_M68kRTD:
6938  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) M68kRTDAttr(S.Context, AL));
6939  return;
6940  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveNone:
6941  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreserveNoneAttr(S.Context, AL));
6942  return;
6943  case ParsedAttr::AT_RISCVVectorCC:
6944  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RISCVVectorCCAttr(S.Context, AL));
6945  return;
6946  default:
6947  llvm_unreachable("unexpected attribute kind");
6948  }
6949 }
6950 
6951 static void handleSuppressAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6952  if (AL.getAttributeSpellingListIndex() == SuppressAttr::CXX11_gsl_suppress) {
6953  // Suppression attribute with GSL spelling requires at least 1 argument.
6954  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
6955  return;
6956  }
6957 
6958  std::vector<StringRef> DiagnosticIdentifiers;
6959  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
6960  StringRef RuleName;
6961 
6962  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, RuleName, nullptr))
6963  return;
6964 
6965  DiagnosticIdentifiers.push_back(RuleName);
6966  }
6967  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
6968  SuppressAttr(S.Context, AL, DiagnosticIdentifiers.data(),
6969  DiagnosticIdentifiers.size()));
6970 }
6971 
6972 static void handleLifetimeCategoryAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
6973  TypeSourceInfo *DerefTypeLoc = nullptr;
6974  QualType ParmType;
6975  if (AL.hasParsedType()) {
6976  ParmType = S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getTypeArg(), &DerefTypeLoc);
6977 
6978  unsigned SelectIdx = ~0U;
6979  if (ParmType->isReferenceType())
6980  SelectIdx = 0;
6981  else if (ParmType->isArrayType())
6982  SelectIdx = 1;
6983 
6984  if (SelectIdx != ~0U) {
6985  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_invalid_argument)
6986  << SelectIdx << AL;
6987  return;
6988  }
6989  }
6990 
6991  // To check if earlier decl attributes do not conflict the newly parsed ones
6992  // we always add (and check) the attribute to the canonical decl. We need
6993  // to repeat the check for attribute mutual exclusion because we're attaching
6994  // all of the attributes to the canonical declaration rather than the current
6995  // declaration.
6996  D = D->getCanonicalDecl();
6997  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Owner) {
6998  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<PointerAttr>(S, D, AL))
6999  return;
7000  if (const auto *OAttr = D->getAttr<OwnerAttr>()) {
7001  const Type *ExistingDerefType = OAttr->getDerefTypeLoc()
7002  ? OAttr->getDerefType().getTypePtr()
7003  : nullptr;
7004  if (ExistingDerefType != ParmType.getTypePtrOrNull()) {
7005  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7006  << AL << OAttr
7007  << (AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() ||
7008  OAttr->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
7009  S.Diag(OAttr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
7010  }
7011  return;
7012  }
7013  for (Decl *Redecl : D->redecls()) {
7014  Redecl->addAttr(::new (S.Context) OwnerAttr(S.Context, AL, DerefTypeLoc));
7015  }
7016  } else {
7017  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<OwnerAttr>(S, D, AL))
7018  return;
7019  if (const auto *PAttr = D->getAttr<PointerAttr>()) {
7020  const Type *ExistingDerefType = PAttr->getDerefTypeLoc()
7021  ? PAttr->getDerefType().getTypePtr()
7022  : nullptr;
7023  if (ExistingDerefType != ParmType.getTypePtrOrNull()) {
7024  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7025  << AL << PAttr
7026  << (AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() ||
7027  PAttr->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
7028  S.Diag(PAttr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
7029  }
7030  return;
7031  }
7032  for (Decl *Redecl : D->redecls()) {
7033  Redecl->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
7034  PointerAttr(S.Context, AL, DerefTypeLoc));
7035  }
7036  }
7037 }
7038 
7039 static void handleRandomizeLayoutAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7040  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<NoRandomizeLayoutAttr>(S, D, AL))
7041  return;
7042  if (!D->hasAttr<RandomizeLayoutAttr>())
7043  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RandomizeLayoutAttr(S.Context, AL));
7044 }
7045 
7046 static void handleNoRandomizeLayoutAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7047  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7048  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<RandomizeLayoutAttr>(S, D, AL))
7049  return;
7050  if (!D->hasAttr<NoRandomizeLayoutAttr>())
7051  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoRandomizeLayoutAttr(S.Context, AL));
7052 }
7053 
7054 bool Sema::CheckCallingConvAttr(const ParsedAttr &Attrs, CallingConv &CC,
7055  const FunctionDecl *FD,
7056  CUDAFunctionTarget CFT) {
7057  if (Attrs.isInvalid())
7058  return true;
7059 
7060  if (Attrs.hasProcessingCache()) {
7061  CC = (CallingConv) Attrs.getProcessingCache();
7062  return false;
7063  }
7064 
7065  unsigned ReqArgs = Attrs.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs ? 1 : 0;
7066  if (!Attrs.checkExactlyNumArgs(*this, ReqArgs)) {
7067  Attrs.setInvalid();
7068  return true;
7069  }
7070 
7071  const TargetInfo &TI = Context.getTargetInfo();
7072  // TODO: diagnose uses of these conventions on the wrong target.
7073  switch (Attrs.getKind()) {
7074  case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl:
7075  CC = TI.getDefaultCallingConv();
7076  break;
7077  case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall:
7078  CC = CC_X86FastCall;
7079  break;
7080  case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall:
7081  CC = CC_X86StdCall;
7082  break;
7083  case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall:
7084  CC = CC_X86ThisCall;
7085  break;
7086  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal:
7087  CC = CC_X86Pascal;
7088  break;
7089  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall:
7090  CC = CC_Swift;
7091  break;
7092  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftAsyncCall:
7093  CC = CC_SwiftAsync;
7094  break;
7095  case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall:
7096  CC = CC_X86VectorCall;
7097  break;
7098  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs:
7099  CC = CC_AArch64VectorCall;
7100  break;
7101  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64SVEPcs:
7102  CC = CC_AArch64SVEPCS;
7103  break;
7104  case ParsedAttr::AT_AMDGPUKernelCall:
7105  CC = CC_AMDGPUKernelCall;
7106  break;
7107  case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall:
7108  CC = CC_X86RegCall;
7109  break;
7110  case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI:
7111  CC = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows() ? CC_C :
7112  CC_Win64;
7113  break;
7114  case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI:
7115  CC = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSWindows() ? CC_X86_64SysV :
7116  CC_C;
7117  break;
7118  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: {
7119  StringRef StrRef;
7120  if (!checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(Attrs, 0, StrRef)) {
7121  Attrs.setInvalid();
7122  return true;
7123  }
7124  if (StrRef == "aapcs") {
7125  CC = CC_AAPCS;
7126  break;
7127  } else if (StrRef == "aapcs-vfp") {
7128  CC = CC_AAPCS_VFP;
7129  break;
7130  }
7131 
7132  Attrs.setInvalid();
7133  Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::err_invalid_pcs);
7134  return true;
7135  }
7136  case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc:
7137  CC = CC_IntelOclBicc;
7138  break;
7139  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost:
7140  CC = CC_PreserveMost;
7141  break;
7142  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll:
7143  CC = CC_PreserveAll;
7144  break;
7145  case ParsedAttr::AT_M68kRTD:
7146  CC = CC_M68kRTD;
7147  break;
7148  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveNone:
7149  CC = CC_PreserveNone;
7150  break;
7151  case ParsedAttr::AT_RISCVVectorCC:
7152  CC = CC_RISCVVectorCall;
7153  break;
7154  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected attribute kind");
7155  }
7156 
7157  TargetInfo::CallingConvCheckResult A = TargetInfo::CCCR_OK;
7158  // CUDA functions may have host and/or device attributes which indicate
7159  // their targeted execution environment, therefore the calling convention
7160  // of functions in CUDA should be checked against the target deduced based
7161  // on their host/device attributes.
7162  if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
7163  auto *Aux = Context.getAuxTargetInfo();
7164  assert(FD || CFT != CUDAFunctionTarget::InvalidTarget);
7165  auto CudaTarget = FD ? CUDA().IdentifyTarget(FD) : CFT;
7166  bool CheckHost = false, CheckDevice = false;
7167  switch (CudaTarget) {
7168  case CUDAFunctionTarget::HostDevice:
7169  CheckHost = true;
7170  CheckDevice = true;
7171  break;
7172  case CUDAFunctionTarget::Host:
7173  CheckHost = true;
7174  break;
7175  case CUDAFunctionTarget::Device:
7176  case CUDAFunctionTarget::Global:
7177  CheckDevice = true;
7178  break;
7179  case CUDAFunctionTarget::InvalidTarget:
7180  llvm_unreachable("unexpected cuda target");
7181  }
7182  auto *HostTI = LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice ? Aux : &TI;
7183  auto *DeviceTI = LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice ? &TI : Aux;
7184  if (CheckHost && HostTI)
7185  A = HostTI->checkCallingConvention(CC);
7186  if (A == TargetInfo::CCCR_OK && CheckDevice && DeviceTI)
7187  A = DeviceTI->checkCallingConvention(CC);
7188  } else {
7189  A = TI.checkCallingConvention(CC);
7190  }
7191 
7192  switch (A) {
7193  case TargetInfo::CCCR_OK:
7194  break;
7195 
7196  case TargetInfo::CCCR_Ignore:
7197  // Treat an ignored convention as if it was an explicit C calling convention
7198  // attribute. For example, __stdcall on Win x64 functions as __cdecl, so
7199  // that command line flags that change the default convention to
7200  // __vectorcall don't affect declarations marked __stdcall.
7201  CC = CC_C;
7202  break;
7203 
7204  case TargetInfo::CCCR_Error:
7205  Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::error_cconv_unsupported)
7206  << Attrs << (int)CallingConventionIgnoredReason::ForThisTarget;
7207  break;
7208 
7209  case TargetInfo::CCCR_Warning: {
7210  Diag(Attrs.getLoc(), diag::warn_cconv_unsupported)
7211  << Attrs << (int)CallingConventionIgnoredReason::ForThisTarget;
7212 
7213  // This convention is not valid for the target. Use the default function or
7214  // method calling convention.
7215  bool IsCXXMethod = false, IsVariadic = false;
7216  if (FD) {
7217  IsCXXMethod = FD->isCXXInstanceMember();
7218  IsVariadic = FD->isVariadic();
7219  }
7220  CC = Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(IsVariadic, IsCXXMethod);
7221  break;
7222  }
7223  }
7224 
7225  Attrs.setProcessingCache((unsigned) CC);
7226  return false;
7227 }
7228 
7229 /// Pointer-like types in the default address space.
7230 static bool isValidSwiftContextType(QualType Ty) {
7231  if (!Ty->hasPointerRepresentation())
7232  return Ty->isDependentType();
7233  return Ty->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default;
7234 }
7235 
7236 /// Pointers and references in the default address space.
7237 static bool isValidSwiftIndirectResultType(QualType Ty) {
7238  if (const auto *PtrType = Ty->getAs<PointerType>()) {
7239  Ty = PtrType->getPointeeType();
7240  } else if (const auto *RefType = Ty->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
7241  Ty = RefType->getPointeeType();
7242  } else {
7243  return Ty->isDependentType();
7244  }
7245  return Ty.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default;
7246 }
7247 
7248 /// Pointers and references to pointers in the default address space.
7249 static bool isValidSwiftErrorResultType(QualType Ty) {
7250  if (const auto *PtrType = Ty->getAs<PointerType>()) {
7251  Ty = PtrType->getPointeeType();
7252  } else if (const auto *RefType = Ty->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
7253  Ty = RefType->getPointeeType();
7254  } else {
7255  return Ty->isDependentType();
7256  }
7257  if (!Ty.getQualifiers().empty())
7258  return false;
7259  return isValidSwiftContextType(Ty);
7260 }
7261 
7262 void Sema::AddParameterABIAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
7263  ParameterABI abi) {
7264 
7265  QualType type = cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType();
7266 
7267  if (auto existingAttr = D->getAttr<ParameterABIAttr>()) {
7268  if (existingAttr->getABI() != abi) {
7269  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7270  << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << existingAttr
7271  << (CI.isRegularKeywordAttribute() ||
7272  existingAttr->isRegularKeywordAttribute());
7273  Diag(existingAttr->getLocation(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
7274  return;
7275  }
7276  }
7277 
7278  switch (abi) {
7279  case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
7280  llvm_unreachable("explicit attribute for ordinary parameter ABI?");
7281 
7282  case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
7283  if (!isValidSwiftContextType(type)) {
7284  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
7285  << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << /*pointer to pointer */ 0 << type;
7286  }
7287  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SwiftContextAttr(Context, CI));
7288  return;
7289 
7290  case ParameterABI::SwiftAsyncContext:
7291  if (!isValidSwiftContextType(type)) {
7292  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
7293  << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << /*pointer to pointer */ 0 << type;
7294  }
7295  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SwiftAsyncContextAttr(Context, CI));
7296  return;
7297 
7298  case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
7299  if (!isValidSwiftErrorResultType(type)) {
7300  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
7301  << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << /*pointer to pointer */ 1 << type;
7302  }
7303  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SwiftErrorResultAttr(Context, CI));
7304  return;
7305 
7306  case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
7307  if (!isValidSwiftIndirectResultType(type)) {
7308  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_swift_abi_parameter_wrong_type)
7309  << getParameterABISpelling(abi) << /*pointer*/ 0 << type;
7310  }
7311  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SwiftIndirectResultAttr(Context, CI));
7312  return;
7313  }
7314  llvm_unreachable("bad parameter ABI attribute");
7315 }
7316 
7317 /// Checks a regparm attribute, returning true if it is ill-formed and
7318 /// otherwise setting numParams to the appropriate value.
7319 bool Sema::CheckRegparmAttr(const ParsedAttr &AL, unsigned &numParams) {
7320  if (AL.isInvalid())
7321  return true;
7322 
7323  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(*this, 1)) {
7324  AL.setInvalid();
7325  return true;
7326  }
7327 
7328  uint32_t NP;
7329  Expr *NumParamsExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
7330  if (!checkUInt32Argument(*this, AL, NumParamsExpr, NP)) {
7331  AL.setInvalid();
7332  return true;
7333  }
7334 
7335  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax() == 0) {
7336  Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_regparm_wrong_platform)
7337  << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
7338  AL.setInvalid();
7339  return true;
7340  }
7341 
7342  numParams = NP;
7343  if (numParams > Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax()) {
7344  Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_regparm_invalid_number)
7345  << Context.getTargetInfo().getRegParmMax() << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
7346  AL.setInvalid();
7347  return true;
7348  }
7349 
7350  return false;
7351 }
7352 
7353 // Checks whether an argument of launch_bounds attribute is
7354 // acceptable, performs implicit conversion to Rvalue, and returns
7355 // non-nullptr Expr result on success. Otherwise, it returns nullptr
7356 // and may output an error.
7357 static Expr *makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(Sema &S, Expr *E,
7358  const CUDALaunchBoundsAttr &AL,
7359  const unsigned Idx) {
7360  if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(E))
7361  return nullptr;
7362 
7363  // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
7364  // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
7365  if (E->isValueDependent())
7366  return E;
7367 
7368  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> I = llvm::APSInt(64);
7369  if (!(I = E->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
7370  S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
7371  << &AL << Idx << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << E->getSourceRange();
7372  return nullptr;
7373  }
7374  // Make sure we can fit it in 32 bits.
7375  if (!I->isIntN(32)) {
7376  S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_ice_too_large)
7377  << toString(*I, 10, false) << 32 << /* Unsigned */ 1;
7378  return nullptr;
7379  }
7380  if (*I < 0)
7381  S.Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_argument_n_negative)
7382  << &AL << Idx << E->getSourceRange();
7383 
7384  // We may need to perform implicit conversion of the argument.
7385  InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(
7386  S.Context, S.Context.getConstType(S.Context.IntTy), /*consume*/ false);
7387  ExprResult ValArg = S.PerformCopyInitialization(Entity, SourceLocation(), E);
7388  assert(!ValArg.isInvalid() &&
7389  "Unexpected PerformCopyInitialization() failure.");
7390 
7391  return ValArg.getAs<Expr>();
7392 }
7393 
7394 CUDALaunchBoundsAttr *
7395 Sema::CreateLaunchBoundsAttr(const AttributeCommonInfo &CI, Expr *MaxThreads,
7396  Expr *MinBlocks, Expr *MaxBlocks) {
7397  CUDALaunchBoundsAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, MaxThreads, MinBlocks, MaxBlocks);
7398  MaxThreads = makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(*this, MaxThreads, TmpAttr, 0);
7399  if (!MaxThreads)
7400  return nullptr;
7401 
7402  if (MinBlocks) {
7403  MinBlocks = makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(*this, MinBlocks, TmpAttr, 1);
7404  if (!MinBlocks)
7405  return nullptr;
7406  }
7407 
7408  if (MaxBlocks) {
7409  // '.maxclusterrank' ptx directive requires .target sm_90 or higher.
7410  auto SM = getCudaArch(Context.getTargetInfo());
7411  if (SM == CudaArch::UNKNOWN || SM < CudaArch::SM_90) {
7412  Diag(MaxBlocks->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cuda_maxclusterrank_sm_90)
7413  << CudaArchToString(SM) << CI << MaxBlocks->getSourceRange();
7414  // Ignore it by setting MaxBlocks to null;
7415  MaxBlocks = nullptr;
7416  } else {
7417  MaxBlocks = makeLaunchBoundsArgExpr(*this, MaxBlocks, TmpAttr, 2);
7418  if (!MaxBlocks)
7419  return nullptr;
7420  }
7421  }
7422 
7423  return ::new (Context)
7424  CUDALaunchBoundsAttr(Context, CI, MaxThreads, MinBlocks, MaxBlocks);
7425 }
7426 
7427 void Sema::AddLaunchBoundsAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
7428  Expr *MaxThreads, Expr *MinBlocks,
7429  Expr *MaxBlocks) {
7430  if (auto *Attr = CreateLaunchBoundsAttr(CI, MaxThreads, MinBlocks, MaxBlocks))
7431  D->addAttr(Attr);
7432 }
7433 
7434 static void handleLaunchBoundsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7435  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1) || !AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 3))
7436  return;
7437 
7438  S.AddLaunchBoundsAttr(D, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
7439  AL.getNumArgs() > 1 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(1) : nullptr,
7440  AL.getNumArgs() > 2 ? AL.getArgAsExpr(2) : nullptr);
7441 }
7442 
7443 static void handleArgumentWithTypeTagAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7444  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7445  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
7446  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
7447  << AL << /* arg num = */ 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
7448  return;
7449  }
7450 
7451  ParamIdx ArgumentIdx;
7452  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 2, AL.getArgAsExpr(1),
7453  ArgumentIdx))
7454  return;
7455 
7456  ParamIdx TypeTagIdx;
7457  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 3, AL.getArgAsExpr(2),
7458  TypeTagIdx))
7459  return;
7460 
7461  bool IsPointer = AL.getAttrName()->getName() == "pointer_with_type_tag";
7462  if (IsPointer) {
7463  // Ensure that buffer has a pointer type.
7464  unsigned ArgumentIdxAST = ArgumentIdx.getASTIndex();
7465  if (ArgumentIdxAST >= getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) ||
7466  !getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, ArgumentIdxAST)->isPointerType())
7467  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_pointers_only) << AL << 0;
7468  }
7469 
7470  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ArgumentWithTypeTagAttr(
7471  S.Context, AL, AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident, ArgumentIdx, TypeTagIdx,
7472  IsPointer));
7473 }
7474 
7475 static void handleTypeTagForDatatypeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7476  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7477  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
7478  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
7479  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
7480  return;
7481  }
7482 
7483  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
7484  return;
7485 
7486  if (!isa<VarDecl>(D)) {
7487  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
7488  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedVariable;
7489  return;
7490  }
7491 
7492  IdentifierInfo *PointerKind = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
7493  TypeSourceInfo *MatchingCTypeLoc = nullptr;
7494  S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getMatchingCType(), &MatchingCTypeLoc);
7495  assert(MatchingCTypeLoc && "no type source info for attribute argument");
7496 
7497  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) TypeTagForDatatypeAttr(
7498  S.Context, AL, PointerKind, MatchingCTypeLoc, AL.getLayoutCompatible(),
7499  AL.getMustBeNull()));
7500 }
7501 
7502 /// Give a warning for duplicate attributes, return true if duplicate.
7503 template <typename AttrType>
7504 static bool checkForDuplicateAttribute(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7505  const ParsedAttr &Attr) {
7506  // Give a warning for duplicates but not if it's one we've implicitly added.
7507  auto *A = D->getAttr<AttrType>();
7508  if (A && !A->isImplicit()) {
7509  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute_exact) << A;
7510  return true;
7511  }
7512  return false;
7513 }
7514 
7515 // Checks if FPGA memory attributes apply on valid variables.
7516 // Returns true if an error occured.
7517 static bool CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(Sema &S, Decl *D) {
7518  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
7519  if (!(isa<FieldDecl>(D) ||
7520  (VD->getKind() != Decl::ImplicitParam &&
7521  VD->getKind() != Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm &&
7522  (S.SYCL().isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
7523  VD->getType()) ||
7524  VD->getType().isConstQualified() ||
7525  VD->getType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_constant ||
7526  VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Static || VD->hasLocalStorage())))) {
7527  return true;
7528  }
7529  }
7530  return false;
7531 }
7532 
7533 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(Decl *D,
7534  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
7535  Expr *E) {
7536  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
7537  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
7538  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
7539  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
7540  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
7541  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
7542  if (Res.isInvalid())
7543  return;
7544  E = Res.get();
7545 
7546  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7547  // already applied to the declaration.
7548  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr>()) {
7549  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
7550  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
7551  // whether this is a null pointer.
7552  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
7553  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7554  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
7555  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7556  }
7557  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
7558  return;
7559  }
7560  }
7561  }
7562 
7563  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(Context, CI, E));
7564 }
7565 
7566 SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr *Sema::MergeSYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(
7567  Decl *D, const SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr &A) {
7568  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7569  // already applied to the declaration.
7570  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr>()) {
7571  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
7572  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue())) {
7573  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7574  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
7575  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7576  }
7577  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
7578  return nullptr;
7579  }
7580  }
7581  }
7582  return ::new (Context)
7583  SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
7584 }
7585 
7586 static void handleSYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7587  const ParsedAttr &A) {
7588  // If no attribute argument is specified, set to default value '1'.
7589  Expr *E = A.isArgExpr(0)
7590  ? A.getArgAsExpr(0)
7591  : IntegerLiteral::Create(S.Context, llvm::APInt(32, 1),
7592  S.Context.IntTy, A.getLoc());
7593 
7594  S.AddSYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(D, A, E);
7595 }

7597 /// Handle the [[intel::singlepump]] attribute.
7598 static void handleSYCLIntelSinglePumpAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7599  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7600  // 'singlepump' Attribute does not take any argument. Give a warning for
7601  // duplicate attributes but not if it's one we've implicitly added and drop
7602  // any duplicates.
7603  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelSinglePumpAttr>()) {
7604  if (ExistingAttr && !ExistingAttr->isImplicit()) {
7605  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute_exact) << &AL;
7606  S.Diag(ExistingAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7607  return;
7608  }
7609  }
7610 
7611  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
7612  // static variables, non-static data members, and device_global variables
7613  // for the device compilation.
7614  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7615  ((D->getKind() == Decl::ParmVar) ||
7616  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(S, D))) {
7617  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7618  << AL << /*agent memory arguments*/ 0;
7619  return;
7620  }
7621 
7622  // If the declaration does not have an [[intel::fpga_memory]]
7623  // attribute, this creates one as an implicit attribute.
7624  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
7625  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
7626  S.Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
7627 
7628  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SYCLIntelSinglePumpAttr(S.Context, AL));
7629 }

7631 /// Handle the [[intel::doublepump]] attribute.
7632 static void handleSYCLIntelDoublePumpAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7633  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7634  // 'doublepump' Attribute does not take any argument. Give a warning for
7635  // duplicate attributes but not if it's one we've implicitly added and drop
7636  // any duplicates.
7637  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelDoublePumpAttr>()) {
7638  if (ExistingAttr && !ExistingAttr->isImplicit()) {
7639  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute_exact) << &AL;
7640  S.Diag(ExistingAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7641  return;
7642  }
7643  }
7644 
7645  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
7646  // static variables, non-static data members, and device_global variables
7647  // for the device compilation.
7648  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7649  ((D->getKind() == Decl::ParmVar) ||
7650  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(S, D))) {
7651  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7652  << AL << /*agent memory arguments*/ 0;
7653  return;
7654  }
7655 
7656  // If the declaration does not have an [[intel::fpga_memory]]
7657  // attribute, this creates one as an implicit attribute.
7658  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
7659  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
7660  S.Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
7661 
7662  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SYCLIntelDoublePumpAttr(S.Context, AL));
7663 }

7665 /// Handle the [[intel::fpga_memory]] attribute.
7666 /// This is incompatible with the [[intel::fpga_register]] attribute.
7667 static void handleSYCLIntelMemoryAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7668  SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::MemoryKind Kind;
7669  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
7670  Kind = SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default;
7671  else {
7672  StringRef Str;
7673  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
7674  return;
7675  if (Str.empty() ||
7676  !SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::ConvertStrToMemoryKind(Str, Kind)) {
7677  SmallString<256> ValidStrings;
7678  SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::generateValidStrings(ValidStrings);
7679  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_intel_fpga_memory_arg_invalid)
7680  << AL << ValidStrings;
7681  return;
7682  }
7683  }
7684 
7685  if (auto *MA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>()) {
7686  // Check to see if there's a duplicate memory attribute with different
7687  // values already applied to the declaration.
7688  if (!MA->isImplicit()) {
7689  if (MA->getKind() != Kind) {
7690  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &AL;
7691  S.Diag(MA->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7692  }
7693  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
7694  return;
7695  }
7696  // We are adding a user memory attribute, drop any implicit default.
7697  D->dropAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>();
7698  }
7699 
7700  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
7701  // static variables, agent memory arguments, non-static data members,
7702  // and device_global variables for the device compilation.
7703  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7704  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(S, D)) {
7705  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7706  << AL << /*agent memory arguments*/ 1;
7707  return;
7708  }
7709 
7710  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SYCLIntelMemoryAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind));
7711 }

7713 /// Handle the [[intel::fpga_register]] attribute.
7714 /// This is incompatible with most of the other memory attributes.
7715 static void handleSYCLIntelRegisterAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7716  const ParsedAttr &A) {
7717 
7718  // 'fpga_register' Attribute does not take any argument. Give a warning for
7719  // duplicate attributes but not if it's one we've implicitly added and drop
7720  // any duplicates.
7721  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelRegisterAttr>()) {
7722  if (ExistingAttr && !ExistingAttr->isImplicit()) {
7723  S.Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute_exact) << &A;
7724  S.Diag(ExistingAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7725  return;
7726  }
7727  }
7728 
7729  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
7730  // static variables, non-static data members, and device_global variables
7731  // for the device compilation.
7732  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7733  ((D->getKind() == Decl::ParmVar) ||
7734  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(S, D))) {
7735  S.Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7736  << A << /*agent memory arguments*/ 0;
7737  return;
7738  }
7739 
7740  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SYCLIntelRegisterAttr(S.Context, A));
7741 }
7742 
7743 /// Handle the [[intel::bankwidth]] and [[intel::numbanks]] attributes.
7744 /// These require a single constant power of two greater than zero.
7745 /// These are incompatible with the register attribute.
7746 /// The numbanks and bank_bits attributes are related. If bank_bits exists
7747 /// when handling numbanks they are checked for consistency.
7748 
7749 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelBankWidthAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
7750  Expr *E) {
7751  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
7752  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
7753  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
7754  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
7755  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
7756  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
7757  if (Res.isInvalid())
7758  return;
7759  E = Res.get();
7760 
7761  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
7762  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
7763  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
7764  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
7765  return;
7766  }
7767 
7768  // This attribute requires a single constant power of two greater than zero.
7769  if (!ArgVal.isPowerOf2()) {
7770  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_not_power_of_two)
7771  << CI;
7772  return;
7773  }
7774 
7775  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
7776  // static variables, agent memory arguments, non-static data members,
7777  // and device_global variables for the device compilation.
7778  if (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7779  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(*this, D)) {
7780  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7781  << CI << /*agent memory arguments*/ 1;
7782  return;
7783  }
7784 
7785  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7786  // already applied to the declaration.
7787  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr>()) {
7788  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
7789  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
7790  // whether this is a null pointer.
7791  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
7792  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7793  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
7794  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7795  }
7796  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
7797  return;
7798  }
7799  }
7800  }
7801 
7802  // If the declaration does not have an [[intel::fpga_memory]]
7803  // attribute, this creates one as an implicit attribute.
7804  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
7805  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
7806  Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
7807 
7808  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr(Context, CI, E));
7809 }

7811 SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr *
7812 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelBankWidthAttr(Decl *D, const SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr &A) {
7813  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7814  // already applied to the declaration.
7815  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr>()) {
7816  const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue());
7817  const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue());
7818  if (DeclExpr && MergeExpr &&
7819  DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7820  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
7821  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7822  return nullptr;
7823  }
7824  }
7825 
7826  return ::new (Context) SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
7827 }

7834 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelNumBanksAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
7835  Expr *E) {
7836  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
7837  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
7838  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
7839  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
7840  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
7841  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
7842  if (Res.isInvalid())
7843  return;
7844  E = Res.get();
7845 
7846  // This attribute requires a strictly positive value.
7847  if (ArgVal <= 0) {
7848  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
7849  << CI << /*positive*/ 0;
7850  return;
7851  }
7852 
7853  // This attribute requires a single constant power of two greater than zero.
7854  if (!ArgVal.isPowerOf2()) {
7855  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_not_power_of_two)
7856  << CI;
7857  return;
7858  }
7859 
7860  // Check or add the related BankBits attribute.
7861  if (auto *BBA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr>()) {
7862  unsigned NumBankBits = BBA->args_size();
7863  if (NumBankBits != ArgVal.ceilLogBase2()) {
7864  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_bankbits_numbanks_conflicting) << CI;
7865  return;
7866  }
7867  }
7868 
7869  // Check attribute applies to constant variables, local variables,
7870  // static variables, agent memory arguments, non-static data members,
7871  // and device_global variables for the device compilation.
7872  if (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
7873  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(*this, D)) {
7874  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
7875  << CI << /*agent memory arguments*/ 1;
7876  return;
7877  }
7878 
7879  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7880  // already applied to the declaration.
7881  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>()) {
7882  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
7883  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
7884  // whether this is a null pointer.
7885  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
7886  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7887  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
7888  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7889  }
7890  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
7891  return;
7892  }
7893  }
7894  }
7895 
7896  // If the declaration does not have an [[intel::fpga_memory]]
7897  // attribute, this creates one as an implicit attribute.
7898  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
7899  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
7900  Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
7901 
7902  // We are adding a user NumBanks attribute, drop any implicit default.
7903  if (auto *NBA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>()) {
7904  if (NBA->isImplicit())
7905  D->dropAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>();
7906  }
7907 
7908  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr(Context, CI, E));
7909 }

7911 SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr *
7912 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelNumBanksAttr(Decl *D, const SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr &A) {
7913  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
7914  // already applied to the declaration.
7915  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>()) {
7916  const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue());
7917  const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue());
7918  if (DeclExpr && MergeExpr &&
7919  DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
7920  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
7921  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
7922  return nullptr;
7923  }
7924  }
7925 
7926  return ::new (Context) SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
7927 }

7931 }

7933 static void handleIntelSimpleDualPortAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
7934  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
7935  // 'simple_dual_port' Attribute does not take any argument. Give a warning for
7936  // duplicate attributes but not if it's one we've implicitly added and drop

8018 SYCLIntelMaxReplicatesAttr *
8019 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelMaxReplicatesAttr(Decl *D,

8024  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {

8026  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {

8028  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
8029  }
8030  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
8031  return nullptr;
8032  }
8033  }
8034  }

8044 /// Handle the merge attribute.
8045 /// This requires two string arguments. The first argument is a name, the
8046 /// second is a direction. The direction must be "depth" or "width".
8047 /// This is incompatible with the register attribute.
8048 static void handleSYCLIntelMergeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8049  SmallVector<StringRef, 2> Results;
8050  for (int I = 0; I < 2; I++) {
8051  StringRef Str;
8052  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, Str))
8053  return;
8054 
8055  if (I == 1 && Str != "depth" && Str != "width") {
8056  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_intel_fpga_merge_dir_invalid) << AL;
8057  return;
8058  }
8059  Results.push_back(Str);
8060  }
8061 
8062  // Warn about duplicate attributes if they have different arguments, no
8063  // diagnostic is emitted if the arguments match, and drop any duplicate
8064  // attributes.
8065  if (const auto *Existing = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMergeAttr>()) {
8066  if (Existing && !(Existing->getName() == Results[0] &&
8067  Existing->getDirection() == Results[1])) {
8068  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
8069  S.Diag(Existing->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
8070  }
8071  // If there is no mismatch, drop any duplicate attributes.
8072  return;
8073  }
8074 
8075  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
8076  // static variables, non-static data members, and device_global variables
8077  // for the device compilation.
8078  if (S.Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
8079  ((D->getKind() == Decl::ParmVar) ||
8080  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(S, D))) {
8081  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
8082  << AL << /*agent memory arguments*/ 0;
8083  return;
8084  }
8085 
8086  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
8087  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
8088  S.Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
8089 
8090  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
8091  SYCLIntelMergeAttr(S.Context, AL, Results[0], Results[1]));
8092 }
8093 
8094 /// Handle the bank_bits attribute.
8095 /// This attribute accepts a list of values greater than zero.
8096 /// This is incompatible with the register attribute.
8097 /// The numbanks and bank_bits attributes are related. If numbanks exists
8098 /// when handling bank_bits they are checked for consistency. If numbanks
8099 /// hasn't been added yet an implicit one is added with the correct value.
8100 /// If the user later adds a numbanks attribute the implicit one is removed.
8101 /// The values must be consecutive values (i.e. 3,4,5 or 2,1).
8102 static void handleSYCLIntelBankBitsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
8103  checkForDuplicateAttribute<SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr>(S, D, A);
8104 
8105  if (!A.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
8106  return;
8107 
8108  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> Args;
8109  for (unsigned I = 0; I < A.getNumArgs(); ++I) {
8110  Args.push_back(A.getArgAsExpr(I));
8111  }
8112 
8113  S.AddSYCLIntelBankBitsAttr(D, A, Args.data(), Args.size());
8114 }
8115 
8116 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelBankBitsAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
8117  Expr **Exprs, unsigned Size) {
8118  SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, Exprs, Size);
8119  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> Args;
8120  SmallVector<int64_t, 8> Values;
8121  bool ListIsValueDep = false;
8122  for (auto *E : TmpAttr.args()) {
8123  llvm::APSInt Value(32, /*IsUnsigned=*/false);
8124  Expr::EvalResult Result;
8125  ListIsValueDep = ListIsValueDep || E->isValueDependent();
8126  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
8127  ExprResult ICE = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &Value);
8128  if (ICE.isInvalid())
8129  return;
8130  if (!Value.isNonNegative()) {
8131  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
8132  << CI << /*non-negative*/ 1;
8133  return;
8134  }
8135  E = ICE.get();
8136  }
8137  Args.push_back(E);
8138  Values.push_back(Value.getExtValue());
8139  }
8140 
8141  // Check that the list is consecutive.
8142  if (!ListIsValueDep && Values.size() > 1) {
8143  bool ListIsAscending = Values[0] < Values[1];
8144  for (int I = 0, E = Values.size() - 1; I < E; ++I) {
8145  if (Values[I + 1] != Values[I] + (ListIsAscending ? 1 : -1)) {
8146  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_bankbits_non_consecutive) << &TmpAttr;
8147  return;
8148  }
8149  }
8150  }
8151 
8152  // Check or add the related numbanks attribute.
8153  if (auto *NBA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>()) {
8154  Expr *E = NBA->getValue();
8155  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
8156  Expr::EvalResult Result;
8157  E->EvaluateAsInt(Result, Context);
8158  llvm::APSInt Value = Result.Val.getInt();
8159  if (Args.size() != Value.ceilLogBase2()) {
8160  Diag(TmpAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_bankbits_numbanks_conflicting);
8161  return;
8162  }
8163  }
8164  } else {
8165  llvm::APInt Num(32, (unsigned)(1 << Args.size()));
8166  Expr *NBE =
8167  IntegerLiteral::Create(Context, Num, Context.IntTy, SourceLocation());
8168  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr::CreateImplicit(Context, NBE));
8169  }
8170 
8171  // Check attribute applies to field, constant variables, local variables,
8172  // static variables, agent memory arguments, non-static data members,
8173  // and device_global variables for the device compilation.
8174  if (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
8175  CheckValidFPGAMemoryAttributesVar(*this, D)) {
8176  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_incorrect_variable)
8177  << CI << /*agent memory arguments*/ 1;
8178  return;
8179  }
8180 
8181  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
8182  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
8183  Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
8184 
8185  D->addAttr(::new (Context)
8186  SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr(Context, CI, Args.data(), Args.size()));
8187 }
8188 
8189 void Sema::AddSYCLIntelPrivateCopiesAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
8190  Expr *E) {
8191  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
8192  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
8193  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
8194  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
8195  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
8196  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
8197  if (Res.isInvalid())
8198  return;
8199  E = Res.get();
8200  // This attribute requires a non-negative value.
8201  if (ArgVal < 0) {
8202  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
8203  << CI << /*non-negative*/ 1;
8204  return;
8205  }
8206 
8207  // Check attribute applies to field as well as const variables, non-static
8208  // local variables, non-static data members, and device_global variables.
8209  // for the device compilation.
8210  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
8211  if (Context.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
8212  (!(isa<FieldDecl>(D) ||
8213  (VD->getKind() != Decl::ImplicitParam &&
8214  VD->getKind() != Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm &&
8215  VD->getKind() != Decl::ParmVar &&
8216  (VD->hasLocalStorage() ||
8217  SYCL().isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
8218  VD->getType())))))) {
8219  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_fpga_attribute_invalid_decl) << CI;
8220  return;
8221  }
8222  }
8223 
8224  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
8225  // already applied to the declaration.
8226  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPrivateCopiesAttr>()) {
8227  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
8228  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
8229  // whether this is a null pointer.
8230  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
8231  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
8232  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
8233  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
8234  }
8235  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
8236  return;
8237  }
8238  }
8239  }
8240 
8241  // If the declaration does not have [[intel::fpga_memory]]
8242  // attribute, this creates default implicit memory.
8243  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
8244  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
8245  Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
8246 
8247  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelPrivateCopiesAttr(Context, CI, E));
8248 }

8250 static void handleSYCLIntelPrivateCopiesAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,

8300 
8301  // If the declaration does not have an [[intel::fpga_memory]]
8302  // attribute, this creates one as an implicit attribute.
8303  if (!D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>())
8304  D->addAttr(SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::CreateImplicit(
8305  Context, SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default));
8306 
8307  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr(Context, CI, E));
8308 }
8309 
8310 SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr *
8311 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr(Decl *D,
8312  const SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr &A) {
8313  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
8314  // already applied to the declaration.
8315  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr>()) {
8316  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getValue())) {
8317  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getValue())) {
8318  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
8319  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << &A;
8320  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
8321  }
8322  // If there is no mismatch, drop any duplicate attributes.
8323  return nullptr;
8324  }
8325  }
8326  }
8327 
8328  return ::new (Context) SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr(Context, A, A.getValue());
8329 }

8332  const ParsedAttr &A) {
8333  S.AddSYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr(D, A, A.getArgAsExpr(0));
8334 }

8336 static void handleXRayLogArgsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8337  ParamIdx ArgCount;
8338 
8339  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 1, AL.getArgAsExpr(0),
8340  ArgCount,
8341  true /* CanIndexImplicitThis */))
8342  return;
8343 
8344  // ArgCount isn't a parameter index [0;n), it's a count [1;n]
8345  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
8346  XRayLogArgsAttr(S.Context, AL, ArgCount.getSourceIndex()));
8347 }

8349 static void handlePatchableFunctionEntryAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
8350  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8351  uint32_t Count = 0, Offset = 0;
8352  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Count, 0, true))
8353  return;
8354  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 2) {
8355  Expr *Arg = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
8356  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, Arg, Offset, 1, true))
8357  return;
8358  if (Count < Offset) {
8359  S.Diag(getAttrLoc(AL), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_range)
8360  << &AL << 0 << Count << Arg->getBeginLoc();
8361  return;
8362  }
8363  }
8364  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
8365  PatchableFunctionEntryAttr(S.Context, AL, Count, Offset));
8366 }
8367 
8368 void Sema::addSYCLIntelPipeIOAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
8369  Expr *E) {
8370  VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
8371  QualType Ty = VD->getType();
8372  // TODO: Applicable only on pipe storages. Currently they are defined
8373  // as structures inside of SYCL headers. Add a check for pipe_storage_t
8374  // when it is ready.
8375  if (!Ty->isStructureType()) {
8376  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type_str)
8377  << CI << CI.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
8378  << "SYCL pipe storage declaration";
8379  return;
8380  }
8381 
8382  if (!E->isValueDependent()) {
8383  // Validate that we have an integer constant expression and then store the
8384  // converted constant expression into the semantic attribute so that we
8385  // don't have to evaluate it again later.
8386  llvm::APSInt ArgVal;
8387  ExprResult Res = VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(E, &ArgVal);
8388  if (Res.isInvalid())
8389  return;
8390  E = Res.get();
8391 
8392  // This attribute requires a non-negative value.
8393  if (ArgVal < 0) {
8394  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_attribute_requires_positive_integer)
8395  << CI << /*non-negative*/ 1;
8396  return;
8397  }
8398 
8399  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
8400  // already applied to the declaration.
8401  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr>()) {
8402  // If the other attribute argument is instantiation dependent, we won't
8403  // have converted it to a constant expression yet and thus we test
8404  // whether this is a null pointer.
8405  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getID())) {
8406  if (ArgVal != DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
8407  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << CI;
8408  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::note_previous_attribute);
8409  }
8410  // Drop the duplicate attribute.
8411  return;
8412  }
8413  }
8414  }
8415 
8416  D->addAttr(::new (Context) SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr(Context, CI, E));
8417 }
8418 
8419 SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr *
8420 Sema::MergeSYCLIntelPipeIOAttr(Decl *D, const SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr &A) {
8421  // Check to see if there's a duplicate attribute with different values
8422  // already applied to the declaration.
8423  if (const auto *DeclAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr>()) {
8424  if (const auto *DeclExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(DeclAttr->getID())) {
8425  if (const auto *MergeExpr = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(A.getID())) {
8426  if (DeclExpr->getResultAsAPSInt() != MergeExpr->getResultAsAPSInt()) {
8427  Diag(DeclAttr->getLoc(), diag::err_disallowed_duplicate_attribute)
8428  << &A;
8429  Diag(A.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
8430  }
8431  // Do not add a duplicate attribute.
8432  return nullptr;
8433  }
8434  }
8435  }
8436 
8437  return ::new (Context) SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr(Context, A, A.getID());
8438 }

8441  Expr *E = A.getArgAsExpr(0);

8508 // Checks if an expression is a valid filter list for an add_ir_attributes_*
8509 // attribute. Returns true if an error occured.
8510 static bool checkAddIRAttributesFilterListExpr(Expr *FilterListArg, Sema &S,
8511  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
8512  const auto *FilterListE = cast<InitListExpr>(FilterListArg);
8513  for (const Expr *FilterElemE : FilterListE->inits())
8514  if (!isa<StringLiteral>(FilterElemE))
8515  return S.Diag(FilterElemE->getBeginLoc(),
8516  diag::err_sycl_add_ir_attribute_invalid_filter)
8517  << CI;
8518  return false;
8519 }
8520 
8521 // Returns true if a type is either an array of char or a pointer to char.
8522 static bool isAddIRAttributesValidStringType(QualType T) {
8523  if (!T->isArrayType() && !T->isPointerType())
8524  return false;
8525  QualType ElemT = T->isArrayType()
8526  ? cast<ArrayType>(T.getTypePtr())->getElementType()
8527  : T->getPointeeType();
8528  return ElemT.isConstQualified() && ElemT->isCharType();
8529 }
8530 
8531 // Checks if an expression is a valid attribute name for an add_ir_attributes_*
8532 // attribute. Returns true if an error occured.
8533 static bool checkAddIRAttributesNameExpr(Expr *NameArg, Sema &S,
8534  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
8535  // Only strings and const char * are valid name arguments.
8536  if (isAddIRAttributesValidStringType(NameArg->getType()))
8537  return false;
8538 
8539  return S.Diag(NameArg->getBeginLoc(),
8540  diag::err_sycl_add_ir_attribute_invalid_name)
8541  << CI;
8542 }
8543 
8544 // Checks if an expression is a valid attribute value for an add_ir_attributes_*
8545 // attribute. Returns true if an error occured.
8546 static bool checkAddIRAttributesValueExpr(Expr *ValArg, Sema &S,
8547  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
8548  QualType ValType = ValArg->getType();
8549  if (isAddIRAttributesValidStringType(ValType) || ValType->isNullPtrType() ||
8550  ValType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() || ValType->isFloatingType())
8551  return false;
8552 
8553  return S.Diag(ValArg->getBeginLoc(),
8554  diag::err_sycl_add_ir_attribute_invalid_value)
8555  << CI;
8556 }
8557 
8558 // Checks and evaluates arguments of an add_ir_attributes_* attribute. Returns
8559 // true if an error occured.
8560 static bool evaluateAddIRAttributesArgs(Expr **Args, size_t ArgsSize, Sema &S,
8561  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
8562  ASTContext &Context = S.getASTContext();
8563 
8564  // Check filter list if it is the first argument.
8565  bool HasFilter = ArgsSize && isa<InitListExpr>(Args[0]);
8566  if (HasFilter && checkAddIRAttributesFilterListExpr(Args[0], S, CI))
8567  return true;
8568 
8569  llvm::SmallVector<PartialDiagnosticAt, 8> Notes;
8570  bool HasDependentArg = false;
8571  for (unsigned I = HasFilter; I < ArgsSize; I++) {
8572  Expr *&E = Args[I];
8573 
8574  if (isa<InitListExpr>(E))
8575  return S.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(),
8576  diag::err_sycl_add_ir_attr_filter_list_invalid_arg)
8577  << CI;
8578 
8579  if (E->isValueDependent() || E->isTypeDependent()) {
8580  HasDependentArg = true;
8581  continue;
8582  }
8583 
8584  Expr::EvalResult Eval;
8585  Eval.Diag = &Notes;
8586  if (!E->EvaluateAsConstantExpr(Eval, Context) || !Notes.empty()) {
8587  S.Diag(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
8588  << CI << (I + 1) << AANT_ArgumentConstantExpr;
8589  for (auto &Note : Notes)
8590  S.Diag(Note.first, Note.second);
8591  return true;
8592  }
8593  assert(Eval.Val.hasValue());
8594  E = ConstantExpr::Create(Context, E, Eval.Val);
8595  }
8596 
8597  // If there are no dependent expressions, check for expected number of args.
8598  if (!HasDependentArg && ArgsSize && (ArgsSize - HasFilter) & 1)
8599  return S.Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_sycl_add_ir_attribute_must_have_pairs)
8600  << CI;
8601 
8602  // If there are no dependent expressions, check argument types.
8603  // First half of the arguments are names, the second half are values.
8604  unsigned MidArg = (ArgsSize - HasFilter) / 2 + HasFilter;
8605  if (!HasDependentArg) {
8606  for (unsigned I = HasFilter; I < ArgsSize; ++I) {
8607  if ((I < MidArg && checkAddIRAttributesNameExpr(Args[I], S, CI)) ||
8608  (I >= MidArg && checkAddIRAttributesValueExpr(Args[I], S, CI)))
8609  return true;
8610  }
8611  }
8612  return false;
8613 }
8614 
8615 static bool hasDependentExpr(Expr **Exprs, const size_t ExprsSize) {
8616  return std::any_of(Exprs, Exprs + ExprsSize, [](const Expr *E) {
8617  return E->isValueDependent() || E->isTypeDependent();
8618  });
8619 }
8620 
8621 static bool hasSameSYCLAddIRAttributes(
8622  const SmallVector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, 4> &LAttrs,
8623  const SmallVector<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, 4> &RAttrs) {
8624  std::set<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> LNameValSet{LAttrs.begin(),
8625  LAttrs.end()};
8626  std::set<std::pair<std::string, std::string>> RNameValSet{RAttrs.begin(),
8627  RAttrs.end()};
8628  return LNameValSet == RNameValSet;
8629 }
8630 
8631 template <typename AddIRAttrT>
8632 static bool checkSYCLAddIRAttributesMergeability(const AddIRAttrT &NewAttr,
8633  const AddIRAttrT &ExistingAttr,
8634  Sema &S) {
8635  ASTContext &Context = S.getASTContext();
8636  // If there are no dependent argument expressions and the filters or the
8637  // attributes are different, then fail due to differing duplicates.
8638  if (!hasDependentExpr(NewAttr.args_begin(), NewAttr.args_size()) &&
8639  !hasDependentExpr(ExistingAttr.args_begin(), ExistingAttr.args_size()) &&
8640  (NewAttr.getAttributeFilter() != ExistingAttr.getAttributeFilter() ||
8641  !hasSameSYCLAddIRAttributes(
8642  NewAttr.getAttributeNameValuePairs(Context),
8643  ExistingAttr.getAttributeNameValuePairs(Context)))) {
8644  S.Diag(ExistingAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_duplicate_attribute) << &NewAttr;
8645  S.Diag(NewAttr.getLoc(), diag::note_conflicting_attribute);
8646  return true;
8647  }
8648  return false;
8649 }
8650 
8651 void Sema::CheckSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttrConflicts(Decl *D) {
8652  const auto *AddIRFuncAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>();
8653 
8654  // If there is no such attribute there is nothing to check. If there are
8655  // dependent arguments we cannot know the actual number of arguments so we
8656  // defer the check.
8657  if (!AddIRFuncAttr ||
8658  hasDependentExpr(AddIRFuncAttr->args_begin(), AddIRFuncAttr->args_size()))
8659  return;
8660 
8661  // If there are no name-value pairs in the attribute it will not have an
8662  // effect and we can skip the check. The filter is ignored.
8663  size_t NumArgsWithoutFilter =
8664  AddIRFuncAttr->args_size() - (AddIRFuncAttr->hasFilterList() ? 1 : 0);
8665  if (NumArgsWithoutFilter == 0)
8666  return;
8667 
8668  // "sycl-single-task" is present on all single_task invocations, implicitly
8669  // added by the SYCL headers. It can only conflict with max_global_work_dim,
8670  // but the value will be the same so there is no need for a warning.
8671  if (NumArgsWithoutFilter == 2) {
8672  auto NameValuePairs = AddIRFuncAttr->getAttributeNameValuePairs(Context);
8673  if (NameValuePairs.size() > 0 &&
8674  NameValuePairs[0].first == "sycl-single-task")
8675  return;
8676  }
8677 
8678  // If there are potentially conflicting attributes, we issue a warning.
8679  for (const auto *Attr : std::vector<AttributeCommonInfo *>{
8680  D->getAttr<SYCLReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(),
8681  D->getAttr<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(),
8682  D->getAttr<SYCLWorkGroupSizeHintAttr>(),
8683  D->getAttr<SYCLDeviceHasAttr>()})
8684  if (Attr)
8685  Diag(Attr->getLoc(), diag::warn_sycl_old_and_new_kernel_attributes)
8686  << Attr;
8687 }
8688 
8689 SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr *Sema::MergeSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(
8690  Decl *D, const SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr &A) {
8691  if (const auto *ExistingAttr =
8692  D->getAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>()) {
8693  checkSYCLAddIRAttributesMergeability(A, *ExistingAttr, *this);
8694  return nullptr;
8695  }
8696  return A.clone(Context);
8697 }
8698 
8699 void Sema::AddSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(Decl *D,
8700  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
8701  MutableArrayRef<Expr *> Args) {
8702  if (const auto *FuncD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
8703  if (FuncD->isDefaulted()) {
8704  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_disallow_attribute_on_func) << CI << 0;
8705  return;
8706  }
8707  if (FuncD->isDeleted()) {
8708  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::err_disallow_attribute_on_func) << CI << 1;
8709  return;
8710  }
8711  }
8712 
8713  auto *Attr = SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr::Create(Context, Args.data(),
8714  Args.size(), CI);
8715  if (evaluateAddIRAttributesArgs(Attr->args_begin(), Attr->args_size(), *this,
8716  CI))
8717  return;
8718  D->addAttr(Attr);
8719 }

8721 static void handleSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
8722  const ParsedAttr &A) {
8723  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Args;
8724  Args.reserve(A.getNumArgs() - 1);
8725  for (unsigned I = 0; I < A.getNumArgs(); I++) {
8726  assert(A.isArgExpr(I));
8727  Args.push_back(A.getArgAsExpr(I));
8728  }
8729 
8730  S.AddSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(D, A, Args);
8731 }

8831 namespace {
8832 struct IntrinToName {
8833  uint32_t Id;
8834  int32_t FullName;
8835  int32_t ShortName;
8836 };
8837 } // unnamed namespace
8838 
8839 static bool ArmBuiltinAliasValid(unsigned BuiltinID, StringRef AliasName,
8840  ArrayRef<IntrinToName> Map,
8841  const char *IntrinNames) {
8842  AliasName.consume_front("__arm_");
8843  const IntrinToName *It =
8844  llvm::lower_bound(Map, BuiltinID, [](const IntrinToName &L, unsigned Id) {
8845  return L.Id < Id;
8846  });
8847  if (It == Map.end() || It->Id != BuiltinID)
8848  return false;
8849  StringRef FullName(&IntrinNames[It->FullName]);
8850  if (AliasName == FullName)
8851  return true;
8852  if (It->ShortName == -1)
8853  return false;
8854  StringRef ShortName(&IntrinNames[It->ShortName]);
8855  return AliasName == ShortName;
8856 }
8857 
8858 static bool ArmMveAliasValid(unsigned BuiltinID, StringRef AliasName) {
8859 #include "clang/Basic/arm_mve_builtin_aliases.inc"
8860  // The included file defines:
8861  // - ArrayRef<IntrinToName> Map
8862  // - const char IntrinNames[]
8863  return ArmBuiltinAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName, Map, IntrinNames);
8864 }

8866 static bool ArmCdeAliasValid(unsigned BuiltinID, StringRef AliasName) {
8867 #include "clang/Basic/arm_cde_builtin_aliases.inc"
8868  return ArmBuiltinAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName, Map, IntrinNames);
8869 }

8871 static bool ArmSveAliasValid(ASTContext &Context, unsigned BuiltinID,
8872  StringRef AliasName) {
8873  if (Context.BuiltinInfo.isAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID))
8874  BuiltinID = Context.BuiltinInfo.getAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID);
8875  return BuiltinID >= AArch64::FirstSVEBuiltin &&
8876  BuiltinID <= AArch64::LastSVEBuiltin;
8877 }

8879 static bool ArmSmeAliasValid(ASTContext &Context, unsigned BuiltinID,
8880  StringRef AliasName) {
8881  if (Context.BuiltinInfo.isAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID))
8882  BuiltinID = Context.BuiltinInfo.getAuxBuiltinID(BuiltinID);
8883  return BuiltinID >= AArch64::FirstSMEBuiltin &&
8884  BuiltinID <= AArch64::LastSMEBuiltin;
8885 }

8887 static void handleArmBuiltinAliasAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8888  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
8889  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
8890  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
8891  return;
8892  }
8893 
8894  IdentifierInfo *Ident = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
8895  unsigned BuiltinID = Ident->getBuiltinID();
8896  StringRef AliasName = cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getIdentifier()->getName();
8897 
8898  bool IsAArch64 = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64();
8899  if ((IsAArch64 && !ArmSveAliasValid(S.Context, BuiltinID, AliasName) &&
8900  !ArmSmeAliasValid(S.Context, BuiltinID, AliasName)) ||
8901  (!IsAArch64 && !ArmMveAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName) &&
8902  !ArmCdeAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName))) {
8903  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_arm_builtin_alias);
8904  return;
8905  }
8906 
8907  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ArmBuiltinAliasAttr(S.Context, AL, Ident));
8908 }
8909 
8910 static bool RISCVAliasValid(unsigned BuiltinID, StringRef AliasName) {
8911  return BuiltinID >= RISCV::FirstRVVBuiltin &&
8912  BuiltinID <= RISCV::LastRVVBuiltin;
8913 }

8915 static bool SYCLAliasValid(ASTContext &Context, unsigned BuiltinID) {
8916  constexpr llvm::StringLiteral Prefix = "__builtin_intel_sycl";
8917  return Context.BuiltinInfo.getName(BuiltinID).starts_with(Prefix);
8918 }

8920 static void handleBuiltinAliasAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
8921  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8922  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
8923  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
8924  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
8925  return;
8926  }
8927 
8928  IdentifierInfo *Ident = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
8929  unsigned BuiltinID = Ident->getBuiltinID();
8930  StringRef AliasName = cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getIdentifier()->getName();
8931 
8932  bool IsAArch64 = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64();
8933  bool IsARM = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isARM();
8934  bool IsRISCV = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isRISCV();
8935  bool IsHLSL = S.Context.getLangOpts().HLSL;
8936  bool IsSYCL = S.Context.getLangOpts().isSYCL();
8937  if ((IsAArch64 && !ArmSveAliasValid(S.Context, BuiltinID, AliasName)) ||
8938  (IsARM && !ArmMveAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName) &&
8939  !ArmCdeAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName)) ||
8940  (IsRISCV && !RISCVAliasValid(BuiltinID, AliasName)) ||
8941  (IsSYCL && !SYCLAliasValid(S.Context, BuiltinID)) ||
8942  (!IsAArch64 && !IsARM && !IsRISCV && !IsHLSL && !IsSYCL)) {
8943  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_builtin_alias) << AL;
8944  return;
8945  }
8946 
8947  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) BuiltinAliasAttr(S.Context, AL, Ident));
8948 }

8950 static void handleNullableTypeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8951  if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr())
8952  return;
8953 
8954  if (auto *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
8955  !CRD || !(CRD->isClass() || CRD->isStruct())) {
8956  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type_str)
8957  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << "classes";
8958  return;
8959  }
8960 
8961  handleSimpleAttribute<TypeNullableAttr>(S, D, AL);
8962 }
8963 
8964 static void handlePreferredTypeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
8965  if (!AL.hasParsedType()) {
8966  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << AL << 1;
8967  return;
8968  }
8969 
8970  TypeSourceInfo *ParmTSI = nullptr;
8971  QualType QT = S.GetTypeFromParser(AL.getTypeArg(), &ParmTSI);
8972  assert(ParmTSI && "no type source info for attribute argument");
8973  S.RequireCompleteType(ParmTSI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(), QT,
8974  diag::err_incomplete_type);
8975 
8976  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) PreferredTypeAttr(S.Context, AL, ParmTSI));
8977 }
