8979 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8980 // Checker-specific attribute handlers.
8981 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8982 static bool isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(QualType QT) {
8983  return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isObjCRetainableType();
8984 }
8985 
8986 static bool isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(QualType QT) {
8987  return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isObjCObjectPointerType() ||
8988  QT->isObjCNSObjectType();
8989 }
8990 
8991 static bool isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(QualType QT) {
8992  return QT->isDependentType() || QT->isPointerType() ||
8993  isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(QT);
8994 }
8995 
8996 static bool isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(QualType QT) {
8997  if (QT->isDependentType())
8998  return true;
8999  QualType PT = QT->getPointeeType();
9000  return !PT.isNull() && PT->getAsCXXRecordDecl() != nullptr;
9001 }
9002 
9003 void Sema::AddXConsumedAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
9004  RetainOwnershipKind K,
9005  bool IsTemplateInstantiation) {
9006  ValueDecl *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
9007  switch (K) {
9008  case RetainOwnershipKind::OS:
9009  handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<OSConsumedAttr>(
9010  *this, VD, CI, isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(VD->getType()),
9011  diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type,
9012  /*ExtraArgs=*/CI.getRange(), "os_consumed", /*pointers*/ 1);
9013  return;
9014  case RetainOwnershipKind::NS:
9015  handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<NSConsumedAttr>(
9016  *this, VD, CI, isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(VD->getType()),
9017 
9018  // These attributes are normally just advisory, but in ARC, ns_consumed
9019  // is significant. Allow non-dependent code to contain inappropriate
9020  // attributes even in ARC, but require template instantiations to be
9021  // set up correctly.
9022  ((IsTemplateInstantiation && getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
9023  ? diag::err_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type
9024  : diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type),
9025  /*ExtraArgs=*/CI.getRange(), "ns_consumed", /*objc pointers*/ 0);
9026  return;
9027  case RetainOwnershipKind::CF:
9028  handleSimpleAttributeOrDiagnose<CFConsumedAttr>(
9029  *this, VD, CI, isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(VD->getType()),
9030  diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type,
9031  /*ExtraArgs=*/CI.getRange(), "cf_consumed", /*pointers*/ 1);
9032  return;
9033  }
9034 }
9035 
9036 static Sema::RetainOwnershipKind
9037 parsedAttrToRetainOwnershipKind(const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9038  switch (AL.getKind()) {
9039  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFConsumed:
9040  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
9041  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
9042  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::CF;
9043  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSConsumesThis:
9044  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSConsumed:
9045  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
9046  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
9047  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetainedOnZero:
9048  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetainedOnNonZero:
9049  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::OS;
9050  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSConsumesSelf:
9051  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSConsumed:
9052  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
9053  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
9054  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
9055  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::NS;
9056  default:
9057  llvm_unreachable("Wrong argument supplied");
9058  }
9059 }
9060 
9061 bool Sema::checkNSReturnsRetainedReturnType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType QT) {
9062  if (isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(QT))
9063  return false;
9064 
9065  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
9066  << "'ns_returns_retained'" << 0 << 0;
9067  return true;
9068 }
9069 
9070 /// \return whether the parameter is a pointer to OSObject pointer.
9071 static bool isValidOSObjectOutParameter(const Decl *D) {
9072  const auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D);
9073  if (!PVD)
9074  return false;
9075  QualType QT = PVD->getType();
9076  QualType PT = QT->getPointeeType();
9077  return !PT.isNull() && isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(PT);
9078 }
9079 
9080 static void handleXReturnsXRetainedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9081  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9082  QualType ReturnType;
9083  Sema::RetainOwnershipKind K = parsedAttrToRetainOwnershipKind(AL);
9084 
9085  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
9086  ReturnType = MD->getReturnType();
9087  } else if (S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && hasDeclarator(D) &&
9088  (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained)) {
9089  return; // ignore: was handled as a type attribute
9090  } else if (const auto *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)) {
9091  ReturnType = PD->getType();
9092  } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
9093  ReturnType = FD->getReturnType();
9094  } else if (const auto *Param = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
9095  // Attributes on parameters are used for out-parameters,
9096  // passed as pointers-to-pointers.
9097  unsigned DiagID = K == Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::CF
9098  ? /*pointer-to-CF-pointer*/2
9099  : /*pointer-to-OSObject-pointer*/3;
9100  ReturnType = Param->getType()->getPointeeType();
9101  if (ReturnType.isNull()) {
9102  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type)
9103  << AL << DiagID << AL.getRange();
9104  return;
9105  }
9106  } else if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr()) {
9107  return;
9108  } else {
9109  AttributeDeclKind ExpectedDeclKind;
9110  switch (AL.getKind()) {
9111  default: llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
9112  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
9113  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
9114  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
9115  ExpectedDeclKind = ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
9116  break;
9117 
9118  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
9119  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
9120  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
9121  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
9122  ExpectedDeclKind = ExpectedFunctionMethodOrParameter;
9123  break;
9124  }
9125  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
9126  << AL.getRange() << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
9127  << ExpectedDeclKind;
9128  return;
9129  }
9130 
9131  bool TypeOK;
9132  bool Cf;
9133  unsigned ParmDiagID = 2; // Pointer-to-CF-pointer
9134  switch (AL.getKind()) {
9135  default: llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
9136  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
9137  TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfNSReturnsRetainedAttribute(ReturnType);
9138  Cf = false;
9139  break;
9140 
9141  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
9142  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
9143  TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfNSAttribute(ReturnType);
9144  Cf = false;
9145  break;
9146 
9147  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
9148  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
9149  TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfCFAttribute(ReturnType);
9150  Cf = true;
9151  break;
9152 
9153  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
9154  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
9155  TypeOK = isValidSubjectOfOSAttribute(ReturnType);
9156  Cf = true;
9157  ParmDiagID = 3; // Pointer-to-OSObject-pointer
9158  break;
9159  }
9160 
9161  if (!TypeOK) {
9162  if (AL.isUsedAsTypeAttr())
9163  return;
9164 
9165  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D)) {
9166  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_parameter_type)
9167  << AL << ParmDiagID << AL.getRange();
9168  } else {
9169  // Needs to be kept in sync with warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type.
9170  enum : unsigned {
9171  Function,
9172  Method,
9173  Property
9174  } SubjectKind = Function;
9175  if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
9176  SubjectKind = Method;
9177  else if (isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))
9178  SubjectKind = Property;
9179  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
9180  << AL << SubjectKind << Cf << AL.getRange();
9181  }
9182  return;
9183  }
9184 
9185  switch (AL.getKind()) {
9186  default:
9187  llvm_unreachable("invalid ownership attribute");
9188  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsAutoreleased:
9189  handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsAutoreleasedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9190  return;
9191  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained:
9192  handleSimpleAttribute<CFReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9193  return;
9194  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsNotRetained:
9195  handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9196  return;
9197  case ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained:
9198  handleSimpleAttribute<CFReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9199  return;
9200  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained:
9201  handleSimpleAttribute<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9202  return;
9203  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsRetained:
9204  handleSimpleAttribute<OSReturnsRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9205  return;
9206  case ParsedAttr::AT_OSReturnsNotRetained:
9207  handleSimpleAttribute<OSReturnsNotRetainedAttr>(S, D, AL);
9208  return;
9209  };
9210 }
9211 
9212 static void handleObjCReturnsInnerPointerAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9213  const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
9214  const int EP_ObjCMethod = 1;
9215  const int EP_ObjCProperty = 2;
9216 
9217  SourceLocation loc = Attrs.getLoc();
9218  QualType resultType;
9219  if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
9220  resultType = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)->getReturnType();
9221  else
9222  resultType = cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D)->getType();
9223 
9224  if (!resultType->isReferenceType() &&
9225  (!resultType->isPointerType() || resultType->isObjCRetainableType())) {
9226  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_ns_attribute_wrong_return_type)
9227  << SourceRange(loc) << Attrs
9228  << (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) ? EP_ObjCMethod : EP_ObjCProperty)
9229  << /*non-retainable pointer*/ 2;
9230 
9231  // Drop the attribute.
9232  return;
9233  }
9234 
9235  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCReturnsInnerPointerAttr(S.Context, Attrs));
9236 }

9238 static void handleObjCRequiresSuperAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9239  const ParsedAttr &Attrs) {
9240  const auto *Method = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
9241 
9242  const DeclContext *DC = Method->getDeclContext();
9243  if (const auto *PDecl = dyn_cast_if_present<ObjCProtocolDecl>(DC)) {
9244  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_objc_requires_super_protocol) << Attrs
9245  << 0;
9246  S.Diag(PDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_protocol_decl);
9247  return;
9248  }
9249  if (Method->getMethodFamily() == OMF_dealloc) {
9250  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_objc_requires_super_protocol) << Attrs
9251  << 1;
9252  return;
9253  }
9254 
9255  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCRequiresSuperAttr(S.Context, Attrs));
9256 }

9258 static void handleNSErrorDomain(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &Attr) {
9259  if (!isa<TagDecl>(D)) {
9260  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_nserrordomain_invalid_decl) << 0;
9261  return;
9262  }
9263 
9264  IdentifierLoc *IdentLoc =
9265  Attr.isArgIdent(0) ? Attr.getArgAsIdent(0) : nullptr;
9266  if (!IdentLoc || !IdentLoc->Ident) {
9267  // Try to locate the argument directly.
9268  SourceLocation Loc = Attr.getLoc();
9269  if (Attr.isArgExpr(0) && Attr.getArgAsExpr(0))
9270  Loc = Attr.getArgAsExpr(0)->getBeginLoc();
9271 
9272  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_nserrordomain_invalid_decl) << 0;
9273  return;
9274  }
9275 
9276  // Verify that the identifier is a valid decl in the C decl namespace.
9277  LookupResult Result(S, DeclarationName(IdentLoc->Ident), SourceLocation(),
9278  Sema::LookupNameKind::LookupOrdinaryName);
9279  if (!S.LookupName(Result, S.TUScope) || !Result.getAsSingle<VarDecl>()) {
9280  S.Diag(IdentLoc->Loc, diag::err_nserrordomain_invalid_decl)
9281  << 1 << IdentLoc->Ident;
9282  return;
9283  }
9284 
9285  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
9286  NSErrorDomainAttr(S.Context, Attr, IdentLoc->Ident));
9287 }

9289 static void handleObjCBridgeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9290  IdentifierLoc *Parm = AL.isArgIdent(0) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(0) : nullptr;
9291 
9292  if (!Parm) {
9293  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
9294  return;
9295  }
9296 
9297  // Typedefs only allow objc_bridge(id) and have some additional checking.
9298  if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
9299  if (!Parm->Ident->isStr("id")) {
9300  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_typedef_not_id) << AL;
9301  return;
9302  }
9303 
9304  // Only allow 'cv void *'.
9305  QualType T = TD->getUnderlyingType();
9306  if (!T->isVoidPointerType()) {
9307  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_typedef_not_void_pointer);
9308  return;
9309  }
9310  }
9311 
9312  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCBridgeAttr(S.Context, AL, Parm->Ident));
9313 }

9318 
9319  if (!Parm) {
9320  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
9321  return;
9322  }
9323 
9324  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
9325  ObjCBridgeMutableAttr(S.Context, AL, Parm->Ident));
9326 }

9328 static void handleObjCBridgeRelatedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9329  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9330  IdentifierInfo *RelatedClass =
9331  AL.isArgIdent(0) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident : nullptr;
9332  if (!RelatedClass) {
9333  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_attr_not_id) << AL << 0;
9334  return;
9335  }
9336  IdentifierInfo *ClassMethod =
9337  AL.getArgAsIdent(1) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(1)->Ident : nullptr;
9338  IdentifierInfo *InstanceMethod =
9339  AL.getArgAsIdent(2) ? AL.getArgAsIdent(2)->Ident : nullptr;
9340  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCBridgeRelatedAttr(
9341  S.Context, AL, RelatedClass, ClassMethod, InstanceMethod));
9342 }

9344 static void handleObjCDesignatedInitializer(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9345  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9346  DeclContext *Ctx = D->getDeclContext();
9347 
9348  // This attribute can only be applied to methods in interfaces or class
9349  // extensions.
9350  if (!isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Ctx) &&
9351  !(isa<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx) &&
9352  cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx)->IsClassExtension())) {
9353  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_designated_init_attr_non_init);
9354  return;
9355  }
9356 
9357  ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace;
9358  if (auto *CatDecl = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(Ctx))
9359  IFace = CatDecl->getClassInterface();
9360  else
9361  IFace = cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Ctx);
9362 
9363  if (!IFace)
9364  return;
9365 
9366  IFace->setHasDesignatedInitializers();
9367  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCDesignatedInitializerAttr(S.Context, AL));
9368 }

9370 static void handleObjCRuntimeName(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9371  StringRef MetaDataName;
9372  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, MetaDataName))
9373  return;
9374  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
9375  ObjCRuntimeNameAttr(S.Context, AL, MetaDataName));
9376 }
9377 
9378 // When a user wants to use objc_boxable with a union or struct
9379 // but they don't have access to the declaration (legacy/third-party code)
9380 // then they can 'enable' this feature with a typedef:
9381 // typedef struct __attribute((objc_boxable)) legacy_struct legacy_struct;
9382 static void handleObjCBoxable(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9383  bool notify = false;
9384 
9385  auto *RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D);
9386  if (RD && RD->getDefinition()) {
9387  RD = RD->getDefinition();
9388  notify = true;
9389  }
9390 
9391  if (RD) {
9392  ObjCBoxableAttr *BoxableAttr =
9393  ::new (S.Context) ObjCBoxableAttr(S.Context, AL);
9394  RD->addAttr(BoxableAttr);
9395  if (notify) {
9396  // we need to notify ASTReader/ASTWriter about
9397  // modification of existing declaration
9398  if (ASTMutationListener *L = S.getASTMutationListener())
9399  L->AddedAttributeToRecord(BoxableAttr, RD);
9400  }
9401  }
9402 }
9403 
9404 static void handleObjCOwnershipAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9405  if (hasDeclarator(D))
9406  return;
9407 
9408  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
9409  << AL.getRange() << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
9410  << ExpectedVariable;
9411 }
9412 
9413 static void handleObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9414  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9415  const auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
9416  QualType QT = VD->getType();
9417 
9418  if (!QT->isDependentType() &&
9419  !QT->isObjCLifetimeType()) {
9420  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_precise_lifetime_bad_type)
9421  << QT;
9422  return;
9423  }
9424 
9425  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime = QT.getObjCLifetime();
9426 
9427  // If we have no lifetime yet, check the lifetime we're presumably
9428  // going to infer.
9429  if (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_None && !QT->isDependentType())
9430  Lifetime = QT->getObjCARCImplicitLifetime();
9431 
9432  switch (Lifetime) {
9433  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
9434  assert(QT->isDependentType() &&
9435  "didn't infer lifetime for non-dependent type?");
9436  break;
9437 
9438  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: // meaningful
9439  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: // meaningful
9440  break;
9441 
9442  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
9443  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
9444  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_objc_precise_lifetime_meaningless)
9445  << (Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing);
9446  break;
9447  }
9448 
9449  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ObjCPreciseLifetimeAttr(S.Context, AL));
9450 }

9452 static void handleSwiftAttrAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9453  // Make sure that there is a string literal as the annotation's single
9454  // argument.
9455  StringRef Str;
9456  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
9457  return;
9458 
9459  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftAttrAttr(S.Context, AL, Str));
9460 }
9461 
9462 static void handleSwiftBridge(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9463  // Make sure that there is a string literal as the annotation's single
9464  // argument.
9465  StringRef BT;
9466  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, BT))
9467  return;
9468 
9469  // Warn about duplicate attributes if they have different arguments, but drop
9470  // any duplicate attributes regardless.
9471  if (const auto *Other = D->getAttr<SwiftBridgeAttr>()) {
9472  if (Other->getSwiftType() != BT)
9473  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute) << AL;
9474  return;
9475  }
9476 
9477  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftBridgeAttr(S.Context, AL, BT));
9478 }
9479 
9480 static bool isErrorParameter(Sema &S, QualType QT) {
9481  const auto *PT = QT->getAs<PointerType>();
9482  if (!PT)
9483  return false;
9484 
9485  QualType Pointee = PT->getPointeeType();
9486 
9487  // Check for NSError**.
9488  if (const auto *OPT = Pointee->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>())
9489  if (const auto *ID = OPT->getInterfaceDecl())
9490  if (ID->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent())
9491  return true;
9492 
9493  // Check for CFError**.
9494  if (const auto *PT = Pointee->getAs<PointerType>())
9495  if (const auto *RT = PT->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>())
9496  if (S.isCFError(RT->getDecl()))
9497  return true;
9498 
9499  return false;
9500 }
9501 
9502 static void handleSwiftError(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9503  auto hasErrorParameter = [](Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) -> bool {
9504  for (unsigned I = 0, E = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D); I != E; ++I) {
9505  if (isErrorParameter(S, getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, I)))
9506  return true;
9507  }
9508 
9509  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attr_swift_error_no_error_parameter)
9510  << AL << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
9511  return false;
9512  };
9513 
9514  auto hasPointerResult = [](Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) -> bool {
9515  // - C, ObjC, and block pointers are definitely okay.
9516  // - References are definitely not okay.
9517  // - nullptr_t is weird, but acceptable.
9518  QualType RT = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
9519  if (RT->hasPointerRepresentation() && !RT->isReferenceType())
9520  return true;
9521 
9522  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attr_swift_error_return_type)
9523  << AL << AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident->getName() << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)
9524  << /*pointer*/ 1;
9525  return false;
9526  };
9527 
9528  auto hasIntegerResult = [](Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) -> bool {
9529  QualType RT = getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D);
9530  if (RT->isIntegralType(S.Context))
9531  return true;
9532 
9533  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attr_swift_error_return_type)
9534  << AL << AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident->getName() << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)
9535  << /*integral*/ 0;
9536  return false;
9537  };
9538 
9539  if (D->isInvalidDecl())
9540  return;
9541 
9542  IdentifierLoc *Loc = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
9543  SwiftErrorAttr::ConventionKind Convention;
9544  if (!SwiftErrorAttr::ConvertStrToConventionKind(Loc->Ident->getName(),
9545  Convention)) {
9546  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
9547  << AL << Loc->Ident;
9548  return;
9549  }
9550 
9551  switch (Convention) {
9552  case SwiftErrorAttr::None:
9553  // No additional validation required.
9554  break;
9555 
9556  case SwiftErrorAttr::NonNullError:
9557  if (!hasErrorParameter(S, D, AL))
9558  return;
9559  break;
9560 
9561  case SwiftErrorAttr::NullResult:
9562  if (!hasErrorParameter(S, D, AL) || !hasPointerResult(S, D, AL))
9563  return;
9564  break;
9565 
9566  case SwiftErrorAttr::NonZeroResult:
9567  case SwiftErrorAttr::ZeroResult:
9568  if (!hasErrorParameter(S, D, AL) || !hasIntegerResult(S, D, AL))
9569  return;
9570  break;
9571  }
9572 
9573  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftErrorAttr(S.Context, AL, Convention));
9574 }
9575 
9576 static void checkSwiftAsyncErrorBlock(Sema &S, Decl *D,
9577  const SwiftAsyncErrorAttr *ErrorAttr,
9578  const SwiftAsyncAttr *AsyncAttr) {
9579  if (AsyncAttr->getKind() == SwiftAsyncAttr::None) {
9580  if (ErrorAttr->getConvention() != SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::None) {
9581  S.Diag(AsyncAttr->getLocation(),
9582  diag::err_swift_async_error_without_swift_async)
9583  << AsyncAttr << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
9584  }
9585  return;
9586  }
9587 
9588  const ParmVarDecl *HandlerParam = getFunctionOrMethodParam(
9589  D, AsyncAttr->getCompletionHandlerIndex().getASTIndex());
9590  // handleSwiftAsyncAttr already verified the type is correct, so no need to
9591  // double-check it here.
9592  const auto *FuncTy = HandlerParam->getType()
9593  ->castAs<BlockPointerType>()
9594  ->getPointeeType()
9595  ->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
9596  ArrayRef<QualType> BlockParams;
9597  if (FuncTy)
9598  BlockParams = FuncTy->getParamTypes();
9599 
9600  switch (ErrorAttr->getConvention()) {
9601  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::ZeroArgument:
9602  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::NonZeroArgument: {
9603  uint32_t ParamIdx = ErrorAttr->getHandlerParamIdx();
9604  if (ParamIdx == 0 || ParamIdx > BlockParams.size()) {
9605  S.Diag(ErrorAttr->getLocation(),
9606  diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds) << ErrorAttr << 2;
9607  return;
9608  }
9609  QualType ErrorParam = BlockParams[ParamIdx - 1];
9610  if (!ErrorParam->isIntegralType(S.Context)) {
9611  StringRef ConvStr =
9612  ErrorAttr->getConvention() == SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::ZeroArgument
9613  ? "zero_argument"
9614  : "nonzero_argument";
9615  S.Diag(ErrorAttr->getLocation(), diag::err_swift_async_error_non_integral)
9616  << ErrorAttr << ConvStr << ParamIdx << ErrorParam;
9617  return;
9618  }
9619  break;
9620  }
9621  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::NonNullError: {
9622  bool AnyErrorParams = false;
9623  for (QualType Param : BlockParams) {
9624  // Check for NSError *.
9625  if (const auto *ObjCPtrTy = Param->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
9626  if (const auto *ID = ObjCPtrTy->getInterfaceDecl()) {
9627  if (ID->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent()) {
9628  AnyErrorParams = true;
9629  break;
9630  }
9631  }
9632  }
9633  // Check for CFError *.
9634  if (const auto *PtrTy = Param->getAs<PointerType>()) {
9635  if (const auto *RT = PtrTy->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
9636  if (S.isCFError(RT->getDecl())) {
9637  AnyErrorParams = true;
9638  break;
9639  }
9640  }
9641  }
9642  }
9643 
9644  if (!AnyErrorParams) {
9645  S.Diag(ErrorAttr->getLocation(),
9646  diag::err_swift_async_error_no_error_parameter)
9647  << ErrorAttr << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
9648  return;
9649  }
9650  break;
9651  }
9652  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::None:
9653  break;
9654  }
9655 }
9656 
9657 static void handleSwiftAsyncError(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9658  IdentifierLoc *IDLoc = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
9659  SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::ConventionKind ConvKind;
9660  if (!SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::ConvertStrToConventionKind(IDLoc->Ident->getName(),
9661  ConvKind)) {
9662  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
9663  << AL << IDLoc->Ident;
9664  return;
9665  }
9666 
9667  uint32_t ParamIdx = 0;
9668  switch (ConvKind) {
9669  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::ZeroArgument:
9670  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::NonZeroArgument: {
9671  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 2))
9672  return;
9673 
9674  Expr *IdxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
9675  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, IdxExpr, ParamIdx))
9676  return;
9677  break;
9678  }
9679  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::NonNullError:
9680  case SwiftAsyncErrorAttr::None: {
9681  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
9682  return;
9683  break;
9684  }
9685  }
9686 
9687  auto *ErrorAttr =
9688  ::new (S.Context) SwiftAsyncErrorAttr(S.Context, AL, ConvKind, ParamIdx);
9689  D->addAttr(ErrorAttr);
9690 
9691  if (auto *AsyncAttr = D->getAttr<SwiftAsyncAttr>())
9692  checkSwiftAsyncErrorBlock(S, D, ErrorAttr, AsyncAttr);
9693 }
9694 
9695 // For a function, this will validate a compound Swift name, e.g.
9696 // <code>init(foo:bar:baz:)</code> or <code>controllerForName(_:)</code>, and
9697 // the function will output the number of parameter names, and whether this is a
9698 // single-arg initializer.
9699 //
9700 // For a type, enum constant, property, or variable declaration, this will
9701 // validate either a simple identifier, or a qualified
9702 // <code>context.identifier</code> name.
9703 static bool
9704 validateSwiftFunctionName(Sema &S, const ParsedAttr &AL, SourceLocation Loc,
9705  StringRef Name, unsigned &SwiftParamCount,
9706  bool &IsSingleParamInit) {
9707  SwiftParamCount = 0;
9708  IsSingleParamInit = false;
9709 
9710  // Check whether this will be mapped to a getter or setter of a property.
9711  bool IsGetter = false, IsSetter = false;
9712  if (Name.consume_front("getter:"))
9713  IsGetter = true;
9714  else if (Name.consume_front("setter:"))
9715  IsSetter = true;
9716 
9717  if (Name.back() != ')') {
9718  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_function) << AL;
9719  return false;
9720  }
9721 
9722  bool IsMember = false;
9723  StringRef ContextName, BaseName, Parameters;
9724 
9725  std::tie(BaseName, Parameters) = Name.split('(');
9726 
9727  // Split at the first '.', if it exists, which separates the context name
9728  // from the base name.
9729  std::tie(ContextName, BaseName) = BaseName.split('.');
9730  if (BaseName.empty()) {
9731  BaseName = ContextName;
9732  ContextName = StringRef();
9733  } else if (ContextName.empty() || !isValidAsciiIdentifier(ContextName)) {
9734  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_invalid_identifier)
9735  << AL << /*context*/ 1;
9736  return false;
9737  } else {
9738  IsMember = true;
9739  }
9740 
9741  if (!isValidAsciiIdentifier(BaseName) || BaseName == "_") {
9742  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_invalid_identifier)
9743  << AL << /*basename*/ 0;
9744  return false;
9745  }
9746 
9747  bool IsSubscript = BaseName == "subscript";
9748  // A subscript accessor must be a getter or setter.
9749  if (IsSubscript && !IsGetter && !IsSetter) {
9750  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_invalid_parameter)
9751  << AL << /* getter or setter */ 0;
9752  return false;
9753  }
9754 
9755  if (Parameters.empty()) {
9756  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_missing_parameters) << AL;
9757  return false;
9758  }
9759 
9760  assert(Parameters.back() == ')' && "expected ')'");
9761  Parameters = Parameters.drop_back(); // ')'
9762 
9763  if (Parameters.empty()) {
9764  // Setters and subscripts must have at least one parameter.
9765  if (IsSubscript) {
9766  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_invalid_parameter)
9767  << AL << /* have at least one parameter */1;
9768  return false;
9769  }
9770 
9771  if (IsSetter) {
9772  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_setter_parameters) << AL;
9773  return false;
9774  }
9775 
9776  return true;
9777  }
9778 
9779  if (Parameters.back() != ':') {
9780  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_function) << AL;
9781  return false;
9782  }
9783 
9784  StringRef CurrentParam;
9785  std::optional<unsigned> SelfLocation;
9786  unsigned NewValueCount = 0;
9787  std::optional<unsigned> NewValueLocation;
9788  do {
9789  std::tie(CurrentParam, Parameters) = Parameters.split(':');
9790 
9791  if (!isValidAsciiIdentifier(CurrentParam)) {
9792  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_invalid_identifier)
9793  << AL << /*parameter*/2;
9794  return false;
9795  }
9796 
9797  if (IsMember && CurrentParam == "self") {
9798  // "self" indicates the "self" argument for a member.
9799 
9800  // More than one "self"?
9801  if (SelfLocation) {
9802  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_multiple_selfs) << AL;
9803  return false;
9804  }
9805 
9806  // The "self" location is the current parameter.
9807  SelfLocation = SwiftParamCount;
9808  } else if (CurrentParam == "newValue") {
9809  // "newValue" indicates the "newValue" argument for a setter.
9810 
9811  // There should only be one 'newValue', but it's only significant for
9812  // subscript accessors, so don't error right away.
9813  ++NewValueCount;
9814 
9815  NewValueLocation = SwiftParamCount;
9816  }
9817 
9818  ++SwiftParamCount;
9819  } while (!Parameters.empty());
9820 
9821  // Only instance subscripts are currently supported.
9822  if (IsSubscript && !SelfLocation) {
9823  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_invalid_parameter)
9824  << AL << /*have a 'self:' parameter*/2;
9825  return false;
9826  }
9827 
9828  IsSingleParamInit =
9829  SwiftParamCount == 1 && BaseName == "init" && CurrentParam != "_";
9830 
9831  // Check the number of parameters for a getter/setter.
9832  if (IsGetter || IsSetter) {
9833  // Setters have one parameter for the new value.
9834  unsigned NumExpectedParams = IsGetter ? 0 : 1;
9835  unsigned ParamDiag =
9836  IsGetter ? diag::warn_attr_swift_name_getter_parameters
9837  : diag::warn_attr_swift_name_setter_parameters;
9838 
9839  // Instance methods have one parameter for "self".
9840  if (SelfLocation)
9841  ++NumExpectedParams;
9842 
9843  // Subscripts may have additional parameters beyond the expected params for
9844  // the index.
9845  if (IsSubscript) {
9846  if (SwiftParamCount < NumExpectedParams) {
9847  S.Diag(Loc, ParamDiag) << AL;
9848  return false;
9849  }
9850 
9851  // A subscript setter must explicitly label its newValue parameter to
9852  // distinguish it from index parameters.
9853  if (IsSetter) {
9854  if (!NewValueLocation) {
9855  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_setter_no_newValue)
9856  << AL;
9857  return false;
9858  }
9859  if (NewValueCount > 1) {
9860  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_setter_multiple_newValues)
9861  << AL;
9862  return false;
9863  }
9864  } else {
9865  // Subscript getters should have no 'newValue:' parameter.
9866  if (NewValueLocation) {
9867  S.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_subscript_getter_newValue)
9868  << AL;
9869  return false;
9870  }
9871  }
9872  } else {
9873  // Property accessors must have exactly the number of expected params.
9874  if (SwiftParamCount != NumExpectedParams) {
9875  S.Diag(Loc, ParamDiag) << AL;
9876  return false;
9877  }
9878  }
9879  }
9880 
9881  return true;
9882 }
9883 
9884 bool Sema::DiagnoseSwiftName(Decl *D, StringRef Name, SourceLocation Loc,
9885  const ParsedAttr &AL, bool IsAsync) {
9886  if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) || isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
9887  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl*> Params;
9888  unsigned ParamCount;
9889 
9890  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
9891  ParamCount = Method->getSelector().getNumArgs();
9892  Params = Method->parameters().slice(0, ParamCount);
9893  } else {
9894  const auto *F = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
9895 
9896  ParamCount = F->getNumParams();
9897  Params = F->parameters();
9898 
9899  if (!F->hasWrittenPrototype()) {
9900  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
9901  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
9902  << ExpectedFunctionWithProtoType;
9903  return false;
9904  }
9905  }
9906 
9907  // The async name drops the last callback parameter.
9908  if (IsAsync) {
9909  if (ParamCount == 0) {
9910  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_decl_missing_params)
9911  << AL << isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
9912  return false;
9913  }
9914  ParamCount -= 1;
9915  }
9916 
9917  unsigned SwiftParamCount;
9918  bool IsSingleParamInit;
9919  if (!validateSwiftFunctionName(*this, AL, Loc, Name,
9920  SwiftParamCount, IsSingleParamInit))
9921  return false;
9922 
9923  bool ParamCountValid;
9924  if (SwiftParamCount == ParamCount) {
9925  ParamCountValid = true;
9926  } else if (SwiftParamCount > ParamCount) {
9927  ParamCountValid = IsSingleParamInit && ParamCount == 0;
9928  } else {
9929  // We have fewer Swift parameters than Objective-C parameters, but that
9930  // might be because we've transformed some of them. Check for potential
9931  // "out" parameters and err on the side of not warning.
9932  unsigned MaybeOutParamCount =
9933  llvm::count_if(Params, [](const ParmVarDecl *Param) -> bool {
9934  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
9935  if (ParamTy->isReferenceType() || ParamTy->isPointerType())
9936  return !ParamTy->getPointeeType().isConstQualified();
9937  return false;
9938  });
9939 
9940  ParamCountValid = SwiftParamCount + MaybeOutParamCount >= ParamCount;
9941  }
9942 
9943  if (!ParamCountValid) {
9944  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_num_params)
9945  << (SwiftParamCount > ParamCount) << AL << ParamCount
9946  << SwiftParamCount;
9947  return false;
9948  }
9949  } else if ((isa<EnumConstantDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D) ||
9950  isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D) ||
9951  isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D) || isa<TagDecl>(D) ||
9952  isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(D) || isa<FieldDecl>(D)) &&
9953  !IsAsync) {
9954  StringRef ContextName, BaseName;
9955 
9956  std::tie(ContextName, BaseName) = Name.split('.');
9957  if (BaseName.empty()) {
9958  BaseName = ContextName;
9959  ContextName = StringRef();
9960  } else if (!isValidAsciiIdentifier(ContextName)) {
9961  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_invalid_identifier) << AL
9962  << /*context*/1;
9963  return false;
9964  }
9965 
9966  if (!isValidAsciiIdentifier(BaseName)) {
9967  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_invalid_identifier) << AL
9968  << /*basename*/0;
9969  return false;
9970  }
9971  } else {
9972  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_attr_swift_name_decl_kind) << AL;
9973  return false;
9974  }
9975  return true;
9976 }
9977 
9978 static void handleSwiftName(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9979  StringRef Name;
9980  SourceLocation Loc;
9981  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Name, &Loc))
9982  return;
9983 
9984  if (!S.DiagnoseSwiftName(D, Name, Loc, AL, /*IsAsync=*/false))
9985  return;
9986 
9987  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftNameAttr(S.Context, AL, Name));
9988 }
9989 
9990 static void handleSwiftAsyncName(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
9991  StringRef Name;
9992  SourceLocation Loc;
9993  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Name, &Loc))
9994  return;
9995 
9996  if (!S.DiagnoseSwiftName(D, Name, Loc, AL, /*IsAsync=*/true))
9997  return;
9998 
9999  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftAsyncNameAttr(S.Context, AL, Name));
10000 }
10001 
10002 static void handleSwiftNewType(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10003  // Make sure that there is an identifier as the annotation's single argument.
10004  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
10005  return;
10006 
10007  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
10008  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10009  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
10010  return;
10011  }
10012 
10013  SwiftNewTypeAttr::NewtypeKind Kind;
10014  IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
10015  if (!SwiftNewTypeAttr::ConvertStrToNewtypeKind(II->getName(), Kind)) {
10016  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << II;
10017  return;
10018  }
10019 
10020  if (!isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
10021  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type_str)
10022  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << "typedefs";
10023  return;
10024  }
10025 
10026  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) SwiftNewTypeAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind));
10027 }
10028 
10029 static void handleSwiftAsyncAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10030  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
10031  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_n_type)
10032  << AL << 1 << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
10033  return;
10034  }
10035 
10036  SwiftAsyncAttr::Kind Kind;
10037  IdentifierInfo *II = AL.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
10038  if (!SwiftAsyncAttr::ConvertStrToKind(II->getName(), Kind)) {
10039  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_swift_async_no_access) << AL << II;
10040  return;
10041  }
10042 
10043  ParamIdx Idx;
10044  if (Kind == SwiftAsyncAttr::None) {
10045  // If this is 'none', then there shouldn't be any additional arguments.
10046  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
10047  return;
10048  } else {
10049  // Non-none swift_async requires a completion handler index argument.
10050  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 2))
10051  return;
10052 
10053  Expr *HandlerIdx = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
10054  if (!checkFunctionOrMethodParameterIndex(S, D, AL, 2, HandlerIdx, Idx))
10055  return;
10056 
10057  const ParmVarDecl *CompletionBlock =
10058  getFunctionOrMethodParam(D, Idx.getASTIndex());
10059  QualType CompletionBlockType = CompletionBlock->getType();
10060  if (!CompletionBlockType->isBlockPointerType()) {
10061  S.Diag(CompletionBlock->getLocation(),
10062  diag::err_swift_async_bad_block_type)
10063  << CompletionBlock->getType();
10064  return;
10065  }
10066  QualType BlockTy =
10067  CompletionBlockType->castAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
10068  if (!BlockTy->castAs<FunctionType>()->getReturnType()->isVoidType()) {
10069  S.Diag(CompletionBlock->getLocation(),
10070  diag::err_swift_async_bad_block_type)
10071  << CompletionBlock->getType();
10072  return;
10073  }
10074  }
10075 
10076  auto *AsyncAttr =
10077  ::new (S.Context) SwiftAsyncAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind, Idx);
10078  D->addAttr(AsyncAttr);
10079 
10080  if (auto *ErrorAttr = D->getAttr<SwiftAsyncErrorAttr>())
10081  checkSwiftAsyncErrorBlock(S, D, ErrorAttr, AsyncAttr);
10082 }
10083 
10084 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10085 // Microsoft specific attribute handlers.
10086 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10087 
10088 UuidAttr *Sema::mergeUuidAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
10089  StringRef UuidAsWritten, MSGuidDecl *GuidDecl) {
10090  if (const auto *UA = D->getAttr<UuidAttr>()) {
10091  if (declaresSameEntity(UA->getGuidDecl(), GuidDecl))
10092  return nullptr;
10093  if (!UA->getGuid().empty()) {
10094  Diag(UA->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_uuid);
10095  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_uuid);
10096  D->dropAttr<UuidAttr>();
10097  }
10098  }
10099 
10100  return ::new (Context) UuidAttr(Context, CI, UuidAsWritten, GuidDecl);
10101 }
10102 
10103 static void handleUuidAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10104  if (!S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus) {
10105  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_in_lang)
10106  << AL << AttributeLangSupport::C;
10107  return;
10108  }
10109 
10110  StringRef OrigStrRef;
10111  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
10112  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, OrigStrRef, &LiteralLoc))
10113  return;
10114 
10115  // GUID format is "XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX" or
10116  // "{XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX}", normalize to the former.
10117  StringRef StrRef = OrigStrRef;
10118  if (StrRef.size() == 38 && StrRef.front() == '{' && StrRef.back() == '}')
10119  StrRef = StrRef.drop_front().drop_back();
10120 
10121  // Validate GUID length.
10122  if (StrRef.size() != 36) {
10123  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
10124  return;
10125  }
10126 
10127  for (unsigned i = 0; i < 36; ++i) {
10128  if (i == 8 || i == 13 || i == 18 || i == 23) {
10129  if (StrRef[i] != '-') {
10130  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
10131  return;
10132  }
10133  } else if (!isHexDigit(StrRef[i])) {
10134  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::err_attribute_uuid_malformed_guid);
10135  return;
10136  }
10137  }
10138 
10139  // Convert to our parsed format and canonicalize.
10140  MSGuidDecl::Parts Parsed;
10141  StrRef.substr(0, 8).getAsInteger(16, Parsed.Part1);
10142  StrRef.substr(9, 4).getAsInteger(16, Parsed.Part2);
10143  StrRef.substr(14, 4).getAsInteger(16, Parsed.Part3);
10144  for (unsigned i = 0; i != 8; ++i)
10145  StrRef.substr(19 + 2 * i + (i >= 2 ? 1 : 0), 2)
10146  .getAsInteger(16, Parsed.Part4And5[i]);
10147  MSGuidDecl *Guid = S.Context.getMSGuidDecl(Parsed);
10148 
10149  // FIXME: It'd be nice to also emit a fixit removing uuid(...) (and, if it's
10150  // the only thing in the [] list, the [] too), and add an insertion of
10151  // __declspec(uuid(...)). But sadly, neither the SourceLocs of the commas
10152  // separating attributes nor of the [ and the ] are in the AST.
10153  // Cf "SourceLocations of attribute list delimiters - [[ ... , ... ]] etc"
10154  // on cfe-dev.
10155  if (AL.isMicrosoftAttribute()) // Check for [uuid(...)] spelling.
10156  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_atl_uuid_deprecated);
10157 
10158  UuidAttr *UA = S.mergeUuidAttr(D, AL, OrigStrRef, Guid);
10159  if (UA)
10160  D->addAttr(UA);
10161 }
10162 
10163 static void handleHLSLNumThreadsAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10164  llvm::VersionTuple SMVersion =
10165  S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getOSVersion();
10166  uint32_t ZMax = 1024;
10167  uint32_t ThreadMax = 1024;
10168  if (SMVersion.getMajor() <= 4) {
10169  ZMax = 1;
10170  ThreadMax = 768;
10171  } else if (SMVersion.getMajor() == 5) {
10172  ZMax = 64;
10173  ThreadMax = 1024;
10174  }
10175 
10176  uint32_t X;
10177  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), X))
10178  return;
10179  if (X > 1024) {
10180  S.Diag(AL.getArgAsExpr(0)->getExprLoc(),
10181  diag::err_hlsl_numthreads_argument_oor) << 0 << 1024;
10182  return;
10183  }
10184  uint32_t Y;
10185  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(1), Y))
10186  return;
10187  if (Y > 1024) {
10188  S.Diag(AL.getArgAsExpr(1)->getExprLoc(),
10189  diag::err_hlsl_numthreads_argument_oor) << 1 << 1024;
10190  return;
10191  }
10192  uint32_t Z;
10193  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(2), Z))
10194  return;
10195  if (Z > ZMax) {
10196  S.Diag(AL.getArgAsExpr(2)->getExprLoc(),
10197  diag::err_hlsl_numthreads_argument_oor) << 2 << ZMax;
10198  return;
10199  }
10200 
10201  if (X * Y * Z > ThreadMax) {
10202  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_hlsl_numthreads_invalid) << ThreadMax;
10203  return;
10204  }
10205 
10206  HLSLNumThreadsAttr *NewAttr = S.HLSL().mergeNumThreadsAttr(D, AL, X, Y, Z);
10207  if (NewAttr)
10208  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
10209 }

10211 static bool isLegalTypeForHLSLSV_DispatchThreadID(QualType T) {
10212  if (!T->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
10213  return false;
10214  if (const auto *VT = T->getAs<VectorType>())
10215  return VT->getNumElements() <= 3;
10216  return true;
10217 }

10219 static void handleHLSLSV_DispatchThreadIDAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
10220  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10221  // FIXME: support semantic on field.
10222  // See https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/57889.
10223  if (isa<FieldDecl>(D)) {
10224  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_hlsl_attr_invalid_ast_node)
10225  << AL << "parameter";
10226  return;
10227  }
10228 
10229  auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
10230  if (!isLegalTypeForHLSLSV_DispatchThreadID(VD->getType())) {
10231  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_hlsl_attr_invalid_type)
10232  << AL << "uint/uint2/uint3";
10233  return;
10234  }
10235 
10236  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) HLSLSV_DispatchThreadIDAttr(S.Context, AL));
10237 }

10239 static void handleHLSLShaderAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10240  StringRef Str;
10241  SourceLocation ArgLoc;
10242  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
10243  return;

10246  if (!HLSLShaderAttr::ConvertStrToShaderType(Str, ShaderType)) {
10247  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)

10250  }

10255  if (NewAttr)

10259 static void handleHLSLResourceBindingAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
10260  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10261  StringRef Space = "space0";
10262  StringRef Slot = "";
10263 
10264  if (!AL.isArgIdent(0)) {
10265  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10266  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
10267  return;
10268  }
10269 
10270  IdentifierLoc *Loc = AL.getArgAsIdent(0);
10271  StringRef Str = Loc->Ident->getName();
10272  SourceLocation ArgLoc = Loc->Loc;
10273 
10274  SourceLocation SpaceArgLoc;
10275  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 2) {
10276  Slot = Str;
10277  if (!AL.isArgIdent(1)) {
10278  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10279  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIdentifier;
10280  return;
10281  }
10282 
10283  IdentifierLoc *Loc = AL.getArgAsIdent(1);
10284  Space = Loc->Ident->getName();
10285  SpaceArgLoc = Loc->Loc;
10286  } else {
10287  Slot = Str;
10288  }
10289 
10290  // Validate.
10291  if (!Slot.empty()) {
10292  switch (Slot[0]) {
10293  case 'u':
10294  case 'b':
10295  case 's':
10296  case 't':
10297  break;
10298  default:
10299  S.Diag(ArgLoc, diag::err_hlsl_unsupported_register_type)
10300  << Slot.substr(0, 1);
10301  return;
10302  }
10303 
10304  StringRef SlotNum = Slot.substr(1);
10305  unsigned Num = 0;
10306  if (SlotNum.getAsInteger(10, Num)) {
10307  S.Diag(ArgLoc, diag::err_hlsl_unsupported_register_number);
10308  return;
10309  }
10310  }
10311 
10312  if (!Space.starts_with("space")) {
10313  S.Diag(SpaceArgLoc, diag::err_hlsl_expected_space) << Space;
10314  return;
10315  }
10316  StringRef SpaceNum = Space.substr(5);
10317  unsigned Num = 0;
10318  if (SpaceNum.getAsInteger(10, Num)) {
10319  S.Diag(SpaceArgLoc, diag::err_hlsl_expected_space) << Space;
10320  return;
10321  }
10322 
10323  // FIXME: check reg type match decl. Issue
10324  // https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/57886.
10325  HLSLResourceBindingAttr *NewAttr =
10326  HLSLResourceBindingAttr::Create(S.getASTContext(), Slot, Space, AL);
10327  if (NewAttr)
10328  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
10329 }

10334  D, AL,
10335  static_cast<HLSLParamModifierAttr::Spelling>(AL.getSemanticSpelling()));
10336  if (NewAttr)
10337  D->addAttr(NewAttr);

10340 static void handleMSInheritanceAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10341  if (!S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus) {
10342  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_supported_in_lang)
10343  << AL << AttributeLangSupport::C;

10354 static void handleDeclspecThreadAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10355  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
10356  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().isTLSSupported()) {
10357  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_thread_unsupported);
10358  return;
10359  }
10360  if (VD->getTSCSpec() != TSCS_unspecified) {
10361  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_declspec_thread_on_thread_variable);
10362  return;
10363  }
10364  if (VD->hasLocalStorage()) {
10365  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_thread_non_global) << "__declspec(thread)";
10366  return;
10367  }
10368  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ThreadAttr(S.Context, AL));
10369 }

10371 static void handleMSConstexprAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10372  if (!S.getLangOpts().isCompatibleWithMSVC(LangOptions::MSVC2022_3)) {
10373  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_unknown_attribute_ignored)
10374  << AL << AL.getRange();
10375  return;
10376  }
10377  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
10378  if (FD->isConstexprSpecified() || FD->isConsteval()) {
10379  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_ms_constexpr_cannot_be_applied)
10380  << FD->isConsteval() << FD;
10381  return;
10382  }
10383  if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
10384  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 && MD->isVirtual()) {
10385  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_ms_constexpr_cannot_be_applied)
10386  << /*virtual*/ 2 << MD;
10387  return;
10388  }
10389  }
10390  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MSConstexprAttr(S.Context, AL));
10391 }

10393 static void handleAbiTagAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10394  SmallVector<StringRef, 4> Tags;
10395  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
10396  StringRef Tag;
10397  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, Tag))
10398  return;
10399  Tags.push_back(Tag);
10400  }
10401 
10402  if (const auto *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
10403  if (!NS->isInline()) {
10404  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attr_abi_tag_namespace) << 0;
10405  return;
10406  }
10407  if (NS->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
10408  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attr_abi_tag_namespace) << 1;
10409  return;
10410  }
10411  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
10412  Tags.push_back(NS->getName());
10413  } else if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
10414  return;
10415 
10416  // Store tags sorted and without duplicates.
10417  llvm::sort(Tags);
10418  Tags.erase(std::unique(Tags.begin(), Tags.end()), Tags.end());
10419 
10420  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
10421  AbiTagAttr(S.Context, AL, Tags.data(), Tags.size()));
10422 }

10424 static void handleARMInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10425  // Check the attribute arguments.
10426  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
10427  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_many_arguments) << AL << 1;
10428  return;
10429  }
10430 
10431  StringRef Str;
10432  SourceLocation ArgLoc;
10433 
10434  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
10435  Str = "";
10436  else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
10437  return;
10438 
10439  ARMInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
10440  if (!ARMInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
10441  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << Str
10442  << ArgLoc;
10443  return;
10444  }
10445 
10446  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ARMInterruptAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind));
10447 }
10448 
10449 static void handleMSP430InterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10450  // MSP430 'interrupt' attribute is applied to
10451  // a function with no parameters and void return type.
10452  if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
10453  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
10454  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
10455  return;
10456  }
10457 
10458  if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
10459  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10460  << /*MSP430*/ 1 << 0;
10461  return;
10462  }
10463 
10464  if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
10465  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10466  << /*MSP430*/ 1 << 1;
10467  return;
10468  }
10469 
10470  // The attribute takes one integer argument.
10471  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
10472  return;
10473 
10474  if (!AL.isArgExpr(0)) {
10475  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10476  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant;
10477  return;
10478  }
10479 
10480  Expr *NumParamsExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
10481  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> NumParams = llvm::APSInt(32);
10482  if (!(NumParams = NumParamsExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context))) {
10483  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10484  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
10485  << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
10486  return;
10487  }
10488  // The argument should be in range 0..63.
10489  unsigned Num = NumParams->getLimitedValue(255);
10490  if (Num > 63) {
10491  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
10492  << AL << (int)NumParams->getSExtValue()
10493  << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
10494  return;
10495  }
10496 
10497  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MSP430InterruptAttr(S.Context, AL, Num));
10498  D->addAttr(UsedAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
10499 }
10500 
10501 static void handleMipsInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10502  // Only one optional argument permitted.
10503  if (AL.getNumArgs() > 1) {
10504  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_many_arguments) << AL << 1;
10505  return;
10506  }
10507 
10508  StringRef Str;
10509  SourceLocation ArgLoc;
10510 
10511  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
10512  Str = "";
10513  else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
10514  return;
10515 
10516  // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute for MIPS:
10517  // a) Must be a function.
10518  // b) Must have no parameters.
10519  // c) Must have the 'void' return type.
10520  // d) Cannot have the 'mips16' attribute, as that instruction set
10521  // lacks the 'eret' instruction.
10522  // e) The attribute itself must either have no argument or one of the
10523  // valid interrupt types, see [MipsInterruptDocs].
10524 
10525  if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
10526  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
10527  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunctionOrMethod;
10528  return;
10529  }
10530 
10531  if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
10532  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10533  << /*MIPS*/ 0 << 0;
10534  return;
10535  }
10536 
10537  if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
10538  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10539  << /*MIPS*/ 0 << 1;
10540  return;
10541  }
10542 
10543  // We still have to do this manually because the Interrupt attributes are
10544  // a bit special due to sharing their spellings across targets.
10545  if (checkAttrMutualExclusion<Mips16Attr>(S, D, AL))
10546  return;
10547 
10548  MipsInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
10549  if (!MipsInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
10550  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
10551  << AL << "'" + std::string(Str) + "'";
10552  return;
10553  }
10554 
10555  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) MipsInterruptAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind));
10556 }
10557 
10558 static void handleM68kInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10559  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 1))
10560  return;
10561 
10562  if (!AL.isArgExpr(0)) {
10563  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10564  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant;
10565  return;
10566  }
10567 
10568  // FIXME: Check for decl - it should be void ()(void).
10569 
10570  Expr *NumParamsExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
10571  auto MaybeNumParams = NumParamsExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context);
10572  if (!MaybeNumParams) {
10573  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
10574  << AL << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
10575  << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
10576  return;
10577  }
10578 
10579  unsigned Num = MaybeNumParams->getLimitedValue(255);
10580  if ((Num & 1) || Num > 30) {
10581  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
10582  << AL << (int)MaybeNumParams->getSExtValue()
10583  << NumParamsExpr->getSourceRange();
10584  return;
10585  }
10586 
10587  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) M68kInterruptAttr(S.Context, AL, Num));
10588  D->addAttr(UsedAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
10589 }
10590 
10591 static void handleAnyX86InterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10592  // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute.
10593  // a) Must be a function.
10594  // b) Must have the 'void' return type.
10595  // c) Must take 1 or 2 arguments.
10596  // d) The 1st argument must be a pointer.
10597  // e) The 2nd argument (if any) must be an unsigned integer.
10598  if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D) || !hasFunctionProto(D) || isInstanceMethod(D) ||
10599  CXXMethodDecl::isStaticOverloadedOperator(
10600  cast<NamedDecl>(D)->getDeclName().getCXXOverloadedOperator())) {
10601  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
10602  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute()
10603  << ExpectedFunctionWithProtoType;
10604  return;
10605  }
10606  // Interrupt handler must have void return type.
10607  if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
10608  S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodResultSourceRange(D).getBegin(),
10609  diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
10610  << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
10611  ? 0
10612  : 1)
10613  << 0;
10614  return;
10615  }
10616  // Interrupt handler must have 1 or 2 parameters.
10617  unsigned NumParams = getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D);
10618  if (NumParams < 1 || NumParams > 2) {
10619  S.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
10620  << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
10621  ? 0
10622  : 1)
10623  << 1;
10624  return;
10625  }
10626  // The first argument must be a pointer.
10627  if (!getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 0)->isPointerType()) {
10628  S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 0).getBegin(),
10629  diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
10630  << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
10631  ? 0
10632  : 1)
10633  << 2;
10634  return;
10635  }
10636  // The second argument, if present, must be an unsigned integer.
10637  unsigned TypeSize =
10638  S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86_64
10639  ? 64
10640  : 32;
10641  if (NumParams == 2 &&
10642  (!getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 1)->isUnsignedIntegerType() ||
10643  S.Context.getTypeSize(getFunctionOrMethodParamType(D, 1)) != TypeSize)) {
10644  S.Diag(getFunctionOrMethodParamRange(D, 1).getBegin(),
10645  diag::err_anyx86_interrupt_attribute)
10646  << (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86
10647  ? 0
10648  : 1)
10649  << 3 << S.Context.getIntTypeForBitwidth(TypeSize, /*Signed=*/false);
10650  return;
10651  }
10652  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AnyX86InterruptAttr(S.Context, AL));
10653  D->addAttr(UsedAttr::CreateImplicit(S.Context));
10654 }
10655 
10656 static void handleAVRInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10657  if (!isFunctionOrMethod(D)) {
10658  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
10659  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunction;
10660  return;
10661  }
10662 
10663  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 0))
10664  return;
10665 
10666  handleSimpleAttribute<AVRInterruptAttr>(S, D, AL);
10667 }

10674  }

10676  if (!AL.checkExactlyNumArgs(S, 0))
10677  return;
10678 
10679  handleSimpleAttribute<AVRSignalAttr>(S, D, AL);
10680 }

10748 WebAssemblyImportModuleAttr *
10749 Sema::mergeImportModuleAttr(Decl *D, const WebAssemblyImportModuleAttr &AL) {
10750  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
10751 
10752  if (const auto *ExistingAttr = FD->getAttr<WebAssemblyImportModuleAttr>()) {
10753  if (ExistingAttr->getImportModule() == AL.getImportModule())
10754  return nullptr;
10755  Diag(ExistingAttr->getLocation(), diag::warn_mismatched_import) << 0
10756  << ExistingAttr->getImportModule() << AL.getImportModule();

10758  return nullptr;
10759  }
10760  if (FD->hasBody()) {
10761  Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_import_on_definition) << 0;
10762  return nullptr;
10763  }
10764  return ::new (Context) WebAssemblyImportModuleAttr(Context, AL,
10765  AL.getImportModule());
10766 }

10776  << ExistingAttr->getImportName() << AL.getImportName();

10820 
10821 static void handleRISCVInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
10822  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10823  // Warn about repeated attributes.
10824  if (const auto *A = D->getAttr<RISCVInterruptAttr>()) {
10825  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(),
10826  diag::warn_riscv_repeated_interrupt_attribute);
10827  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::note_riscv_repeated_interrupt_attribute);
10828  return;
10829  }
10830 
10831  // Check the attribute argument. Argument is optional.
10832  if (!AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 1))
10833  return;
10834 
10835  StringRef Str;
10836  SourceLocation ArgLoc;
10837 
10838  // 'machine'is the default interrupt mode.
10839  if (AL.getNumArgs() == 0)
10840  Str = "machine";
10841  else if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str, &ArgLoc))
10842  return;
10843 
10844  // Semantic checks for a function with the 'interrupt' attribute:
10845  // - Must be a function.
10846  // - Must have no parameters.
10847  // - Must have the 'void' return type.
10848  // - The attribute itself must either have no argument or one of the
10849  // valid interrupt types, see [RISCVInterruptDocs].
10850 
10851  if (D->getFunctionType() == nullptr) {
10852  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
10853  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunction;
10854  return;
10855  }
10856 
10857  if (hasFunctionProto(D) && getFunctionOrMethodNumParams(D) != 0) {
10858  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10859  << /*RISC-V*/ 2 << 0;
10860  return;
10861  }
10862 
10863  if (!getFunctionOrMethodResultType(D)->isVoidType()) {
10864  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_interrupt_attribute_invalid)
10865  << /*RISC-V*/ 2 << 1;
10866  return;
10867  }
10868 
10869  RISCVInterruptAttr::InterruptType Kind;
10870  if (!RISCVInterruptAttr::ConvertStrToInterruptType(Str, Kind)) {
10871  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << AL << Str
10872  << ArgLoc;
10873  return;
10874  }
10875 
10876  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) RISCVInterruptAttr(S.Context, AL, Kind));
10877 }
10878 
10879 static void handleInterruptAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
10880  // Dispatch the interrupt attribute based on the current target.
10881  switch (S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch()) {
10882  case llvm::Triple::msp430:
10883  handleMSP430InterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10884  break;
10885  case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
10886  case llvm::Triple::mips:
10887  handleMipsInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10888  break;
10889  case llvm::Triple::m68k:
10890  handleM68kInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10891  break;
10892  case llvm::Triple::x86:
10893  case llvm::Triple::x86_64:
10894  handleAnyX86InterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10895  break;
10896  case llvm::Triple::avr:
10897  handleAVRInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10898  break;
10899  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
10900  case llvm::Triple::riscv64:
10901  handleRISCVInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10902  break;
10903  default:
10904  handleARMInterruptAttr(S, D, AL);
10905  break;
10906  }
10907 }

10909 static bool
10910 checkAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeArguments(Sema &S, Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr,
10911  const AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr &Attr) {
10912  // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
10913  // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
10914  if (MinExpr->isValueDependent() || MaxExpr->isValueDependent())
10915  return false;
10916 
10917  uint32_t Min = 0;
10918  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MinExpr, Min, 0))
10919  return true;
10920 
10921  uint32_t Max = 0;
10922  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MaxExpr, Max, 1))
10923  return true;
10924 
10925  if (Min == 0 && Max != 0) {
10926  S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
10927  << &Attr << 0;
10928  return true;
10929  }
10930  if (Min > Max) {
10931  S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
10932  << &Attr << 1;
10933  return true;
10934  }
10935 
10936  return false;
10937 }
10938 
10939 AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr *
10940 Sema::CreateAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
10941  Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr) {
10942  AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
10943 
10944  if (checkAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeArguments(*this, MinExpr, MaxExpr, TmpAttr))
10945  return nullptr;
10946  return ::new (Context)
10947  AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(Context, CI, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
10948 }

10950 void Sema::addAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(Decl *D,
10951  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
10952  Expr *MinExpr, Expr *MaxExpr) {
10953  if (auto *Attr = CreateAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(CI, MinExpr, MaxExpr))
10954  D->addAttr(Attr);
10955 }

10959  Expr *MinExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(0);
10960  Expr *MaxExpr = AL.getArgAsExpr(1);
10961 
10962  S.addAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(D, AL, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
10963 }

10965 static bool checkAMDGPUWavesPerEUArguments(Sema &S, Expr *MinExpr,
10966  Expr *MaxExpr,
10967  const AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr &Attr) {
10968  if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(MinExpr) ||
10969  (MaxExpr && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(MaxExpr)))
10970  return true;
10971 
10972  // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
10973  // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
10974  if (MinExpr->isValueDependent() || (MaxExpr && MaxExpr->isValueDependent()))
10975  return false;
10976 
10977  uint32_t Min = 0;
10978  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MinExpr, Min, 0))
10979  return true;
10980 
10981  uint32_t Max = 0;
10982  if (MaxExpr && !checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, MaxExpr, Max, 1))
10983  return true;
10984 
10985  if (Min == 0 && Max != 0) {
10986  S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
10987  << &Attr << 0;
10988  return true;
10989  }
10990  if (Max != 0 && Min > Max) {
10991  S.Diag(Attr.getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_argument_invalid)
10992  << &Attr << 1;
10993  return true;
10994  }
10995 
10996  return false;
10997 }

11007  return ::new (Context) AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(Context, CI, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
11008 }

11044 static bool
11045 checkAMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsArguments(Sema &S, Expr *XExpr, Expr *YExpr,
11046  Expr *ZExpr,
11047  const AMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsAttr &Attr) {
11048  if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(XExpr) ||
11049  (YExpr && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(YExpr)) ||
11050  (ZExpr && S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(ZExpr)))
11051  return true;
11052 
11053  // Accept template arguments for now as they depend on something else.
11054  // We'll get to check them when they eventually get instantiated.
11055  if (XExpr->isValueDependent() || (YExpr && YExpr->isValueDependent()) ||
11056  (ZExpr && ZExpr->isValueDependent()))
11057  return false;
11058 
11059  uint32_t NumWG = 0;
11060  Expr *Exprs[3] = {XExpr, YExpr, ZExpr};
11061  for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
11062  if (Exprs[i]) {
11063  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, Attr, Exprs[i], NumWG, i,
11064  /*StrictlyUnsigned=*/true))
11065  return true;
11066  if (NumWG == 0) {
11067  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_is_zero)
11068  << &Attr << Exprs[i]->getSourceRange();
11069  return true;
11070  }
11071  }
11072  }
11073 
11074  return false;
11075 }

11077 AMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsAttr *
11078 Sema::CreateAMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsAttr(const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
11079  Expr *XExpr, Expr *YExpr, Expr *ZExpr) {
11080  AMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsAttr TmpAttr(Context, CI, XExpr, YExpr, ZExpr);
11081 
11082  if (checkAMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsArguments(*this, XExpr, YExpr, ZExpr, TmpAttr))
11083  return nullptr;
11084 
11085  return ::new (Context)
11086  AMDGPUMaxNumWorkGroupsAttr(Context, CI, XExpr, YExpr, ZExpr);
11087 }

11099  Expr *ZExpr = (AL.getNumArgs() > 2) ? AL.getArgAsExpr(2) : nullptr;

11103 static void handleX86ForceAlignArgPointerAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11104  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11105  // If we try to apply it to a function pointer, don't warn, but don't
11106  // do anything, either. It doesn't matter anyway, because there's nothing
11107  // special about calling a force_align_arg_pointer function.
11108  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D);
11109  if (VD && VD->getType()->isFunctionPointerType())
11110  return;
11111  // Also don't warn on function pointer typedefs.
11112  const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D);
11113  if (TD && (TD->getUnderlyingType()->isFunctionPointerType() ||
11114  TD->getUnderlyingType()->isFunctionType()))
11115  return;
11116  // Attribute can only be applied to function types.
11117  if (!isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
11118  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
11119  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunction;
11120  return;
11121  }
11122 
11123  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) X86ForceAlignArgPointerAttr(S.Context, AL));
11124 }
11125 
11126 static void handleLayoutVersion(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11127  uint32_t Version;
11128  Expr *VersionExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
11129  if (!checkUInt32Argument(S, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Version))
11130  return;
11131 
11132  // TODO: Investigate what happens with the next major version of MSVC.
11133  if (Version != LangOptions::MSVC2015 / 100) {
11134  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_out_of_bounds)
11135  << AL << Version << VersionExpr->getSourceRange();
11136  return;
11137  }
11138 
11139  // The attribute expects a "major" version number like 19, but new versions of
11140  // MSVC have moved to updating the "minor", or less significant numbers, so we
11141  // have to multiply by 100 now.
11142  Version *= 100;
11143 
11144  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) LayoutVersionAttr(S.Context, AL, Version));
11145 }
11146 
11147 DLLImportAttr *Sema::mergeDLLImportAttr(Decl *D,
11148  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
11149  if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) {
11150  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << "'dllimport'";
11151  return nullptr;
11152  }
11153 
11154  if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
11155  return nullptr;
11156 
11157  return ::new (Context) DLLImportAttr(Context, CI);
11158 }
11159 
11160 DLLExportAttr *Sema::mergeDLLExportAttr(Decl *D,
11161  const AttributeCommonInfo &CI) {
11162  if (DLLImportAttr *Import = D->getAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
11163  Diag(Import->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << Import;
11164  D->dropAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
11165  }
11166 
11167  if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
11168  return nullptr;
11169 
11170  return ::new (Context) DLLExportAttr(Context, CI);
11171 }
11172 
11173 static void handleDLLAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &A) {
11174  if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(D) &&
11175  (S.Context.getTargetInfo().shouldDLLImportComdatSymbols())) {
11176  S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << A;
11177  return;
11178  }
11179 
11180  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
11181  if (FD->isInlined() && A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_DLLImport &&
11182  !(S.Context.getTargetInfo().shouldDLLImportComdatSymbols())) {
11183  // MinGW doesn't allow dllimport on inline functions.
11184  S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored_on_inline)
11185  << A;
11186  return;
11187  }
11188  }
11189 
11190  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
11191  if ((S.Context.getTargetInfo().shouldDLLImportComdatSymbols()) &&
11192  MD->getParent()->isLambda()) {
11193  S.Diag(A.getRange().getBegin(), diag::err_attribute_dll_lambda) << A;
11194  return;
11195  }
11196  }
11197 
11198  Attr *NewAttr = A.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_DLLExport
11199  ? (Attr *)S.mergeDLLExportAttr(D, A)
11200  : (Attr *)S.mergeDLLImportAttr(D, A);
11201  if (NewAttr)
11202  D->addAttr(NewAttr);
11203 }
11204 
11205 MSInheritanceAttr *
11206 Sema::mergeMSInheritanceAttr(Decl *D, const AttributeCommonInfo &CI,
11207  bool BestCase,
11208  MSInheritanceModel Model) {
11209  if (MSInheritanceAttr *IA = D->getAttr<MSInheritanceAttr>()) {
11210  if (IA->getInheritanceModel() == Model)
11211  return nullptr;
11212  Diag(IA->getLocation(), diag::err_mismatched_ms_inheritance)
11213  << 1 /*previous declaration*/;
11214  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::note_previous_ms_inheritance);
11215  D->dropAttr<MSInheritanceAttr>();
11216  }
11217 
11218  auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
11219  if (RD->hasDefinition()) {
11220  if (checkMSInheritanceAttrOnDefinition(RD, CI.getRange(), BestCase,
11221  Model)) {
11222  return nullptr;
11223  }
11224  } else {
11225  if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
11226  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_ignored_ms_inheritance)
11227  << 1 /*partial specialization*/;
11228  return nullptr;
11229  }
11230  if (RD->getDescribedClassTemplate()) {
11231  Diag(CI.getLoc(), diag::warn_ignored_ms_inheritance)
11232  << 0 /*primary template*/;
11233  return nullptr;
11234  }
11235  }
11236 
11237  return ::new (Context) MSInheritanceAttr(Context, CI, BestCase);
11238 }
11239 
11240 static void handleCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11241  // The capability attributes take a single string parameter for the name of
11242  // the capability they represent. The lockable attribute does not take any
11243  // parameters. However, semantically, both attributes represent the same
11244  // concept, and so they use the same semantic attribute. Eventually, the
11245  // lockable attribute will be removed.
11246  //
11247  // For backward compatibility, any capability which has no specified string
11248  // literal will be considered a "mutex."
11249  StringRef N("mutex");
11250  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
11251  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Capability &&
11252  !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, N, &LiteralLoc))
11253  return;
11254 
11255  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) CapabilityAttr(S.Context, AL, N));
11256 }
11257 
11258 static void handleAssertCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11259  SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
11260  if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
11261  return;
11262 
11263  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
11264  AssertCapabilityAttr(S.Context, AL, Args.data(), Args.size()));
11265 }
11266 
11267 static void handleAcquireCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11268  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11269  SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
11270  if (!checkLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
11271  return;
11272 
11273  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) AcquireCapabilityAttr(S.Context, AL, Args.data(),
11274  Args.size()));
11275 }
11276 
11277 static void handleTryAcquireCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11278  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11279  SmallVector<Expr*, 2> Args;
11280  if (!checkTryLockFunAttrCommon(S, D, AL, Args))
11281  return;
11282 
11283  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) TryAcquireCapabilityAttr(
11284  S.Context, AL, AL.getArgAsExpr(0), Args.data(), Args.size()));
11285 }

11287 static void handleReleaseCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11288  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11289  // Check that all arguments are lockable objects.
11290  SmallVector<Expr *, 1> Args;
11291  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args, 0, true);
11292 
11293  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) ReleaseCapabilityAttr(S.Context, AL, Args.data(),
11294  Args.size()));
11295 }
11296 
11297 static void handleRequiresCapabilityAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11298  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11299  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
11300  return;
11301 
11302  // check that all arguments are lockable objects
11303  SmallVector<Expr*, 1> Args;
11304  checkAttrArgsAreCapabilityObjs(S, D, AL, Args);
11305  if (Args.empty())
11306  return;
11307 
11308  RequiresCapabilityAttr *RCA = ::new (S.Context)
11309  RequiresCapabilityAttr(S.Context, AL, Args.data(), Args.size());
11310 
11311  D->addAttr(RCA);
11312 }

11314 static void handleDeprecatedAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11315  if (const auto *NSD = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
11316  if (NSD->isAnonymousNamespace()) {
11317  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::warn_deprecated_anonymous_namespace);
11318  // Do not want to attach the attribute to the namespace because that will
11319  // cause confusing diagnostic reports for uses of declarations within the
11320  // namespace.
11321  return;
11322  }
11323  } else if (isa<UsingDecl, UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl,
11324  UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D)) {
11325  S.Diag(AL.getRange().getBegin(), diag::warn_deprecated_ignored_on_using)
11326  << AL;
11327  return;
11328  }
11329 
11330  // Handle the cases where the attribute has a text message.
11331  StringRef Str, Replacement;
11332  if (AL.isArgExpr(0) && AL.getArgAsExpr(0) &&
11333  !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 0, Str))
11334  return;
11335 
11336  // Support a single optional message only for Declspec and [[]] spellings.
11337  if (AL.isDeclspecAttribute() || AL.isStandardAttributeSyntax())
11338  AL.checkAtMostNumArgs(S, 1);
11339  else if (AL.isArgExpr(1) && AL.getArgAsExpr(1) &&
11340  !S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, 1, Replacement))
11341  return;
11342 
11343  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 && AL.isCXX11Attribute() && !AL.isGNUScope())
11344  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(), diag::ext_cxx14_attr) << AL;
11345 
11346  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) DeprecatedAttr(S.Context, AL, Str, Replacement));
11347 }
11348 
11349 static bool isGlobalVar(const Decl *D) {
11350  if (const auto *S = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
11351  return S->hasGlobalStorage();
11352  return false;
11353 }
11354 
11355 static bool isSanitizerAttributeAllowedOnGlobals(StringRef Sanitizer) {
11356  return Sanitizer == "address" || Sanitizer == "hwaddress" ||
11357  Sanitizer == "memtag";
11358 }
11359 
11360 static void handleNoSanitizeAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D, const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11361  if (!AL.checkAtLeastNumArgs(S, 1))
11362  return;
11363 
11364  std::vector<StringRef> Sanitizers;
11365 
11366  for (unsigned I = 0, E = AL.getNumArgs(); I != E; ++I) {
11367  StringRef SanitizerName;
11368  SourceLocation LiteralLoc;
11369 
11370  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(AL, I, SanitizerName, &LiteralLoc))
11371  return;
11372 
11373  if (parseSanitizerValue(SanitizerName, /*AllowGroups=*/true) ==
11374  SanitizerMask() &&
11375  SanitizerName != "coverage")
11376  S.Diag(LiteralLoc, diag::warn_unknown_sanitizer_ignored) << SanitizerName;
11377  else if (isGlobalVar(D) && !isSanitizerAttributeAllowedOnGlobals(SanitizerName))
11378  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported_global)
11379  << AL << SanitizerName;
11380  Sanitizers.push_back(SanitizerName);
11381  }
11382 
11383  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context) NoSanitizeAttr(S.Context, AL, Sanitizers.data(),
11384  Sanitizers.size()));
11385 }
11386 
11387 static void handleNoSanitizeSpecificAttr(Sema &S, Decl *D,
11388  const ParsedAttr &AL) {
11389  StringRef AttrName = AL.getAttrName()->getName();
11390  normalizeName(AttrName);
11391  StringRef SanitizerName = llvm::StringSwitch<StringRef>(AttrName)
11392  .Case("no_address_safety_analysis", "address")
11393  .Case("no_sanitize_address", "address")
11394  .Case("no_sanitize_thread", "thread")
11395  .Case("no_sanitize_memory", "memory");
11396  if (isGlobalVar(D) && SanitizerName != "address")
11397  S.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_decl_type)
11398  << AL << AL.isRegularKeywordAttribute() << ExpectedFunction;
11399 
11400  // FIXME: Rather than create a NoSanitizeSpecificAttr, this creates a
11401  // NoSanitizeAttr object; but we need to calculate the correct spelling list
11402  // index rather than incorrectly assume the index for NoSanitizeSpecificAttr
11403  // has the same spellings as the index for NoSanitizeAttr. We don't have a
11404  // general way to "translate" between the two, so this hack attempts to work
11405  // around the issue with hard-coded indices. This is critical for calling
11406  // getSpelling() or prettyPrint() on the resulting semantic attribute object
11407  // without failing assertions.
11408  unsigned TranslatedSpellingIndex = 0;
11409  if (AL.isStandardAttributeSyntax())
11410  TranslatedSpellingIndex = 1;
11411 
11412  AttributeCommonInfo Info = AL;
11413  Info.setAttributeSpellingListIndex(TranslatedSpellingIndex);
11414  D->addAttr(::new (S.Context)
11415  NoSanitizeAttr(S.Context, Info, &SanitizerName, 1));
11416 }

11420  D->addAttr(Internal);
11421 }
